front.lore: Naroon Cuthus' predecessor as Jabba's right hand man. Sees what he wants to see. Hears what he wants to hear. Has a pet womp rat named Worra.
front.title: •Boelo

front.gametext: * Ferocity = destiny -1. Habitat: Dagobah. Parasite: Character (that can move). Relocate Bog-wing and host up to two sites away (opponent of victim chooses). Bog-wing then detaches.
front.lore: Avian jungle-dweller. Fiercely territorial. Uses powerful talons to pick up and bear off victims. Carries up to nine times it's own body weight. Feeds primarily on root lizards and vine snakes.
front.title: Bog-wing

front.gametext: Once during your deploy phase, may draw destiny: (0-2) no result; (3-4) Askol draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise for remainder of turn; (5+) Askol is power +4 for remainder of turn.
front.lore: At birth, a Pacithhips gene configuration usually indicates if they're to become a farmer, an intellectual, or a warrior. Bok Askol's destiny remained a mystery for years.
front.title: •Bok Askol

rulings: The values listed are ranges, for example a destiny of 3.5 fulfills the 3-4 range.
If a draw doesn't fit any range (such as a draw of 2.5), no result.

front.gametext: Deploy on a non-interior planet site (except Dagobah). May move to an adjacent non-interior site at start of your move phase. Your bombers at a related system you control may move to this site. Bombers must return to system at end of your battle phase (if possible).
front.lore: Bombers can sometimes slip past orbital defenses. Making a lowaltitude bombing run allows 'surgical strikes,' even in cramped situations such as canyons and city streets.
front.title: <>Bombing Run

front.gametext: Deploy on Podrace Arena. Once per game, either player may initiate a Podrace: During your control phase, each player may draw one race destiny. Each player may place any drawn race destiny on their Podracer (or on Podrace Arena if they have none) or in their Used Pile. During any move phase, winner is any player with a race total > 24 and greater than opponent's highest race total. Winner retrieves 6 Force and loser loses 6 Force. Place all race destiny cards in owner's Used Piles and all Podracers are lost.
front.title: Boonta Eve Podrace

rulings: Winner of podrace is determined automatically during any move phase.

front.gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your TIE Advanced x1. May target a starship using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Subtract 1 if targeting a capital starship. Add 1 if targeting a starfighter. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.
front.lore: Enhanced TIE blaster cannon prototype. Greater range and power. Improved targeting software. Requires more powerful energy cells. Tested by elite TIE squadrons.
front.title: Boosted TIE Cannon

front.gametext: Cancel either: Report To Lord Vader, Scomp Link Access, Rebel Planners, Rebel Reinforcements, Gift of the Mentor, Panic, Don't Get Cocky, Skywalkers, Demotion, Combined Attack or Surprise Assault.
front.lore: 'Uh...had a slight weapons malfunction. But, uh, everything's perfectly all right now. We're fine. We're all fine here, now, thank you. How are you?'
front.title: Boring Conversation Anyway

combo: Bossk + Luke? Luuuuke! + any Chewbacca Makes Chewbacca Lost. (Indiana Jones Jedi Knight)

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Hound's Tooth, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. Adds 1 to attrition against opponent in battles at same site. While present, may reduce Chewie's forfeit to zero while here.
front.lore: Male Trandoshan bounty hunter. Strong but clumsy. Extremely proud and arrogant. Suffered a humiliating defeat at the hands of Chewbacca and his partner Han Solo.
front.title: •Bossk

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. While at same site as a smuggler, power +3. While with opponent's smuggler or Wookiee, opponent may not draw more than one battle destiny here. Immune to attrition < number of opponent's smugglers on table.
front.lore: Male Trandoshan bounty hunter. Strong but clumsy. Extremely proud and arrogant. Suffered a humiliating defeat at the hands of Chewbacca and his partner Han Solo.
front.title: •Bossk (V)

front.gametext: May add 6 passengers and 1 vehicle. Permanent pilot is •Bossk, who provides ability of 2, adds 2 to power and adds one battle destiny. Deploys and moves like a starfighter. Has ship-docking capability.
front.lore: Bossk once said of his ship, 'Greeezeg out nikek!'
front.title: •Bossk In Hound's Tooth

front.gametext: Permanent pilot is •Bossk, who provides ability of 2.  During battle with opponent's [Independent] starship (or Falcon), may add one destiny to total power or attrition.  Immune to attrition < 4.
front.lore: Bossk once said of his ship, 'Greeezeg out nikek!'
front.title: •Bossk In Hound's Tooth (V)

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Permanent weapon is •Bossk's Mortar Gun (may fire for free; draw destiny; may subtract or add 1 if at same site as a bounty; choose one character with that destiny number present to be captured.)
front.lore: Trandoshan bounty hunter. Modified his mortar gun to fire stun cartridges for live captures. Uses non-fragmentary capture rounds to minimize collateral damage.
front.title: •Bossk With Mortar Gun

rulings: Choosing a character counts as 'targeting a character with a weapon' and so is countered by (for example) Blaster Deflection.
May not target inactive cards or owner's cards.

front.gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on Bossk, 4 on any other warrior. May fire using 2 Force. Draw destiny. If destiny > 0, one card with that destiny number at same site is lost (your choice). If destiny = 0, mortar gun explodes and warrior firing it is lost.
front.lore: Relby-v10 micro grenade launcher. Modified version of the limited range CSPL 'Caspel' Projectile Launcher. Blows lots of stuff up.
front.title: •Bossk's Mortar Gun

rulings: Choosing a character counts as 'targeting a character with a weapon' and so is countered by e.g. Blaster Deflection.
May not target inactive cards or owner's cards.

combo: Bounty + Boba Fett (CC) Add five to the number of cards retrieved.
Bounty + Corporal Vandolay Makes We Have A Prisoner a Used Interrupt, and lets you pull a prison from Reserve Deck.
Bounty + Carbon-Freezing

front.gametext: Deploy on an opponent's non-droid character. If subsequently captured, seized by a bounty hunter and then transferred to a prison, retrieve Force equal to character's forfeit -2 and place Effect in Used Pile. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: One of the most profitable occupations in the galaxy is hunting down and capturing wanted beings. The more notable the quarry, the more profitable the venture.
front.title: Bounty

rulings: Only completes if the captive is imprisoned by the original seizing bounty hunter card.

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Once per game, may take Finalizer into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Once per character, when you deploy Hux, Kylo, Phasma, or Snoke to an [Episode VII] battleground, may take any one card from Used Pile into hand; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Blank.
front.title: •Bow To The First Order

rulings: The Force used to deploy Hux, Kylo, Phasma, or Snoke is already in the Used Pile and is among the cards that will be searched through.

front.gametext: Power +2 at Cantina. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Once per turn, may exchange a docking bay from hand with top card of Lost Pile. Your docking bay transit is free when moving to or from same site. Immune to attrition < 3.
front.lore: Elder of a dextrous race of renowned travelers. Gambler. Frequents casinos, bars and spaceports. Originally from distant planet Dor Nameth
front.title: •Brangus Glee

front.gametext: If an Imperial just moved to an Echo site, deploy on your side of table. While you have presence at an Echo site, your total power is +1 in battles at Hoth sites.
front.lore: 'Imperial troops have entered the base! Imperial troops have entered-'
front.title: •Breached Defenses

front.gametext: Just after the weapons phase of a battle, use 2 Force to cause each player to target one of that player's characters involved in the battle. Target characters cannot apply their ability toward drawing battle destiny this turn.
front.lore: Eliciting fear from the opponent gives the dark side a powerful advantage.
front.title: •Brief Loss Of Control

back.gametext: Bring Him Before Me:Deploy Throne Room, Insignificant Rebellion and Your Destiny.{For} remainder of game, Scanning Crew may not be played. Opponent's cards that place a character out of play may not target Luke. You may deploy Emperor (deploy -2) from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Opponent may deploy Luke from Reserve Deck (deploy -2; reshuffle) or Lost Pile. If Luke is present with Vader and Vader is not escorting a captive, Luke is captured and seized by Vader. Vader may not transfer Luke.{Flip} this card if Luke captured.Take Your Father's Place:{While} this side up, lose 1 Force at end of each of your turns. Once during each of your turns, when Vader, Luke (even as a non-frozen captive) and Emperor are all present at your Throne Room, you may initiate a Luke/Vader duel: Each player draws two destiny. Add ability. Highest total wins. If Vader wins, opponent loses 3 Force. If Luke wins, shuffle Reserve Deck and draw destiny; if destiny > 12, Luke crosses to Dark Side, totally depleting opponent's Life Force.{Flip} if Luke neither present with Vader nor a captive.
back.title: Bring Him Before Me / Take Your Father's Place

front.gametext: Bring Him Before Me:Deploy Throne Room, Insignificant Rebellion and Your Destiny.{For} remainder of game, Scanning Crew may not be played. Opponent's cards that place a character out of play may not target Luke. You may deploy Emperor (deploy -2) from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Opponent may deploy Luke from Reserve Deck (deploy -2; reshuffle) or Lost Pile. If Luke is present with Vader and Vader is not escorting a captive, Luke is captured and seized by Vader. Vader may not transfer Luke.{Flip} this card if Luke captured.Take Your Father's Place:{While} this side up, lose 1 Force at end of each of your turns. Once during each of your turns, when Vader, Luke (even as a non-frozen captive) and Emperor are all present at your Throne Room, you may initiate a Luke/Vader duel: Each player draws two destiny. Add ability. Highest total wins. If Vader wins, opponent loses 3 Force. If Luke wins, shuffle Reserve Deck and draw destiny; if destiny > 12, Luke crosses to Dark Side, totally depleting opponent's Life Force.{Flip} if Luke neither present with Vader nor a captive.
front.title: Bring Him Before Me / Take Your Father's Place

rulings: The 'deploy -2' text only applies while deploying using this objective.
If Vader is aboard an open vehicle without capacity for Luke, Vader automatically disembarks to seize Luke.

front.gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Apprentices subtract X from training destiny, where X = ability - Jedi Test number (minimum zero). Also, once per turn, you may use 2 Force to move the top card of opponent's Force Pile to the top of opponent's Reserve Deck.
front.lore: To effectively use the Force, a Jedi is required to learn concentration. A Jedi who gives in to distraction places both himself and his friends in peril.
front.title: •Broken Concentration

front.gametext: Habitat: planet sites (except Hoth). Does not attack your characters. When at a Jabba's palace site, prevents opponent's characters from using their landspeed.
front.lore: Watchbeast. Unwittingly foiled Ree Yees' plot to kill Jabba with a thermal detonator when it ate a crucial component. Louder than it is tough. Keeps watch for unwary intruders.
front.title: •Bubo

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Your other bounty hunters here are power +1. Draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise. During battle, if with your other bounty hunter, may cancel the immunity to attrition of a Jedi here.
front.lore: Duros bounty hunter.
front.title: •Cad Bane

front.gametext: Deploy on Imperial or Jawa. During your control phase, may steal one droid at same site if it is controlled by a Restraining Bolt. After droid is stolen, Restraining Bolt returns to owner's hand.
front.lore: Hand-held device that commands restraining bolt. Each caller can be keyed to a specific bolt. Used throughout the galaxy. Also called 'owners.'
front.title: Caller

front.gametext: If opponent just initiated a Force drain at a non-shielded planet location, deploy on that location. Your characters, vehicles and starships may deploy here regardless of presence and location deployment restrictions. (Immune to Control.)
front.lore: Adventurous pilot. Boasts to Jabba that he has traveled to every uncharted planet in the galaxy. Has been hired by the Empire to keep an eye out for Rebel activity.
front.title: Cane Adiss

rulings: This does <u>not</u> circumvent restrictions listed on an Objective (even if the Objective references limiting deployment at certain locations).
This does <u>not</u> circumvent text on a card that says it only deploys if a certain Objective on table.
This does <u>not</u> circumvent rules or text that certain cards cannot <u>exist</u> at certain locations (e.g. no starfighters at Cantina or Endor: Dense Forest).
This does <u>not</u> circumvent deployment restriction text that is entirely unrelated to locations (e.g. Emperor's Orders or Revenge Of The Sith).
Allows cards to deploy regardless of presence or Force icons.
Allows cards to deploy to Dagobah or Ahch-To.
Allows cards to deploy regardless of their own game text saying they can only deploy to certain locations.
Allows cards to deploy regardless of game text on other cards (except Objectives) saying certain cards may not deploy to certain locations.

If deployed on a non-shielded location (e.g. Hoth: Defensive Perimeter) and then that location becomes shielded later, Cane Adiss remains there and will allow cards to deploy there regardless of the shield.

front.gametext: During your control phase, may search your Reserve Deck, take one Laser Gate, Heart Of The Chasm or Rite Of Passage into hand and reshuffle. Opponent's characters may not move from same site as Bewil to a mobile site.
front.lore: Tactical officer from Dentaal. Leader. Familiar with utilizing computer controls to lure an invading enemy into a tactically weak position.
front.title: •Captain Bewil

front.gametext: While at a Cloud City site, adds one to the number of Bespin locations required to cancel Dark Deal. Once per turn, if Dark Deal on table, may search your Force Pile and take one Interrupt into hand; reshuffle.
front.lore: Tactical officer from Dentaal. Leader. Familiar with utilizing computer controls to lure an invading enemy into a tactically weak position.
front.title: •Captain Bewil (V)

front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of any capital starship he pilots. Once per game may take Activate The Droids into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. While aboard Blockade Flagship, it is immune to attrition < 5 and Activate The Droids is immune to Alter.
front.lore: Neimoidian captain of the Trade Federation Droid Control Ship blockading Naboo. Cowardly, lazy, and extremely greedy.
front.title: •Captain Daultay Dofine

front.gametext: Deploys for free to Thrawn's location. Each other Imperial aboard same capital starship is forfeit +2. Adds 2 to power of any capital starship he pilots (3 if Chimaera). While aboard Chimaera with Thrawn, also adds 2 to that starship's armor and hyperspeed.
front.lore: Corellian leader. Lied about his age to enter the Academy. Took command of Chimaera when its captain was killed at the Battle of Endor. Admires Grand Admiral Thrawn.
front.title: •Captain Gilad Pellaeon

front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of any capital starship he pilots. While aboard a Star Destroyer, adds 1 to armor, adds 1 to hyperspeed and, once during each of your move phases, may cancel Landing Claw at same system or sector.
front.lore: Elite fleet engineer. Technically brilliant. Key operator of magnetic signature sensors monitoring Star Destroyer hulls.
front.title: •Captain Godherdt

front.gametext: Deploys -2 aboard Scimitar 2. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When forfeited from a TIE/sa he is piloting, also satisfies all remaining attrition and battle damage against you.
front.lore: Often flies as top cover during bombing runs. Served with Death Squadron. Narrowly escaped death by space slug. Scored several kills against rebel blockade runners.
front.title: •Captain Jonus

rulings: Text to satisfy all battle damage and attrition requires that Jonus was piloting a TIE/sa.
Text to satisfy all battle damage and attrition requires either battle damage or attrition. It does not require both.

front.gametext: Permanent pilot is *Jonus, who provides ability of 2. This starship's missile weapon destiny draws are +1. If at a system you control, your total power at related sites is +1.
front.lore: TIE bomber repaired after being struck by an asteroid in the Anoat system. Stationed aboard second Death Star battle station.
front.title: •Captain Jonus In Scimitar 2

front.gametext: Once during each of your control phases, you may use 2 Force to take one Scanning Crew into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Docking bay security officer. Leader. Honored for bravery aboard the Star Destroyer Thunderflare where he rescued five officers from the wreckage of a shuttle crash.
front.title: •Captain Khurgee

combo: Captain Lennox + Tractor Beam + Besieged

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots (3 if starship is Tyrant). When on a Star Destroyer, may use its tractor beam once during each of your control phases.
front.lore: Captain of the Imperial Star Destroyer Tyrant. An able leader. Unlike most Imperial officers, he is dedicated to his ship and crew. Finds political maneuvering distasteful.
front.title: •Captain Lennox

front.errataNotes: Last sentence reworded to be more clear. No gameplay change.
front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Avenger, that starship is also immune to attrition < 4. You may re-target applicable Utinni Effects to Needa. While Needa in battle, your other non-'hit' characters here may not be forfeited.
front.lore: Able leader and captain of the Avenger. Was given his command by Admiral Ozzel. Treated with suspicion by Darth Vader and the Emperor, who distrust Ozzel's close advisors.
front.title: •Captain Needa

rulings: Characters hit by weapons may be forfeited before forfeiting Needa.

front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. Deploys -1 to Finalizer. While piloting Finalizer, it is immune to attrition <8 (< 10 while with a Resistance character or [Resistance] starship). May be targeted by Imperial Command as an admiral (even if a unit of Force).
front.lore: Leader.
front.title: •Captain Peavey

front.gametext: Adds one battle destiny with a stormtrooper. If you just won a battle at same or related location, may retrieve a trooper.
front.lore: Female leader. Stormtrooper.
front.title: •Captain Phasma

rulings: Biker Scouts, Death Troopers, Sandtroopers, and Snowtroopers count as Stormtroopers.

front.gametext: Adds one battle destiny with a stormtrooper. If you just won a battle at same or related location, may retrieve a trooper.
front.lore: Female leader. Stormtrooper.
front.title: •Captain Phasma (AI)

rulings: Biker Scouts, Death Troopers, Sandtroopers, and Snowtroopers count as Stormtroopers.

front.gametext: Power +1 when at same site as Vader. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots (3 if starship is Executor). May use 1 Force to take one Probe Droid into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Captain on the Executor. Monitored probe droid telemetry. His flawless record of arrests and suppressions has contributed to an impressive rise through the ranks.
front.title: •Captain Piett

combo: Captain Sarkli + Nevar Yalnal

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. While he controls opponent's non-battleground location, opponent generates no Force here. While he occupies opponent's Subjugated system, Liberation is flipped and Local Uprising may not be flipped.
front.lore: Piett's nephew. Once granted audience with Emperor. On fast-track to promotion. Absolutely fearless spy.
front.title: •Captain Sarkli

combo: Captain Yorr In Onyx 2 + Colonel Jendon In Onyx 1

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots (3 if a starfighter). When piloting a TIE Defender and with Jendon, adds one battle destiny.
front.lore: Former member of Imperial Demonstration Team. Flew test flights during development of various TIE prototypes. Jendon's wingman. Has scored 24 combat victories.
front.title: •Captain Yorr

back.gametext: Carbon Chamber Testing:Deploy Carbonite Chamber, Carbonite Chamber Console and Security Tower with a Rebel (opponent's choice) from opponent's Reserve Deck (if possible) imprisoned there.{While} this side up, once during each of your deploy phases, you may deploy from Reserve Deck one Audience Chamber, Docking Bay 94 or East Platform; reshuffle. You may not play Dark Deal.{Flip} this card if you move a frozen captive to Audience Chamber (or if no Rebel was in opponent's Reserve Deck at start of game).My Favorite Decoration:{While} this side up, your aliens and starships are immune to attrition < 4 and, once during each of your control phases, you may retrieve 1 Force. While you have a frozen captive at Audience Chamber, Scum And Villainy is immune to Alter and during your deploy phase, you may deploy Scum And Villainy from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.{Place} out of play if there are no frozen captives on table (unless no Rebel was in opponent's Reserve Deck at start of game).
back.title: Carbon Chamber Testing / My Favorite Decoration

front.gametext: Carbon Chamber Testing:Deploy Carbonite Chamber, Carbonite Chamber Console and Security Tower with a Rebel (opponent's choice) from opponent's Reserve Deck (if possible) imprisoned there.{While} this side up, once during each of your deploy phases, you may deploy from Reserve Deck one Audience Chamber, Docking Bay 94 or East Platform; reshuffle. You may not play Dark Deal.{Flip} this card if you move a frozen captive to Audience Chamber (or if no Rebel was in opponent's Reserve Deck at start of game).My Favorite Decoration:{While} this side up, your aliens and starships are immune to attrition < 4 and, once during each of your control phases, you may retrieve 1 Force. While you have a frozen captive at Audience Chamber, Scum And Villainy is immune to Alter and during your deploy phase, you may deploy Scum And Villainy from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.{Place} out of play if there are no frozen captives on table (unless no Rebel was in opponent's Reserve Deck at start of game).
front.title: Carbon Chamber Testing / My Favorite Decoration

rulings: The Rebel deployed at start of game ignores location deployment restrictions, but not other restrictions.
Prisoner 2187 and TK-422 cannot be the targeted Rebel.
If Light is playing an Objective that starts a character on table, that character cannot be the targeted Rebel.
If no Rebel can be deployed, Dark may verify and Dark follows the 'if no Rebel was in opponent's Reserve Deck' instructions.

combo: Carbon-Freezing + R2-Q2 (Artoo-Kyootoo) While at a scomp link, R2-Q2 allows you to look at the top 3 cards of your Reserve Deck during your draw phase. Next turn, activate to the desired destiny, and leave it on top of your Reserve. When the control phase comes up; you draw the number you want to freeze your captive.
Carbon-Freezing + Ugnaughts + Ugloste

front.gametext: Deploy on Carbonite Chamber. During your control phase, may target one captive present. Draw destiny. If destiny < 5, captive lost. If destiny > 10, place on captive. Captive is 'frozen' and opponent loses 8 Force. If captive released, lose Effect. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: 'Oh, they've encased him in carbonite. He should be quite well protected. If he survived the freezing process, that is.'
front.title: Carbon-Freezing

front.gametext: Deploy on Carbonite Chamber. Adds 3 to Carbon-Freezing destiny. Also, once during each of your turns, you may use 1 Force to take one Ugnaught, Prepare The Chamber or Carbon-Freezing into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Most often used to freeze Tibanna gas for transport. Modified by Ugloste to work on humans. Intended to capture Luke Skywalker, the Emperor's prize.
front.title: •Carbonite Chamber Console

front.gametext: Deploy on Carbonite Chamber. Once during opponent's turn, if a frozen captive on table, may activate 1 Force. Once per turn, may use 1 Force to take He's All Yours, Bounty Hunter into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Most often used to freeze Tibanna gas for transport. Modified by Ugloste to work on humans. Intended to capture Luke Skywalker, the Emperor's prize.
front.title: •Carbonite Chamber Console (V)

combo: Carida + Aratech Corporation

front.gametext: Dark:  If you occupy, once during each of your control phases, you may lose 1 Force to retrieve one trooper into hand.  Light:  Force drain -1 here. If you do not occupy, all your troopers are forfeit -1.
front.title: •Carida

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

cancels: Sorry About The Mess & Blaster Proficiency

front.gametext: If a battle was just initiated, lose 2 Force to prevent all weapons from being fired for remainder of battle. OR Target all your battle droids at a site. Targets may not have their forfeit value reduced for remainder of turn. OR Cancel Blaster Proficiency.
front.lore: The amount of time it takes for a subcommand to transfer to an officer battle droid, and then to the rest of his regiment, is .396 of a second.
front.title: •Cease Fire!

front.gametext: When deployed, you may take one non-unique alien into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Your aliens deploy -1 to same or adjacent Tatooine site.
front.lore: Male Morseerian leader. Methane breather. Has ties to Tatooine's Imperial government. Uses alien agents to maintain surveillance on Jabba and the Rebellion.
front.title: •Chall Bekan

rulings: If deployed at the start of the game using the text on 'You Can Either Profit By This...', may take a non-unique alien into hand. In this case Dark's starting hand will have 1 more card than usual.

front.gametext: If Tarkin and a Rebel with ability > 2 are involved in the same battle, you may add one battle destiny (add two destiny if Rebel is Leia).
front.lore: 'You're far too trusting. Dantooine is too remote to make an effective demonstration. But don't worry...We will deal with your Rebel friends soon enough.'
front.title: Charming To The Last

rulings: Can only target Leia if she is a Rebel with ability > 2.

front.gametext: Power +2 and forfeit +1 while Ephant Mon is at Audience Chamber. When forfeited at same site as one of your alien leaders, may satisfy all remaining attrition against you.
front.lore: Most Chevin are mercenaries, gun runners and slavers. Have strong communities on their homeworld. Wear clothing only because others do.
front.title: Chevin

rulings: If prevented from being used to satisfy attrition (e.g. by Crack Shot), his text will not satisfy all remaining attrition.

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Power +1 at same site as Tarkin. If a battle was just initiated at a system where Bast is present with your non-droid character, may 'evacuate' (relocate) both to a related site.
front.lore: Aide to Grand Moff Tarkin. Rarely underestimates enemies. Learned cunning and patience hunting big game as a youth.
front.title: •Chief Bast

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. While with Vader in a battle you lost, Imperials and Imperial starships may be forfeited directly from your hand (for printed forfeit value) to reduce attrition and/or battle damage.
front.lore: Aide to Grand Moff Tarkin. Rarely underestimates enemies. Learned cunning and patience hunting big game as a youth.
front.title: •Chief Bast (V)

combo: Chief Retwin + Defel(s)

front.gametext: May use 3 Force to 'hide' (be excluded) from a battle. May use 2 Force to target one device or weapon present which deploys on a site. Draw destiny. If destiny > target's deploy cost, target is lost.
front.lore: Highly skilled saboteur. Former Imperial sympathizer who worked for the defense forces on his home planet, Ralltiir. Joined the Empire after Ralltiir's subjugation.
front.title: •Chief Retwin

rulings: May not target devices/weapons deployed on a character, vehicle, or starship (even if at a site).
May target (for example) Seekers, Vaporator, or Medium Repeating Blaster Cannon.

combo: Chimaera + Imperial Helmsman Draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

front.gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles and 4 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. Immune to attrition < 4 (< 5 while an Imperial leader aboard, < 6 while Thrawn aboard).
front.lore: Early model Imperial-class Star Destroyer. Acting command ship in the absence of Executor.
front.title: •Chimaera

combo: Chokk + Gamall Wironicc Power 11 while defending a battle and they double the weapons protection for your characters.
Chokk + Mighty Jabba + Ephant Mon

front.gametext: Each of your alien leaders present is defense value +2. Power +3 while defending a battle. Adds 2 to his total weapon destiny when firing a blaster. Your characters present may not have their forfeit value reduced.
front.lore: Klatooinian bodyguard currently in the paid service of Jabba the Hutt. Chokk takes pride in his work, and he is very good at it.
front.title: •Chokk

rulings: Chokk's first sentence (and last sentence) applies only to Dark's characters who are at the same site as Chokk and are present at that site. Chokk himself could be in a starship or enclosed vehicle.

front.gametext: While on Cloud City, adds 4 to destiny of each of your miners drawn for battle destiny and adds 1 to your Force drains at related cloud sectors where you have a minor or refinery (adds 2 if both).
front.lore: Placed several ISB agents and Aqualish in the Cloud City miner's guild. Promised a position when the Empire took over Cloud City. She's still waiting.
front.title: •Chyler

rulings: The phrase 'on Cloud City' means at a Cloud City site, not the Bespin: Cloud City sector.

combo: Close Call + Scanning Crew

front.gametext: USED: Cancel one asteroid destiny and cause it to be drawn again.  LOST: Lose 1 Force. Opponent must reveal the top card of Reserve Deck, Force Pile and Used Pile. Card(s) with lowest destiny number greater than zero are lost.

All modifiers transfer from the old destiny card to the new one.

front.lore: Stormtrooper from Coruscant. Honed piloting skills by racing swoops in underworld of Imperial capital. Still tempering his skills as a biker scout.
front.title: •Corporal Drelosyn

front.gametext: While Grenwick is on Death Star, your Death Star Sentry is not unique (•), is doubled, deploys free, applies all three of its modifiers and is immune to Alter. Power -1 when not on Death Star.
front.lore: Death Star trooper who witnessed Leia's interrogation. Senior tactical advisor to Sergeant Major Enfield. Coordinates security duty assignments for Detention Block AA-23.
front.title: •Corporal Grenwick

front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of any speeder bike he pilots. When firing a Scout Blaster, adds 1 to his total weapon destiny. When with Barich in a battle and piloting or driving a vehicle, may add that vehicle's maneuver to your total power.
front.lore: Son of a Tatooine diplomat. Stormtrooper. Biker scout. Deadly shot. Develops speeder bike tactics with Sergeant Barich. Hopes for promotion to Emperor's Demonstration Team.
front.title: •Corporal Misik

front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of any speeder bike he pilots. Once during each of your control phases, may target one opponent's missing character at same site. Draw destiny. Add 2 if Oberk is armed with a blaster. Target captured if total destiny > ability.
front.lore: Originally from Ukio. Stormtrooper assigned to search for Rebel activity on Endor. Trying to impress the commander of his biker scout detachment.
front.title: •Corporal Oberk

rulings: This card is not a commander.

combo: Corporal Prescott + any prison

front.gametext: When at a prison, instead of Force draining there, may use X Force to retrieve X Force, where X = number of imprisoned Rebels there. Power -2 when not on Death Star.
front.lore: Death Star trooper and detention block guard. Volunteered for prison detail. Takes sadistic pleasure in seeing Imperial justice enforced.
front.title: •Corporal Prescott

front.gametext: May use 1 Force to search your Reserve Deck and take one Spice Mines Of Kessel or Detention Block Corridor into hand. Shuffle, cut and replace. While at a mobile site, We Have A Prisoner is a Used Interrupt.
front.lore: ISB attache to the Executor. Detention Officer. Political Liaison for COMPNOR. Responsible for all prisoner transfers. Fiercely loyal to the Emperor's New Order.
front.title: •Corporal Vandolay

front.gametext: Adds 1 to power of anything he pilots. When deployed, may take an ISB agent here into hand. Once per turn, if you just drew an ISB agent for battle destiny anywhere, may take that card into hand to cancel and re-draw that destiny.
front.lore: ISB attache to the Executor. Detention Officer. Political Liaison for COMPNOR. Responsible for all prisoner transfers. Fiercely loyal to the Emperor's New Order.
front.title: •Corporal Vandolay (V)

front.gametext: Deploy on Space Slug Belly. At the end of each player's turn, for every character and starship that player has present, that player must lose 1 Force. Effect canceled if Space Slug lost.
front.lore: The interior or a space slug's maw is mildly acidic. Long-term exposure to this corrosive environment can cause considerable damage.
front.title: <>Corrosive Damage

front.gametext: Dark:  If you control, all non-unique Imperials are power and forfeit +1 and Imperial trooper guards may move.  Light:  If you control, Force drain -1 here.
front.title: •Corulag

front.gametext: While at a Corulag site: adds 1 to your Force drains there, is power +1 (or +2 if your trooper is on Corulag) and, once during each of your deploy phases, may deploy one site to Corulag from Reserve Deckreshuffle.
front.lore: Independent traders make money selling equipment to the academy at Corulag. Resentful of the Alliance pilots that disrupt their shipping lines.
front.title: Corulag Operative

front.gametext: Dark:  If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Coruscant sites.  Light:  If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Coruscant sites.
front.title: •Coruscant

front.title: •Coruscant

front.title: •Coruscant (V)

combo: Coruscant Guard + Nar Shaddaa Wind Chimes

front.gametext: Once per turn, may use 1 Force to add 2 to politics of one of your senators present for remainder of turn. While present at Galactic Senate, all characters without politics here are forfeit = 0 (except Coruscant Guards).
front.lore: Coruscant Guards are an elite force whose assignments include the protection of important political figures, as well as the policing of Coruscant's higher profile city districts.
front.title: Coruscant Guard

front.gametext: Dark:  Grievous moves from here for free.  Light:  May not be separated from Coruscant: Private Platform.
front.title: •Coruscant: 500 Republica

front.title: •Coruscant: Docking Bay

front.gametext: Dark:  Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force (free if an Imperial present).  Light:  Your docking bay transit from here requires 3 Force. Your transit to here requires +8 Force.
front.title: •Coruscant: Docking Bay

pulledBy: Begin Landing Your Troops & Fighters Straight Ahead

front.title: •Coruscant: Xizor's Palace

front.gametext: Deploys -1 if Sidious (or Insidious Prisoner) on table. Power +1 for each Jedi here. May be targeted by Force Lightning. Once per game, if opponent just initiated battle here, may take Force Lightning or Force Push into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Immune to attrition < 6 (< 8 if with a Jedi).
front.lore: Serrennoian leader. Trade Federation.
front.title: •Count Dooku

rulings: When using this text, treat all instances of the word 'Emperor' on Force Lightning as 'Dooku' instead.

cancels: A Force drain at one location
combo: Counter Assault + Luke? Luuuuke! The power reduction on this card can make it easier to have a successful Counter Assault, especially if the Utinni Effect is targeting Luke.
Counter Assault + Lateral Damage (Indiana Jones Jedi Knight)

front.gametext: Use 1 Force to cancel a Force drain at one location. Draw one destiny for each character, starship and vehicle the opponent has present. Compare your destiny total to opponent's power total. Player with lowest total loses Force equal to the difference.
front.lore: Imperial stormtroopers use tactical training to regroup and mount a surprise counterattack, such as when they halted Han Solo's wild pursuit.
front.title: Counter Assault

rulings: When this interrupt begins its result, the total power and the number of destiny draws are 'locked in' and will not change.
Do not draw destinies for characters inside starships or enclosed vehicles.
This is not a 'battle' and cards may not be forfeited.

cancels: A Force drain at a mobile site

front.gametext: Cancel Surprise Assault. OR Use 4 Force to cancel opponent's Force drain at a mobile site. Deploy (for free) from Reserve Deck any number of non-unique troopers to that site. (Light Side characters, vehicles and starships here may 'escape' to Used Pile).
front.lore: 'He certainly has courage.' 'What good will it do us if he gets himself killed?'
front.title: Counter Surprise Assault

front.gametext: If a battle that opponent initiated just ended, initiate a new battle at same location. 'Reacts' are allowed only for opponent, but cards may not 'react' away or hide from battle. Loser ignores battle damage. If your trooper present there, add one battle destiny.
front.lore: The Imperial forces on Endor quickly responded to the Rebel intrusion. Commander Igar had a plan in place to deal with such a commando force of Rebels.
front.title: •Counterattack

rulings: Allows cards to participate in another battle and fire weapons again.
Does not allow cards to 'react' a second time in one turn.
The player who played this Interrupt initiated the battle and by default gets first action of each segment.
A card excluded from the previous battle is not necessarily excluded from the new battle.

Bounty Hunters are forfeit +2 and immune to Goo Nee Tay. You may not play Scanning Crew. rulings: A frozen captive (such as from Profit) counts as an ability = 0 captive towards the Flip condition.
When deploying a starship from Reserve Deck, if the starship is unpiloted, may combine it with a pilot from hand, allowing deployment to a system or sector.

Once the player initiates the action to deploy a card from Reserve Deck, they must deploy something if possible. On the 0-side, player is <u>required</u> to combine an unpiloted starship with a pilot from hand if that is the only possible option.

If the attempt to deploy a card from Reserve Deck fails, opponent verifies Reserve Deck (not hand). On the 0-side, a judge may be called to review hand and Reserve Deck to confirm that no starship + pilot deployment was possible.

front.gametext: If you have a piloted AT-AT present at a site, target opponent's non-creature vehicle present at same or adjacent exterior site. Draw destiny. If AT-AT has a vehicle weapon, add 1 to destiny draw. Target 'crashes' if total destiny > 3.
front.lore: AT-AT weapons are rarely quick enough to score a direct hit on a fast-moving snowspeeder. They are more likely to wing a craft, causing a forced landing.
front.title: Crash Landing

front.gametext: Deploy on table. When you fire two weapons (except lightsabers) in a battle, your total power is +5. Also, S-foils and Maneuvering Flaps are suspended where you have either a weapon present or a starship (or vehicle) with maneuver > 3 present. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Scout walker pilots are trained to set up a deadly heavy fire zone. This tactic can be disrupted by enemy weapons fire.
front.title: •Crossfire

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points
rulings: If a weapon firing is canceled, that weapon did not fire and does not count towards Crossfire.

front.gametext: Plays on table. S-foils and Maneuvering Flaps are suspended where you have either a weapon present or a starship (or vehicle) with maneuver > 3 present.
front.lore: Scout walker pilots are trained to set up a deadly heavy fire zone. This tactic can be disrupted by enemy weapons fire.
front.title: •Crossfire

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Once per turn, may take I Have You Now or Evader into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. At mobile sites, opponent draws no more than two battle destiny per battle. Evader is immune to Sense. May lose 1 Force to cancel Clash of Sabers. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: After dueling his son and seizing control of a city in the clouds, Vader resumed his quest to destroy the Alliance.
front.title: •Crush The Rebellion

front.gametext: Opponent may not 'react' to or from same site. You may 'react' to a battle or Force drain at same or adjacent Jabba's Palace site by deploying (at normal use of the Force) one non-unique alien to that site from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Very common communications droid. Some have been modified to be defense drones. Programmed to warn their masters of an imminent attack.
front.title: CZ-4

front.gametext: Dark:  If you occupy, opponent may not Force drain at related locations.  Light:  Neither player may Force drain here.
front.title: •Dagobah

combo: Dagobah: Cave + Failure At The Cave

front.gametext: Dark:  If opponent has presence here, your Force Icons are canceled.  Light:  Lose 1 Force during each of your control phases if Yoda on table but not on Dagobah.
front.title: •Dagobah: Cave

front.gametext: Once per battle, may use 1 Force to 'eat the soup' of (place out of play) one opposing non-droid character just lost or forfeited at same site. * Power = 1 + total ability of all victims whose soup was eaten.
front.lore: Anzati assassin. Cheek-folds hide proboscises which allow him to 'eat the soup' (consume the life Force) of his victims. Smokes t'bac. Currently working for Jabba.
front.title: •Dannik Jerriko

rulings: Only gets bonus power from characters if Dannik used his 'eat the soup' text on them.
If Dannik leaves table and a new Dannik enters play, the previous bonus power is retained.

front.gametext: Dark:  Your starships may move here as a 'react'.  Light:  (none)
front.title: •Dantooine

front.gametext: While at a Dantooine site: adds 1 to your Force drains there, is power +1 (or +2 if your thief is on Dantooine) and, once during each of your deploy phases, may deploy one site to Dantooine from Reserve Deck- reshuffle.
front.lore: Corrupt Pacithhip businessmen. Report to the Empire on who makes contributions to the Alliance.
front.title: Dantooine Operative

front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. Adds 1 to weapon destiny draws of anything he is aboard as a passenger.
front.lore: Cocky gunner and bounty hunter. Maintains a residence on Nar Shaddaa, the spaceport moon of the Hutt homeworld. To his companions' delight, he's nearly as good as he boasts.
front.title: •Danz Borin

front.gametext: If Tarkin and either Tagge or Motti are in a battle together, you may add two battle destiny. OR Cancel Restricted Deployment or Rebel Barrier.
front.lore: Imperial leaders are ruthlessly effective when working together. Tarkin, Motti and Tagge presented a deadly combination as they plotted to, 'crush the Rebellion.'
front.title: •Dark Collaboration

combo: Dark Deal + Aqualish

front.gametext: Deploy on Bespin: Cloud City if you control that sector and at least three related sites. At each Cloud City site, your total power is +4 and your Force drains are +2. Effect canceled if opponent occupies four Bespin locations. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: 'Perhaps you think you're being treated unfairly?' 'No.' 'Good. It would be unfortunate if I had to leave a garrison here.'
front.title: •Dark Deal

front.gametext: Deploy on your side of table. When Surprise Assault is played, may use 1 Force to add one destiny to your total. Also, when Sense or Alter is played, may use X Force to exclude X Jedi from being the 'highest-ability character.'
front.lore: 'The ability to destroy a planet is insignificant next to the power of the Force.'
front.title: •Dark Forces

rulings: The player playing Sense or Alter must then immediately choose a new target character if possible. If not possible, the Sense or Alter fails.
If Alter is played in response to the attempted deployment of this Effect, this Effect's game text may not be used yet.

front.gametext: Select one site under 'nighttime conditions.' Target every character there (except droids) and draw one destiny each. If destiny > ability, character 'sleeps' (power, forfeit and ability = 0, 'game text' unusable) until the end of your next turn.
front.lore: After surviving Tarkin's extortion, kidnapping, threats of execution and the assault of the Interrogator droid, Princess Leia was asleep when her rescuers came.
front.title: •••Dark Hours

rulings: Characters introduced to this site after Dark Hours begins its result are not targeted.
If Dark fails to draw destiny (empty Reserve Deck), Light chooses the outcome.
A character affected by multiple copies of Dark Hours remains asleep until all copies leave table.

front.gametext: Use X Force to deploy on your warrior where X = (7 - warrior's ability). May add 1 to Force drain where present. May target a character or creature using X Force. Draw two destiny. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.
front.lore: Multifaceted jewels focus light into a deadly blade. Projects a meter-long beam of pure energy. A lightsaber is constructed personally by a Jedi as a part of training.
front.title: Dark Jedi Lightsaber

pulledBy: I Will Finish What You Started

front.gametext: Deploy on Aurra, Grievous, or your warrior of ability > 4. May add 1 to Force drain where present. May target a character or creature for free. Draw two destiny. Target hit, and may not be used to satisfy attrition, if total destiny > defense value.
front.lore: Multifaceted jewels focus light into a deadly blade. Projects a meter-long beam of pure energy. A lightsaber is constructed personally by a Jedi as a part of training.
front.title: Dark Jedi Lightsaber (V)

front.gametext: If one of your Dark Jedi is present during any battle, use 1 Force to cause all other Imperials there to battle at double power.
front.lore: A Dark Lord's presence motivates Imperial troops. 'See to it personally, Commander.'
front.title: Dark Jedi Presence

combo: Dark Maneuvers + Tallon Roll

front.gametext: Add 2 to maneuver and 1 to power of any starfighter for the remainder of this turn. If it has hyperdrive, also add 2 to hyperspeed. (Interrupt may even affect the result immediately after a destiny draw targeting the starfighter's maneuver.)
front.lore: Imperial TIE fighters, while easily damaged, are very fast and agile. Sophisticated tactics are executed to take advantage of Rebel X-wing and Y-wing weaknesses.
front.title: Dark Maneuvers

front.gametext: Add 2 to maneuver and 1 to power of any TIE for the remainder of this turn. (Interrupt may even affect the result immediately after a destiny draw targeting the TIE's maneuver.) OR Target two starfighters (your TIE/ln and any Rebel starfighter) present at same system or sector. Each player draws destiny. Opponent totals destiny and starship's power. You total destiny, TIE's power, and TIE's maneuver. Lowest total loses starfighter (if tied, neither starfighter is lost).
front.title: Dark Maneuvers & Tallon Roll

front.gametext: If opponent just initiated a duel, use 3 Force to cancel it. OR Take Deep Hatred into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. OR If Maul has no combat cards, target a Jedi to place one of their combat cards (random selection) in opponent's Used Pile. (Immune to Sense.)
front.lore: While Qui-Gon meditated to regain strength lost during the ferocious duel, Darth Maul paced impatiently outside the energy barrier like a caged krayt dragon.
front.title: •Dark Rage

front.gametext: If you just targeted with a lightsaber, add 3 to your total weapon destiny. OR Cancel Swing-And-A-Miss. OR Lose 1 Force to cause one opponent's just 'hit' character to be immediately placed in Lost Pile.
front.lore: Many have experienced the awesome power of the Dark Lord in battle. Few have lived to tell about it.
front.title: •Dark Strike

front.gametext: Deploy on any exterior planet site (except Hoth) or any interior vehicle site. Opponent's Force drains are -1 here. (Immune to Alter when a swamp creature is present.)
front.lore: Swamp predators require damp and cluttered environments to enhance their camouflage and stealth. 'Something just moved past my leg.'
front.title: Dark Waters

rulings: If on a vehicle site, characters there may be attacked despite being 'aboard a vehicle'.

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. If opponent initiates a battle at same system, may reveal the top card of your Reserve Deck. If it is a Star Destroyer, may deploy it here for free. Otherwise, card is lost.
front.lore: Jawa who has inside connections with the Empire. Frequently speaks with his Imperial contact, whom he reports to regarding Rebel activity in the Outer Rim.
front.title: •Daroe

cards.conceptBy: (Original concept by Ryan Jellison and Tom Marlin)

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Information Broker. When deployed, may deploy a droid here or a Restraining Bolt from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. During battle, may retarget an opponent's weapon targeting your droid to another one of your characters present (even Daroe).
front.lore: Jawa who has inside connections with the Empire. Frequently speaks with his Imperial contact, whom he reports to regarding Rebel activity in the Outer Rim.
front.title: •Daroe (V)

pulls: A droid or a restraining bolt
rulings: If deployed at the start of the game using the text on 'You Can Either Profit By This...', may deploy a droid (the droid is free).
Restraining bolt can be deployed to a different location.

combo: Darth Maul + Maul's Sith Infiltrator at Tatooine system: Deploys for 6, it's Maul -2 and -3 on his ship.
Darth Maul + Maul Strikes
Darth Maul + The Phantom Menace While present with an opponent's Jedi, Maul is defense value +2 and immune to attrition.
Darth Maul + I Have You Now Add one battle destiny (two if Rebel is Luke) if a Dark Jedi and a Rebel with ability > 2 are involved in the same battle.
Darth Maul + Force Field Cancels an attempt to target a Dark Jedi with a character weapon.

front.gametext: Deploys -2 to Tatooine. During your control phase may lose 1 Force to duel opponent's Jedi present. Both players draw 2 destiny. Loser is lost. Unless opponent's character of ability > 3 here, opponent's total ability here = 0. Immune to attrition < 5.
front.lore: Apprentice to Darth Sidious. Sent to capture Queen Amidala on Tatooine. Full of anger and fury as a child. Sidious used Maul's pent-up rage to train him in the ways of the Sith.
front.title: •Darth Maul

rulings: The loser of the duel is the character with the lower total.
If the duel totals are tied, there is no winner and no loser.

If a character of ability > 3 is excluded and this causes Maul's text to make Dark control the location, the excluded character is still active for the purposes of Objective flip conditions (e.g. Quiet Mining Colony) and for the purposes of preventing cards like Haven from leaving table.

front.lore: Trade Federation.
front.title: •Darth Maul, Lone Hunter

front.gametext: Deploys -2 to Coruscant. When Maul swings a lightsaber at a Jedi, each weapon destiny draw is +1. If Maul hits a Jedi Master during battle, that Jedi Master is power -3 for remainder of battle. Immune to Clash Of Sabers and attrition < 5.
front.lore: Fueled by a hatred of the Jedi and an arsenal of dark abilities, this Sith warrior is a powerful weapon for his dark mentor, Darth Sidious.
front.title: •Darth Maul, Young Apprentice

front.gametext: Deploys -2 to Coruscant. When Maul swings a lightsaber at a Jedi, each weapon destiny draw is +1. If Maul hits a Jedi Master during battle, that Jedi Master is power -3 for remainder of battle. Immune to Clash Of Sabers and attrition < 5.

front.gametext: While no other characters present, if opponent just lost a Jedi from table, may lose 1 Force to place that Jedi out of play. While on Coruscant, may use 1 Force to add one battle destiny in a battle your Neimoidian is in. Immune to attrition.
front.lore: Mysterious Sith Master who is manipulating the Trade Federation for his own nefarious ends. Shrouded in mystery, his identity and agenda remain unclear.
front.title: •Darth Sidious

front.lore: These Trade Federation droids are basically a mobile weapons platform. They were commissioned by the Trade Federation from the Colicoids of Colla IV.

combo: Devastator + Imperial Helmsman Draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

front.gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles and 4 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 2.
front.lore: Supported the devastating subjugation of Ralltiir. While under the command of Darth Vader, chased and captured the traitor Princess Leia Organa aboard the consular ship Tantive IV.
front.title: •Devastator

front.gametext: Deploy only to a desert or Tatooine site. Ability = ¼. May add 1 'rider' (passenger). When 'ridden' by a Sandtrooper, may draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

front.title: Dewback

front.title: •••DFS Squadron Starfighter

front.lore: Tactical support starfighter that utilizes learning subroutines to maximize the effectiveness of droid starfighter offensive strategies.
front.title: •DFS-1015

front.gametext: Deploys -1 to same location as your battleship. While with another droid starfighter at a system, opponent may not draw more than one battle destiny here.
front.lore: 1308 was one of several droids who analyzed the N-1 starfighter during the Trade Federation's occupation of Naboo. Was unable to calculate the 'human factor' inside the N-1.
front.title: •DFS-1308

front.gametext: While at same system as your battleship, DFS-327 is power +3, and opponent's pilots deploy +2 to starfighters at this system.

front.title: •DFS-327

front.gametext: * Ferocity = (power/ferocity of last character or creature eaten) + destiny. Habitat: exterior Dagobah sites, Trash Compactor and Dark Waters.
front.lore: 'Garbage squid' from Vodran's jungles. Changes color to match last meal. When unfed, turns transparent. Eats almost anything. Flexible eyestalk. 7 tentacles. Up to 6 meters long.
front.title: Dianoga

front.gametext: Use 2 Force to target two opponent's Jedi at same interior battleground. Targets may not participate in battle for remainder of turn. OR Target opponent's Jedi. Draw destiny. If destiny > 2, target's game text is canceled for remainder of turn.
front.lore: Green gas that is lethal to most carbon-based life forms.
front.title: •Dioxis

front.title: Direct Hit

If Disarmed is removed, any permanent weapon(s) are restored.
During persona replacement, for power comparison purposes, reduces the power of only the on-table character card, not the new version.
During persona replacement, transfers to the new version of the character.

front.title: Disruptor Pistol

combo: Dominator + Imperial Helmsman Draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

front.title: •Dominator

If a draw doesn't fit any range (such as a draw of 2.5), no result.

front.lore: Having lost sight of Boba Fett, Luke was surprised by his sudden reappearance.

front.lore: Similar power output to the Atgar P-tower. Equipped with a hydraulic coolant system. Effective in dealing with raiding swoop gangs.

front.lore: 'You've got a lot of guts coming here. . . after what you pulled.'
front.title: •Double-Crossing, No-Good Swindler

front.title: •D'Qar

front.lore: Female information broker, spy, and thief. Trade Federation.
front.title: •Dr. Chelli Lona Aphra

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. The not-so-good doctor may 'operate' on any other character present that was just 'hit' or just Disarmed; 'patient' is lost.
front.lore: Thug. Smuggler. Twisted 'doctor'. Disfigured by blaster. Has death sentence in over 12 systems. Notorious partner of Ponda Baba. Aliases: Dr. Cornelius and Rooboo.
front.title: •Dr. Evazan

front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything they pilot. Power -3 if opponent has a lightsaber present. Draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. May target any other character present that was just 'hit.' Target character is lost.
front.lore: Smugglers who met each other in the Corellian system. Gained the rights to Han Solo's old smuggling routes from Jabba the Hutt. They don't like you either.
front.title: •Dr. Evazan & •Ponda Baba

canceledBy: Game text canceled by Mandalorian Mishap

front.gametext: Deploy on Dr. Evazan (may deploy on him as a 'react') or use 3 Force to deploy on your warrior. May target a character or creature at same or adjacent site using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny +1 > defense value. May fire repeatedly.
front.lore: Equipped with powerful infrared scope. Extremely sensitive trigger mechanism. Used to earn Evazan the death sentence on several systems.
front.title: •Dr. Evazan's Sawed-off Blaster

front.gametext: Ferocity = 3 + destiny. Habitat: swamps, jungles and Dark Waters. May attack droids. Defeated droids are relocated to an adjacent exterior site (opponent of victim chooses).
front.lore: One of Dagobah's deadliest predators. Has razor-sharp fins, powerful constrictor coils and large fangs. Feeds on almost anything. Often mistaken for a swamp slug, due to its size.
front.title: <>Dragonsnake

front.lore: The Empire uses short-range fighters and patrol craft to maintain a presence in every system within its scope of power.
front.title: •Dreaded Imperial Starfleet

rulings: A card with asterisk deploy cost is treated as X = 0.

front.title: Dreadnaught-Class Heavy Cruiser

front.lore: Anakin had to heed Qui-Gon's advice to avoid the rapidly approaching storm.
front.title: •Drop!

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Saber 3, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. Opponent may not 'react' to same system or sector.
front.lore: Flies Saber 3 in fighting 181st. Studied under Baron Fel at the Prefsbelt Imperial Academy; now flies as his wing. Nicknamed 'Fel's Wrath'. Watches the Baron's back.
front.title: •DS-181-3

front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of any TIE he pilots. Once during each of your deploy phases, you may take one unique (•) TIE Interceptor into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Wingman of Major Phennir. Earned promotion to Fel's squadron by scoring 12 kills at Mon Calamari. Repeatedly refused further promotion so that he could remain in the 181st.
front.title: •DS-181-4

front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Black 2, also adds 1 to maneuver and may draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.
front.lore: Vader's left wingman. Flies Black 2. Specially trained pilot held in reserve for missions with Vader. Nicknamed 'Mauler Mithel.'
front.title: •DS-61-2

front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Black 3, also adds 1 to maneuver and may draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.
front.lore: Vader's right wingman. Flies Black 3. Reputation for ferocity in combat. Corellian pilot with excellent skills. Nicknamed 'Backstabber.'
front.title: •DS-61-3

front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Black 4, also may draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. May use 1 Force to take one Lone Pilot into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Imperial pilot nicknamed 'Dark Curse.' Survived assaults against several dissenter worlds including Ralltiir and Mon Calamari. Intends to retire after his next combat mission.
front.title: •DS-61-4

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots, 3 when piloting Black 5.  While piloting Black 5, it is maneuver +1 and he draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.  If at opponent's system, instead of Force draining here, may take any one card into hand from Force Pile; reshuffle.
front.lore: Blank.
front.title: •DS-61-5

front.lore: RS 557 Podracer. Secretly hired by Sebulba to protect him during Podraces.
front.title: •Dud Bolt's Podracer

combo: Dune Sea Sabacc (or any Sabacc really) + Trinto Duaba + Voyeur Play Sabacc to get cards in their Used Pile, then the other 2 Interrupts to make them lose Force/other cards. (maxbeedo)
Dune Sea Sabacc + Iasa, The Traitor Of Jawa Canyon

front.gametext: Requirements: A Jawa at a Tatooine site. Wild cards (0-7): sandcrawler sites, Magnetic Suction Tube, Jawa Siesta and Jawa Pack. Clone cards: Tatooine locations, sandcrawlers, Jawa weapons, and Utinni! Stakes: One device or droid with out armor.
front.lore: Popular among Tatooine's native population. Apart from the Jawas, no one else seems to understand the rules.
front.title: •Dune Sea Sabacc

combo: Dune Walker + Trample

front.gametext: Deploy -1 to a desert or Tatooine site. May add 1 pilot and 6 passengers. Immune to attrition < 4. Landspeed may not be increased. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1.
front.lore: Enclosed armored transport adapted for hot climates by replacing tertiary weapons systems with additional Sienar t23 heat dissipation units.
front.title: •••Dune Walker

combo: E Chu Ta + U-3PO (Yoo-Threepio) or E-3PO

front.gametext: One of your protocol droids 'insults' one character present, canceling that character's game text for remainder of turn. OR During your battle phase, initiate a battle where both players have droids (but no presence or spies). Both sides add one battle destiny.
front.lore: 'How rude!'
front.title: •E Chu Ta

rulings: Once initiated, the battle will continue even if presence and/or spies are introduced to the battle.

front.gametext: Total power at same site is +1 for each of your alien/Imperial pairs present. Once during every turn, may use 1 Force to 'insult' one opponent's droid present (except R2-D2), canceling that droid's game text for remainder of turn.
front.lore: Brought to Cloud City by the Empire. Facilitates Imperial-to-alien communication. Relayed carbonite chamber modification instructions to Ugloste. Arrogant. Rude. Vulgar.
front.title: •E-3PO

front.gametext: Deploy on any site. May be moved with two warriors for 1 additional Force. Your warrior present may target a starfighter (use 5 as defense value), character, creature or vehicle using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny +1 > defense value.
front.lore: Massive infantry weapon powerful enough to damage even starfighters.
front.title: E-web Blaster

rulings: Moving the E-web Blaster does not permit those carrying it to make an extra move.
Normal movement costs apply to the characters moving the E-web Blaster.
The characters moving the E-web Blaster move with it, using landspeed, simultaneously.
This weapon is a blaster.

front.gametext: Deploy on an interior site that has a Scomp link. While you occupy this site, once per battle you may deploy a non-unique Imperial starship as a 'react' (for free if starfighter) to the related system from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Listening posts are often constructed as part of a standard Imperial installation. On Endor, such a post was incorporated into the control bunker.
front.title: <>Early Warning Network

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

front.gametext: Agenda: ambition. While in a senate majority, opponent may not draw more than one battle destiny in battles at battleground sites and you may not cancel opponent's battle destiny draws at sites.
front.lore: Senator from the planet Roona. One of the first to support Amidala's motion for a vote of no confidence in Supreme Chancellor Valorum. Intolerant of other species.
front.title: •Edcel Bar Gane

front.gametext: USED: For remainder of turn, subtract 1 from forfeit of each opponent's Ewok (or subtract 2 from any one opponent's character).  LOST: Cancel one Ewok's game text for remainder of turn. OR Cancel Sound The Attack.
front.lore: Paploo's brave diversion provided more of a ride than the adventurous Ewok had bargained for.
front.title: •Eee Chu Wawa!

front.gametext: Adds 1 to power of each of your droids present, except power droids. *Destiny equals zero, but if drawn as a battle destiny where you have less power than opponent, your total power present is doubled (once per battle).
front.lore: Ambulatory power generator made by Veril Line Systems to support equipment and vehicles. Slow-witted. This EG unit is memory-wiped and doesn't know its name or serial number.
front.title: EG-6 (Eegee-Six)

rulings: Doubles total power at a location, including modifiers.
Does not double any power destiny / battle destiny draws.
Does not double attrition.

front.gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on any AT-AT Cannon. It may fire at targets two sites away. Also, when used to Target The Main Generator, adds 1 to total.
front.lore: Long-range stereoscopic sighting device connected to the cannons of an Imperial walker. Calibrated to allow the AT-AT commander to accurately fire at distant targets.
front.title: Electro-Rangefinder

canceledBy: Quite A Mercenary makes all characters transported by Elis Helrot lost

front.gametext: At any time (except during battle), target any or all of your characters at one site to 'transport' (relocate) to any one other site. Draw destiny. Use that much Force to 'transport,' or place Interrupt in Lost Pile.
front.lore: A Givin pilot who can seal his joints to withstand the vacuum of space. Makes slaving and spike runs to Kala'uun. Has made many special modifications to his ship, the Hinthra.
front.title: Elis Helrot

rulings: The destiny draw and cost are paid during initiation, and then responses (e.g. Sense) may take place.
If retargeted by I Have A Bad Feeling About This, it must EITHER select new characters to be transported OR select a new destination site.
If using I Have A Bad Feeling About This to choose new characters, the new characters may be at the same origin site or a different origin site, but it cannot include any of the original characters.

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot and 3 passengers. Permanent pilot is •Elis, who provides ability of 2. Once per game, may use 1 Force to deploy a smuggler aboard from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Immune to attrition < 5.
front.lore: Blank.
front.title: •Elis In Hinthra

front.gametext: Power +2 while armed with a blaster. When using a blaster, subtracts 1 from Force required to fire it. Adds 2 to forfeit of each stormtrooper of ability < 2 at same site.
front.lore: Commander Igar selected the Empire's most dedicated stormtroopers to guard Endor for the Emperor. All they know is killing and white uniforms.
front.title: •••Elite Squadron Stormtrooper

front.gametext: If opponent just initiated a battle where opponent has more than double your power, reveal up to 3 cards from your Reserve Deck. Of those 3, deploy anywhere (for free) any characters, starships, vehicles, devices or weapons. Any others are lost.
front.lore: TIE fighters are stored in large racks far above the hangar deck. Catapulted into space by powerful tractor beam generators, TIEs can quickly scramble to engage the enemy.
front.title: Emergency Deployment

rulings: The revealed cards may be deployed in any order.
Does not circumvent any deployment rules such as requiring presence or Force icons, Dagobah rules, etc.
All cards revealed but not deployed are lost.
If Blizzard 4 shuffles the Reserve Deck, any remaining revealed cards are un-revealed and shuffled in, ending the action.
If the player somehow activates or loses Force from Reserve Deck while the top card is revealed, it is un-revealed and then activated/lost normally.

combo: Emperor Palpatine + Force Lightning
Emperor Palpatine + I Have You Now Add one battle destiny (two if Rebel is Luke) if a Dark Jedi and a Rebel with ability > 2 are involved in the same battle.
Emperor Palpatine + Force Field Cancels an attempt to target a Dark Jedi with a character weapon.
Emperor Palpatine + Janus Greejatus
Emperor Palpatine + Overseeing It Personally

front.gametext: Never deploys or moves (even aboard a starship or vehicle) to a site opponent occupies. Where present, subtracts 3 from attempts to cross Vader over. Once per turn, you may take Force Lightning into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Immune to attrition.
front.lore: Sith Master and leader of Galactic Empire. Dark side mentor to Darth Vader. Controls the Empire by instilling fear in its subjects and greed in its governors.
front.title: •Emperor Palpatine

rulings: Must be present at a location (not inside a starship or enclosed vehicle) to subtract 3 from attempts to cross Vader.  Vader does not need to be present at the location.
Cannot deploy, move, or persona replace to a site opponent occupies.
May deploy, move, or persona replace to a <u>system or sector</u> opponent occupies.

combo: Emperor Palpatine + Force Lightning
Emperor Palpatine + I Have You Now Add one battle destiny (two if Rebel is Luke) if a Dark Jedi and a Rebel with ability > 2 are involved in the same battle.
Emperor Palpatine + Force Field Cancels an attempt to target a Dark Jedi with a character weapon.
Emperor Palpatine + Janus Greejatus
Emperor Palpatine + Overseeing It Personally

front.gametext: Never deploys or moves (even if carried) to a site opponent occupies. Once during your turn, may peek at the top three cards of your Reserve Deck; place one in Used Pile, one in Lost Pile, and take one into hand. Immune to attrition.
front.lore: From his throne room aboard the second Death Star, Emperor Palpatine monitors activity throughout the galaxy. Leader.
front.title: •Emperor Palpatine, Foreseer

combo: Emperor's Personal Shuttle + Emperor Palpatine

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot and 4 passengers. Permanent pilot provides ability 2. Emperor deploys for free aboard. While Emperor aboard, immune to attrition and adds one battle destiny.
front.lore: Transport used extensively by Emperor Palpatine. Extremely well guarded. Pilots ordered to maintain constant contact with all nearby Imperial strike forces.
front.title: •Emperor's Personal Shuttle

front.gametext: Deploy on your Throne Room. You may not Force drain here. While Emperor here, opponent's characters are deploy +2 to Death Star II sites and, one per turn, you may lose Effect (or 1 Force from top of Reserve Deck) to add one battle destiny anywhere. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: From his throne room aboard the second Death Star, Emperor Palpatine monitors activity throughout the galaxy.
front.title: •Emperor's Power

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Droid Merchant game text is canceled. Also, while none of your ability on table is provided by aliens, retrieve 1 Force after each battle in which opponent's alien is lost (or 2 if Ewok, Elom or operative). (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Palpatine's cruel vision of his Empire included the enslavement and subjugation of entire species.
front.title: •Empire's New Order

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

front.gametext: USED: During a battle at a site, instead of firing one character weapon, cause one opponent's character present to be power -4 until end of turn.  LOST: During a battle at a site, use 3 Force to cancel one battle destiny just drawn.
front.lore: 'Join me, and together we can rule the galaxy as father and son.'
front.title: •End This Destructive Conflict

rulings: (Used) Weapon must be capable of firing and have an eligible target. Not required to have enough Force to fire. If a character with a permanent weapon has had their game text canceled, they cannot fire and therefore cannot use this function.

combo: Endor + Establish Secret Base
Endor + Endor Shield (V) Opponent generates no Force at Endor system unless Rebel Strike Team on table.
Endor + Presence Of The Force + Endor Shield (V) Three Force icons for you, none for the Light Side. Opportunity to drain for three.

front.gametext: Dark:  If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Endor site.  Light:  If you have no Ewoks on Endor, Force drain -1 here. To move or deploy your starship to here requires +1 Force.
front.title: •Endor

cancels: All My Urchins & Cloud City Celebration

front.gametext: Cancel Tatooine Celebration, Cloud City Celebration or Coruscant Celebration. (Immune to Sense.) OR During your activate phase, activate 1 Force for each Endor battleground you occupy.
front.lore: Each planet controlled by the Empire drains potential resources from the Rebel Alliance.
front.title: •Endor Occupation

front.gametext: Deploy on Bunker. Imperials deploy -1 here while Death Star II system orbits Endor and you control Bunker. At Death Star II system and each Death Star site opponent may not deploy and must use +3 Force to move there.
front.lore: Planetary scale shield projected from surface of Endor moon. Protected second Death Star during construction. Only another superlaser could penetrate it while operational.
front.title: •Endor Shield

front.gametext: Deploy on table.  While your [Endor] objective on table (and opponent's [Endor] objective not on table) opponent generates no Force at Endor system. Twice per game, may take an Imperial admiral into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Planetary scale shield projected from surface of Endor moon. Protected second Death Star during construction. Only another superlaser could penetrate it while operational.

combo: Endor: Bunker + Major Hewex
