rulings: If Light chooses a Resistance Agent, only cards with that same title are a Resistance Agent. They do not become Resistance character cards.
If no choice is made, all Luke persona cards are a Resistance Agent and lose immunity to attrition (if any). They do not become Resistance character cards.
Interrupts stacked on I Will Finish What You Started remain stacked if this Objective flips back to the 0-side, but Dark can only play stacked Interrupts while on the 7-side.

front.gametext: Deploy on one opponent's unique (•) starship at a location you do not occupy. When starship is targeted by any tractor beam or ion cannon, subtract 2 from maneuver. If starship is captured or lost, lose Effect and opponent must lose 3 Force (5 if Falcon).
front.lore: Like nerf herders herding nerfs, Imperial commanders often use TIE fighters to drive fleeing Rebel ships into tractor beam range.
front.title: •I Want That Ship

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Opponent may deploy Amidala from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. If Maul present with Amidala and opponent has no Jedi there, she is captured. Once per game may take If The Trace Was Correct into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Utilizing his 'dark eye' probe droids and sensory equipment, Maul knew he would eventually find his target.
front.title: •I Will Find Them Quickly, Master

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Vader is lost. Once per turn, may stack an Interrupt from hand face up here to cancel a just drawn weapon destiny at Kylo's site. Kylo is power +1 for each card here. Once per game, may deploy a lightsaber from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Blank.
front.title: •I Will Finish What You Started

combo: Iasa, The Traitor Of Jawa Canyon + Dune Sea Sabacc

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. When firing any Jawa weapon, subtracts 3 from target's defense value. When playing Dune Sea Sabacc, may subtract 1 from or add 1 to your total.
front.lore: While on a trip, King Kalit entrusted his credits, sandcrawler and mate to his friend Iasa. When Kalit returned, one was spent, one was sold and the other was missing.
front.title: •Iasa, The Traitor Of Jawa Canyon

pulledBy: Herat to deploy to same location

front.gametext: Deploy at outermost marker. All characters present at same exterior site are missing. Each turn, during your control phase, storm moves to next marker, reversing direction if at innermost marker. Mobile Effect lost when moved beyond outermost marker.
front.lore: Among the gravest dangers in the harsh environment of Hoth are frequent quick-moving ice storms.
front.title: •Ice Storm

rulings: Will deploy and move to/from Wampa Cave like any other marker site. Does not cause characters at Wampa Cave to go missing.
May be canceled during the response step, such as by Control, in which case it will be canceled without making any characters missing.

front.gametext: Use 3 Force to place an opponent's just deployed character, starship, vehicle, weapon, or device in opponent's hand. On opponent's next turn, that card (or one card of same title) may deploy for free.
front.lore: 'I can arrange that. You could USE a good kiss!'
front.title: •I'd Just As Soon Kiss A Wookiee
front.printableSlipUrl: https://res.starwarsccg.org/vkit/cards/standard/Id Just As Soon Kiss A Wookiee (Errata)/image.png

rulings: The target does deploy briefly, triggering any automatic actions (such as Objective flips) first.
The target card is placed in owner's hand, even if it was being deployed from Reserve Deck or somewhere else.
If two cards were being deployed simultaneously, such as via Squadron Assignments, both cards are equally affected (both placed in hand and may deploy free next turn).
If the target card is unique, that unique card/persona cannot deploy again this turn.
Cannot be played as a response to persona replacement (e.g. Commander Luke Skywalker replacing Luke Skywalker).
Cannot be played as a response to other replacement (e.g. X-wing Assault Squadron replacing 3 X-wings).

front.gametext: Deploy on I Will Find Them Quickly, Master. Once during each of your deploy phases may deploy a Sith Probe Droid from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. If Amidala forfeited at same site as Maul, she is captured instead of lost. While Maul escorting Amidala, opponent's battle destiny draws are -1 and during your turn you may use up to 3 Force in opponent's Force Pile. While Maul escorting Amidala at a non-Tatooine battleground site, opponent's Force drains at Tatooine sites are -1 and at the end of every turn, may reshuffle opponent's Reserve Deck.
front.title: •If The Trace Was Correct

front.gametext: Grievous is defense value +2 here. While aboard Invisible Hand, draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise and characters here are immune to Clash Of Sabers.
front.lore: Assassin. Trade Federation.
front.title: •••IG MagnaGuard

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot (must be a smuggler or bounty hunter) and 2 passengers. Maneuver +3 and immune to attrition < 3 if IG-88 piloting. Ion Cannon may deploy aboard.
front.lore: IG-88's assault starfighter. Custom designed. Boasts a Kuat Galaxy-15 engine from a Nebulon-B frigate. Heavy ion cannon often used to disable starships before boarding.
front.title: •IG-2000

pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. May 'assassinate' any character at same site hit by IG-88 (victim is immediately lost). May use two different weapons. May initiate battle and be battled. Immune to Restraining Bolt and purchase.
front.lore: Bounty hunter. Went berserk upon activation. Murdered all designers at Holowan Mechanicals. IG-88's outstanding 'dismantle on sight' warrant ignored by Darth Vader.
front.title: •IG-88

rulings: Cards with multiple warrior icons can still only escort one captive at a time.
Canceling IG-88's game text or excluding him from battle could result in a battle ending immediately (in cases where his game text is required for the battle to occur).

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. May use two weapons. Once per turn, if escorting a captive, may take any one card from Force Pile into hand; reshuffle. May lose 1 Force to cancel a just drawn weapon destiny targeting IG-88. Immune to attrition < 5.
front.lore: Bounty hunter. Went berserk upon activation. Murdered all designers at Holowan Mechanicals. IG-88's outstanding 'dismantle on sight' warrant ignored by Darth Vader.
front.title: •IG-88 (V)

rulings: A destiny targets IG-88 (V) if it is used in comparison with a number on the IG-88 (V) card, such as his armor.
The destiny drawn for the weapon Booma does not target IG-88 (V).
Cards with multiple warrior icons can still only escort one captive at a time.

front.gametext: May add 2 passengers. Permanent pilot is •IG-88, who adds 2 to power and 3 to maneuver. May initiate battle. When in a battle you initiate, adds one battle destiny. Ion Cannon may deploy aboard.
front.lore: Starship adapted to the assassin droid's specifications. Flight controls linked directly to processing unit. Real-time relays minimize response time.
front.title: •IG-88 In IG-2000

rulings: Canceling IG-2000's game text or excluding it from battle could result in a battle ending immediately (in cases where its game text is required for the battle to occur).

front.gametext: May initiate battle. Permanent weapon is riot gun (may target a character for free; draw destiny; target captured if destiny +1 > defense value). Adds one battle destiny if alone or with your other bounty hunter. Immune to Restraining Bolt and purchase.
front.lore: Bounty hunter droid equipped with proprietary stealth technology. Archived several of its enhancement subroutines in favor of sophisticated tracking and capture programming.
front.title: •IG-88 With Riot Gun

rulings: Canceling IG-88's game text or excluding him from battle could result in a battle ending immediately (in cases where his game text is required for the battle to occur).

front.gametext: Deploy on IG-88, or use 2 Force on any other bounty hunter. May target a non-droid character using 3 Force. Draw destiny. If destiny +1 > ability, until end of your next turn character is power, forfeit and landspeed = 0.
front.lore: Menotor DAS-430 electromagnetic projectile launcher. Often mistaken for a blaster rifle. Fires small hollow darts filled with neurotoxin which cause temporary paralysis.
front.title: •IG-88's Neural Inhibitor

front.gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on IG-88, 4 on your other warrior. Adds 2 to power. May target X non-droid characters or creatures using X Force. Draw destiny for each. If destiny = 0, character is power -1 and forfeit -1 until end of turn. If destiny -1 > defense value, target hit.
front.lore: IG-88's personal favorite for mass destruction. Rapid-fire fusion plasma bursts are extremely effective against multiple targets. Not widely used due to incidental damage.
front.title: •IG-88's Pulse Cannon

front.gametext: Target opponent's starfighter making an Attack Run. Draw destiny. Add 1 for each of your TIEs in Death Star: Trench. If total destiny > maneuver, starfighter is lost. OR Add 1 to weapon destiny draws of any starfighter for remainder of this turn.
front.lore: In the defense of the Death Star at the Battle of Yavin, Darth Vader took the lead attacker, supported by his wingmen Black 2 and Black 3.
front.title: •I'm On The Leader

front.gametext: Deploy on table. If This Deal Is Getting Worse All The Time on table, once per game may take up to 2 interior Cloud City battlegrounds into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. You may not play Scanning Crew or Imperial Barrier. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: 'I'm sorry, too.'
front.title: •I'm Sorry

front.gametext: Whenever opponent Force drains at same or adjacent site, may deploy up to four troopers there as a 'react.' When IM4 is present with your trooper, Rebels are deploy +2 to same site and opponent may not 'react' to or from same site.
front.lore: Imperial Mark IV Patrol Droid. Identifies criminal activity and transmits information to local authorities. Monitors random comm signals for illegal activity.
front.title: IM4-099 (Eyeemmfour)

front.gametext: Use 4 Force to deploy at any site if opponent is generating at least 3 Force more than you. At that site, adjacent sites and same site as Vader, players activate Force only if they have presence.
front.lore: Vader's hologram exacts loyalty from his legions.
front.title: •Image Of The Dark Lord

front.gametext: Deploy on a planet site. Opponent's Force drains are -1 here (-2 if Vader controls an adjacent site).
front.lore: Vader's hologram exacts loyalty from his legions.
front.title: •Image Of The Dark Lord (V)

front.gametext: If opponent just retrieved Force, opponent must lose X Force, where X = one-half the number of cards retrieved (round up).
front.lore: 'ConcentraaAAATE!'
front.title: •Imbalance

cancels: Sorry About The Mess & Blaster Proficiency

front.gametext: Cancel Blaster Proficiency. (Immune to Sense.) OR If opponent just retrieved Force, opponent must lose X Force, where X = one-half the number of cards retrieved (round down) to a minimum of 1. OR If opponent's character just lost, lose 1 Force to retrieve the topmost character of ability < 6 (except a [Maintenance] or [Permanent Weapon] card) in your Lost Pile into hand.
front.title: •Imbalance & •Kintan Strider

front.gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Each of your non-unique Imperials armed with a non-unique blaster is forfeit +2, adds 1 to his total weapon destiny and, where present, cumulatively adds 1 to total battle destiny. (Immune to Alter while your non-unique blaster is on table.)
front.lore: Graduates of the Empire's military academies train to fire standard-issue weapons efficiently.
front.title: •Imperial Academy Training

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Unique (•) Imperials of ability < 3 are forfeit +2. Nabrun Leids and Elis Helrot are limited to owner's move phase and exterior sites. Once during each of your deploy phases, may deploy one docking bay from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: When an Imperial blockade raises the alert level, all independent ships are scanned and any suspicious characters on planet are detained and interrogated.
front.title: •Imperial Arrest Order

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points
rulings: Read this as owner's move phase and <u>any</u> exterior sites (not as owner's move phase and <u>owner's</u> exterior sites).
For Nabrun and Elis, the origin site and the destination site must <u>both</u> be exterior (interior/exterior sites such as Death Star: Docking Bay are allowed).

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Unique (•) Imperials of ability < 3 are forfeit +1. Nabrun Leids and Elis Helrot are limited to owner's move phase and exterior sites only. Once during each of your deploy phases, may deploy one docking bay from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. When opponent retrieves X cards, opponent must first use X Force or that retrieval is canceled. (Immune to Alter.)
front.title: •Imperial Arrest Order & •Secret Plans

rulings: Read this as owner's move phase and <u>any</u> exterior sites (not as owner's move phase and <u>owner's</u> exterior sites).
For Nabrun and Elis, the origin site and the destination site must <u>both</u> be exterior (interior/exterior sites such as Death Star: Docking Bay are allowed).
Light has the option to decline and cancel the retrieval.
The amount of Force used ('X') equals the retrieval amount initiated, even if the Lost pile has fewer than X cards.

front.gametext: During your control phase, if you have a weapon (except a lightsaber or [Permanent Weapon]) at a battleground you control, opponent loses 1 Force. OR If you just used a weapon (except a lightsaber or [Permanent Weapon]) to 'hit' a character or starship, opponent loses 1 Force. (Immune to Sense.)
front.lore: The Empire always had a large weapons cache held in reserve, in case of an emergency.
front.title: ••Imperial Artillery

rulings: First function: A player with only one weapon may play two copies of this Interrupt in the same control phase (two separate top-level actions causing 1 damage each).
Second function: After hitting a single character or starship, a player may respond with two copies of this Interrupt (two separate response actions causing 1 damage each).

front.gametext: Use 1 Force to prevent any character or starship just deployed by the opponent from battling or moving for the remainder of this turn.
front.lore: As is often the case with a hasty plan, a quick heroic escape from the Death Star was temporarily thwarted by the magnetically sealed door in the trash compactor.
front.title: Imperial Barrier

combo: Imperial Blaster + Blaster Scope Target at an adjacent site.
Imperial Blaster + Biker Scout Gear
Imperial Blaster + Compact Firepower

front.gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your warrior. May target a character, creature or vehicle using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny > defense value.
front.lore: A BlasTech DH-17 blaster pistol. Uses power packs and high-energy blaster gases. Shoots bolts of explosive coherent light energy.
front.title: Imperial Blaster

front.gametext: If any Imperial leader is present with a Scomp link, you may: Glance at the cards in any Reserve Deck for 20 seconds. Shuffle, cut and replace. OR If also at a Death Star site, cancel Scomp Link Access or Into The Garbage Chute, Flyboy.
front.lore: Imperial officers are issued coded cylinders which access computer information via Scomp links. Each cylinder is coded to the officer's own security clearance.
front.title: Imperial Code Cylinder

front.gametext: Take one admiral or general into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. OR If your admiral is in battle at a system (or your general is in battle at a site), you may either add one battle destiny or prevent opponent from drawing more than one battle destiny.
front.lore: The Emperor's high command is subjected to close scrutiny by the Imperial bureaucracy. Despite this apparent lack of trust, many turn out to be fine commanders.
front.title: •Imperial Command

front.gametext: Adds 1 to forfeit of each of your other Imperials (except leaders) at same site.
front.lore: Typical Imperial leader. Uses constant training and crisis simulations to help maintain high performance levels. Commander Daine Jir is known to be bold and outspoken.
front.title: Imperial Commander

combo: Imperial Decree + Walker Garrison Gives all of the benefits of the Walker Garrison deck with extremely minimal adjustments to get the benefits of Imperial Decree.

front.gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Whenever you control any two Rebel Base locations, or any one planet site and two systems, the effects of Revolution and all opponent's Force drain bonuses are canceled. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: To Imperial command personnel: The Rebellion must be crushed! Minor acts of sedition are to be ignored. The destruction of the Alliance is your primary goal.
front.title: Imperial Decree

rulings: Only cancels Force drain bonuses that come from LS cards affecting LS Force drains.
For example, if LS Force drains at the DS system Eriadu, the +1 bonus in Eriadu's game text is not canceled because it is a DS card.
For example, if DS Force drains at the LS site Tatooine: Obi-Wan's Hut, the +1 bonus in the site's game text is not canceled because it is a DS Force drain.

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Whenever you lose Force (except from Force drains, battle damage, or your card), may reduce loss (to a minimum of 1) by the number of battlegrounds you occupy. During battle, may place this Effect out of play to draw one battle destiny if unable to otherwise. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: To Imperial command personnel: The Rebellion must be crushed! Minor acts of sedition are to be ignored. The destruction of the Alliance is your primary goal.
front.title: Imperial Decree (V)

front.gametext: Plays on table. For opponent to deploy a character, starship, or vehicle for free (except by that card's own game text), opponent must first use 2 Force. [Jabba's Palace] I Must Be Allowed To Speak may not target locations except Lars' Moisture Farm and Jabba's Palace sites.
front.lore: Blank.
front.title: •Imperial Detention

rulings: A card that deploys for 0 such as Kal'Falnl C'ndros is not the same as 'free' and thus doesn't trigger this card.
Prevents IMBATS(V) from deploying the generic Farm.
Prevents IMBATS(V) from searching Used Pile when a specified character (e.g. Luke) deploys to a site (except Lar's Moisture Farm or a Jabba's Palace Site).
Does not restrict what card Light may take into hand from Used Pile via IMBATS(V).
Does not affect non-V IMBATS (or the Set 18 combo card) in any way.

front.gametext: Deploy on any location. Whenever you control this location during your control phase but do not Force drain here, opponent generates no Force here on opponent's next turn.
front.lore: When Vader's forces impose the New Order upon a region, Rebel resources and lifelines are quickly eliminated.
front.title: ••Imperial Domination

rulings: Triggers if Dark controls the location at any point during their Control Phase.
Of course it un-triggers if Dark Force drains there.

front.errataNotes: E1 Text: Deploy on table. Lost if your non-Imperial character (or starship) on table. Unless you occupy fewer locations than opponent: if you win a battle, retrieve an Imperial; and, during battle, may take an Imperial just drawn for destiny into hand to cancel and redraw that destiny. [Immune to Alter.]
front.gametext: Deploy on table. You may initiate battles for free. Once per turn, if you just drew a character for destiny, may take that card into hand to cancel and redraw that destiny. Canceled if your non-Imperial character (or starship) on table. [Immune to Alter.]
front.lore: When Vader's forces impose the New Order upon a region, Rebel resources and lifelines are quickly eliminated.
front.title: •Imperial Enforcement

rulings: Mara Jade, The Emperor's Hand (for example) does not make this Effect canceled.
Imperial starships (Dark starships with no allegiance icon such as Independent, Republic, etc) do not make this Effect canceled.

rulings: You may deploy (for example) Mara Jade, The Emperor's Hand.

front.gametext: Adds 1 to weapon destiny draws of anything he is aboard as a passenger.
front.lore: Walker operators work in pairs, one trained to pilot the AT-AT, the other serving as gunner. Imperial gunners consider themselves the best marksmen in the Empire.
front.title: Imperial Gunner

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting a Star Destroyer, also draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.
front.lore: Warrant Officer Bachenkall is typical of the many graduates of the Imperial Training academy on Raithal. The sector naval school trains pilots in capital starship help tactics.
front.title: •••Imperial Helmsman

combo: Imperial Holotable + HoloNet Transmission

front.gametext: Dark:  'Dejarik Rules' in effect here.  Light:  'Dejarik Rules' in effect here. Site converted by Dejarik Hologameboard.
front.title: •Imperial Holotable

cancels: Makes a location immune to Revolution

front.gametext: If opponent is generating at least 4 more Force than you, deploy on a location to cancel all Force generation at that location. OR Deploy on a location. It is now immune to Revolution.
front.lore: 'There's nothing you could have done Luke, had you been there. You'd have been killed too.'
front.title: Imperial Justice

rulings: When initiating deployment, Dark declares which function they are using on this card.
Once deployed, only that chosen function operates until the card leaves table.

front.gametext: Deploy on table; shuffle your Reserve Deck, peek at top two cards, and stack them face-up here. During battle, may take a card here into hand to prevent all battle destiny draws from being modified or canceled (each player may draw no more than one battle destiny). (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Tatooine's twin suns cause turbulent storms that strike with little or no warning. Strong winds whip rocks through the air with enormous force.
front.title: •Coarse And Rough And Irritating

rulings: Preventing destiny draws from being modified even prevents global modifiers such as from the Silence Is Golden (V) and the Senate Objective.

Preventing destiny draws from being modified can be circumvented with a substituted destiny that has been modified <u>before</u> the substitution (e.g. Darklighter Spin on a modified maneuver value, or a senator on Sando Aqua Monster that is already receiving a global modifier from the Senate Objective).

rulings: The ♢ site deployed at start of game must be capable of deploying to that system.
If a ♢ site says it may not deploy to a Renegade planet, it may not be deployed by this Objective at start of game.

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots.
front.lore: Among the Empire's best pilots. Loyal and fearless. Use superior numbers to overwhelm opponents. Trained under combat conditions. Wear sealed, high-gravity flight suits.
front.title: Imperial Pilot

rulings: Two copies of this card piloting the same starship only increases the starship's power by 2, not 4.

front.gametext: If you occupy at least two battlegrounds and just lost more than 2 Force to a Force drain at a location, deploy on that location (limit one per Force drain). Opponent loses 2 Force for each Imperial Propaganda on table.
front.lore: Imperial data transmissions depict Rebel incursions as terrorist acts. The Alliance is portrayed as a danger to civilians of the Empire.
front.title: Imperial Propaganda

front.gametext: If opponent has more total characters and starships on table than you have, use 1 Force to draw destiny. Retrieve that number of Stormtroopers and/or TIE/lns.
front.lore: Imperial stormtroopers deploy in 8-10 trooper squads. Reinforcements are typically held in reserve according to standard Imperial operating procedures.
front.title: Imperial Reinforcements

front.gametext: Adds 1 to forfeit of your other troopers at same site. When moving with a 'squad' of exactly three other troopers, all four move for 1 Force. Imperial Trooper Guards at same site may move.
front.lore: Captain Mod Terrik, a typical officer of the Desert Sands sandtrooper unit. Fearless and highly motivated. Willing to sacrifice as many troops as necessary.
front.title: Imperial Squad Leader

rulings: This card is a trooper.
When about to move, may target other troopers/guards to move with him.
Does not permit the other troopers/guards to perform a move they are not otherwise able to make.
Suspends the 'cannot move' text on Imperial Trooper Guards at same site.

front.gametext: USED: Lose 1 Force to activate 2 Force.  LOST: Lose 1 Force to activate 4 Force.
front.lore: The Empire's efficient, fear-driven logistical systems can quickly divert weapons and equipment from one conflict to another, focusing on regions of highest strategic priority.
front.title: •Imperial Supply

front.gametext: Power +4 when defending a battle. Cannot move.
front.lore: Elite soldiers trained in combat techniques and weapons skills. Death Star trooper Tajis Durmin is typical of those assigned to guard key areas of the Death Star.
front.title: Imperial Trooper Guard

cancels: Opponent's Force drains at adjacent sites
combo: Imperial Trooper Guard Dainsom + Imperial Squad Leader A mobile Force drain blocker for the Dark Side.

front.gametext: Deploys only aboard Executor or on any Death Star Site. Cannot move. May cancel opponent's Force Drains at adjacent Death Star or Executor sites.
front.lore: Experienced trooper guard from Algarian. Assigned to guard sensitive areas. Formerly served aboard the Star Destroyer Thunderflare.
front.title: •Imperial Trooper Guard Dainsom

front.gametext: If an opponent's alien is defending a battle against your non-unique Imperial, add one battle destiny. If an opponent's Ewok, Elom or operative is defending, also add 3 to your total power. OR Add 2 to your total weapon destiny when targeting a non-unique alien.
front.lore: The Empire considers alien species to be inferior.
front.title: •Imperial Tyranny

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot and 8 passengers. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.
front.lore: Four-legged, enclosed combat vehicle. The monstrous, plodding AT-AT (All Terrain Armored Transport) can carry an entire squadron of armed troops.
front.title: Imperial Walker

combo: Imperial-Class Star Destroyer + Imperial Helmsman Draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

front.gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles and 4 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.
front.lore: Mainstay of Imperial Navy. 1.6 kilometers long. Has hangars and facilities for TIE fighter squadrons, shuttles, drop-ships and combat vehicles such as AT-ATs and AT-ATs.
front.title: Imperial-Class Star Destroyer

combo: In Range + any Star Destroyer + Tractor Beam
In Range + Our First Catch of the Day

front.gametext: If you have a Star Destroyer in a battle, during the weapons segment use its tractor beam for free. Add 2 to tractor beam destiny if targeting a unique (•) starship. If not captured, target is power and maneuver -3 for remainder of turn.
front.lore: 'They'll be in range of our tractor beam in moments, my lord.' 'Good. Prepare the boarding party and set your weapons for stun.'
front.title: •In Range

rulings: This Interrupt targets a specific starship (e.g. for the purposes of Han's Toolkit).
A starship captured and stolen mid-battle with In Range becomes inactive that battle.

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Each turn, each of your characters, vehicles, and starships may forfeit one of its weapons (except a lightsaber) using forfeit value = 3. Also, your forfeited weapons go to Used Pile. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: With its superior numbers, the Empire knowingly sacrifices the safety of many units and weapons in order to preserve the greater war machine.
front.title: •Inconsequential Losses

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points
rulings: A character/starship/vehicle may only forfeit a weapon that is deployed directly on itself.
Causes all of your forfeited weapons go to Used Pile, even if not forfeited via this Effect (e.g. artillery weapons being forfeited normally).

combo: Infantry Battle Droid + Daultay Dofine

front.gametext: Power +1 in battles you initiate. Once per turn, if this droid just fired a blaster and 'hit' an opponent's character, opponent loses 1 Force. Opponent's Gungans and Republic characters present are forfeit -1.
front.lore: Main unit of the Trade Federation droid army. Cheap to manufacture. Required to be in contact with a Droid Control Ship at all times.
front.title: Infantry Battle Droid

front.gametext: Deploy at same exterior site as your mining droid. 'Explodes' if a character deploys or moves (without using a vehicle or starfighter) to or across same site. Draw destiny. Character lost if destiny +2 > ability. Infantry Mine is also lost.
front.lore: Deadly explosive typically planted on the perimeter of strategic sites or high-security installations to prevent Rebel spies and saboteurs from gaining access.
front.title: Infantry Mine

front.gametext: If a battle was just initiated at same site as your Undercover spy, your characters at adjacent sites may move there as a 'react' (for free). OR Cancel Sabotage.
front.lore: The Empire's network of spies and petty informants allows Imperial operatives to discover and react to Rebel assaults before they occur.
front.title: Informant

front.gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Whenever you have an information broker at a location where you just initiated a battle, you may examine the top four cards of opponent's Reserve Deck. You may then lose 1 Force to immediately cancel the battle.
front.lore: Chisa nyooda ishaley. Kun Jabba neguda len Malta.' 'Ikkit ui! Yobbit, yobbiy. Nelan tui ke bada.'
front.title: •Information Exchange

front.gametext: If A Stunning Move on table, deploy on 500 Republica. Opponent's Force generation is -1 here. While at a site (even while on a captive), adds one [Dark Side] icon here. While on Coruscant, opponent loses no more than 1 Force from your Force drains here. Once per turn, if a player controls this site, they may have this card (unless on Palpatine) follow their first character to move from here using landspeed (or docking bay transit) to a battleground site. If about to leave table, relocate to 500 Republica (if possible).
front.title: •Insidious Prisoner

front.gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on table. Each time you win a battle, opponent loses 1 Force (cannot be reduced) and stacks lost card here face down. When attempting to cross Luke over (except with Epic Duel), add 3 to total destiny for each card in stack. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: 'Your fleet is lost. And your friends on the Endor moon will not survive. There is no escape, my young apprentice.'
front.title: •Insignificant Rebellion

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points
rulings: If a player loses Force from hand to stack here, it is first revealed to both players, then stacked face down.
If a player loses Force from Life Force to stack here, it is not revealed to anyone. Stack it face down, unseen.
Text referring to cards stacked 'on'/'under'/'beneath' this Effect all means the same thing.
Neither player may view Light's cards after they are stacked face down here.

front.gametext: Each player, if that player has a capital starship armed with a starship weapon in battle, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise and once per battle, may reduce the defense value of one opponent's capital starship present by 4 for remainder of the battle. At sites related to systems you occupy, your non-pilot warriors are deploy -1, defense value +2 and forfeit +1.
front.title: •Intensify The Forward Batteries

front.gametext: Deploy on a prison. During your control phase, opponent loses 1 Force for each captive of ability > 2 here. Also, during your control phase, may use 1 Force to search your Reserve Deck, take one Torture or Aiiii! Aaa! Agggggggggg! into hand and reshuffle.
front.lore: Torture rack so visually frightening it sometimes yields the desired results without even being switched on.
front.title: •Interrogation Array

front.gametext: Deploy on your TIE Bomber, TIE Defender or freighter. May target a capital starship for free. Draw destiny. Add 3 if that capital starship was targeted by another weapon this turn. Target hit if total destiny > defense value. After firing, place Missile in Used Pile.
front.lore: Produced by Sienar for TIE bombers and TIE defenders, using plans stolen from Slayn & Korpil by ISB agents. Often sold to bounty hunters and mercenaries by Black Sun.
front.title: Intruder Missile

back.gametext: Invasion:Deploy Naboo system with Blockade Flagship there, swamp, and Droid Racks.{For} remainder of game, you may not deploy cards with ability except [Trade Federation] starships and characters with 'Trade Federation' in lore. Civil Disorder is canceled.{While} this side up, once during your deploy phase may deploy a Naboo site from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Opponent's Force icons at Naboo system are canceled.{Flip} this card if you control Theed Palace Throne Room (with a Neimoidian there) and Naboo system.In Complete Control:{While} this side up, you lose no more than 2 Force to any Force drain. Your battle droids deploy -1. If you have two [Presence] droids with different card titles (or a [Presence] droid and a Neimoidian) in battle at a site, draw two battle destiny if unable to otherwise. Your droid starfighters are immune to attrition < 3. If opponent just drew an Interrupt for battle destiny, once per battle you may place that card out of play.{Flip} this card if opponent controls Naboo system or Theed Palace Throne Room.
back.title: Invasion / In Complete Control

Civil Disorder is canceled.{While} this side up, once during your deploy phase may deploy a Naboo site from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Opponent's Force icons at Naboo system are canceled.{Flip} this card if you control Theed Palace Throne Room (with a Neimoidian there) and Naboo system.In Complete Control:{While} this side up, you lose no more than 2 Force to any Force drain. Your battle droids deploy -1. Your droid starfighters are immune to attrition < 3. If opponent just drew an Interrupt for battle destiny, once per battle you may place that card out of play.{Flip} this card if opponent controls Naboo system or Theed Palace Throne Room.
front.title: Invasion / In Complete Control

rulings: While 0-side is up, Naboo is a non-battleground in all states. For example, it may not be deployed by cards that deploy a battleground and it does not count towards the five battleground systems for Hidden Base.
As an exception, Naboo is considered a battleground during the 'start of game' when being checked by cards such as Careful Planning (V).
underlyingCardFor: A Stunning Move / A Valuable Hostage

front.gametext: May add 3 pilots, 5 passengers, and 4 [Trade Federation] starfighters. Permanent pilot provides ability of 3. Adds one battle destiny if Grievous on table. Immune to attrition < 5.
front.lore: Blank.
front.title: •Invisible Hand

front.gametext: Dark:  Once per game, if you control, may take Invisible Hand into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.  Light:  Unless your [Clone Army] character here, Force drain -1 here.
front.title: •Invisible Hand: Bridge

front.gametext: Dark:  Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force (free if your [Presence] droid present).  Light:  Your docking bay transit from here requires 3 Force (free if Palpatine present).
front.title: •Invisible Hand: Docking Bay

pulledBy: Begin Landing Your Troops & Fighters Straight Ahead
rulings: A starfighter (belonging to <u>either player</u>!) at same system or sector as Invisible Hand may land here.
A starfighter (belonging to <u>either player</u>!) here may take off to same system or sector as Invisible Hand.
If Invisible Hand is lost from table, this site remains on table.

front.gametext: Dark:  If you occupy, opponent must use +1 Force to move from here using landspeed.  Light:  You move to here using landspeed for free.
front.title: •Invisible Hand: Hallway 328

front.gametext: Dark:  While Insidious Prisoner here, your characters are power +1 here.  Light:  While your [Clone Army] character here, your characters are defense value +1 here.
front.title: •Invisible Hand: Observatory Entrance

combo: Ion Cannon + Turbolaser Battery
Ion Cannon + I Want That Ship
Ion Cannon + Tractor Beam

front.gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your Star Destroyer. May target a starship using 1 Force. Draw destiny. If destiny +2 > defense value, all starship weapons deployed on target are lost, armor or maneuver = 0 and hyperspeed = 0.
front.lore: Fires blasts of ionized energy. Causes massive disruptions in weapon, engine and computer systems aboard a target. Disables starship defenses against tractor beams.
front.title: Ion Cannon

rulings: Whether fired during battle or at another time, the target starship is armor/maneuver and hyperspeed = 0 until it leaves play (or until something makes it 'restored to normal').
Weapons aboard the starship are only lost as a one-time response to the Cannon firing. Weapons can subsequently be deployed on the starship without becoming lost.

back.gametext: ISB Operations:Deploy any Coruscant location.{For} remainder of game, your characters with 'ISB,' 'Rebel' or 'Rebellion' in lore are ISB agents and spies, and may deploy regardless of deployment restrictions listed in their game text.{Flip} this card if ISB agents control at least two Rebel Base locations or if four ISB agents are on table.Empire's Sinister Agents:{While} this side up, once during each of your draw phases, you may retrieve one ISB agent. When you have a non-Undercover ISB agent at a battleground site, your Force drains are +1 there and opponent's Force drains are -1 at same and related locations.{Flip} this card if no ISB agents are on table.
back.title: ISB Operations / Empire's Sinister Agents

front.gametext: ISB Operations:Deploy any Coruscant location.{For} remainder of game, your characters with 'ISB,' 'Rebel' or 'Rebellion' in lore are ISB agents and spies, and may deploy regardless of deployment restrictions listed in their game text.{Flip} this card if ISB agents control at least two Rebel Base locations or if four ISB agents are on table.Empire's Sinister Agents:{While} this side up, once during each of your draw phases, you may retrieve one ISB agent. When you have a non-Undercover ISB agent at a battleground site, your Force drains are +1 there and opponent's Force drains are -1 at same and related locations.{Flip} this card if no ISB agents are on table.
front.title: ISB Operations / Empire's Sinister Agents

canceledBy: Force drain bonus is canceled by Captive Fury

front.gametext: When at Detention Block Corridor, adds X to your Force drains there, where X = the number of captives present. Immune to Restraining Bolt.
front.lore: Floating prisoner interrogation droid. Uses probes and needles to dispense truth drugs and perform 'surgery.' Sensors determine subject's pain threshold and truthfulness.
front.title: •IT-O (Eyetee-Oh)

rulings: Does not count frozen captives.
If stolen by Light, its Force drain bonus does not work.

front.gametext: USED: If opponent just landed a starship at an exterior site, you may deploy up to three related sites from your Reserve Deck; reshuffle.  LOST: Use 2 Force to 'scan' (reveal) opponent's hand. You may place one starship you find there in opponent's Used Pile.
front.lore: Even though Vader allowed the stolen shuttle Tydirium to land on Endor, he had a plan to deal with the Rebels.
front.title: •It's An Older Code

front.gametext: If It Could Be Worse was just played, it is canceled and you may use X Force to raise damage against opponent by X amount. OR If opponent just lost Force from a battle, play to increase loss by 1 Force.
front.lore: Things went from bad to worse when Luke was attacked by a dianoga, a parasitic predator native to the planet Vodran.
front.title: It's Worse

rulings: Increases the original Force loss amount, for example a Force drain of 1 could be increased to a drain of 6, then finally the damage capped to 2 by Ultimatum.

When increasing the loss from a Force drain, It's Worse is a Force drain modifier and a Force drain bonus. As such, its increase to a Force drain can be entirely eliminated by (for example) Menace Fades, Great Warrior, or The Planet That It's Farthest From.
Responses to the original Force loss are no longer possible, for example a Force drain that has been increased can no longer be canceled by Control.

front.gametext: Use 1 Force to target opponent's starfighter with maneuver at a system or sector where a battle just finished. Draw destiny. Starfighter lost if destiny > maneuver.
front.lore: Debris fragments damaged Jek Porkins' X-wing, causing a cascade of computer and flight control failures.
front.title: I've Got A Problem Here

combo: I've lost Artoo! + Lateral Damage (NateA)

front.gametext: Use 1 Force to target a starship's [Nav Computer] or astromech. Draw destiny. If destiny > 1, [Nav Computer] or astromech is lost. If starship's [Nav Computer] is lost, place Effect on starship (may add 1 astromech); otherwise, Effect lost.
front.lore: 'WHAAAAAAAAAOOOOW!'
front.title: I've Lost Artoo!

rulings: If this Effect is canceled, the nav computer it removed (if any) is restored.

If this Effect is canceled, the added astromech capacity is removed. If this results in insufficient capacity, astromech owner moves it to a passenger slot (if available), otherwise place astromech in Used Pile.

combo: Jabba + 4-LOM With Concussion Rifle 4-LOM adds one battle destiny with Jabba.
Jabba + Boelo Cancel one opponent's battle destiny.
Jabba + Ephant Mon + Chokk

front.gametext: To use his landspeed requires +1 Force. Your aliens are deploy -1 to same location. While at Audience Chamber, adds 2 to forfeit of all your non-unique aliens and makes Scum And Villainy immune to Alter. Immune to attrition < 4.
front.lore: Gangster. Leader. Infamous Hutt crime lord. Operates his vast empire from an ancient monastery on Tatooine. Uses mercenary pilots to smuggle spice and other contraband.
front.title: •Jabba

combo: Jabba Desilijic Tiure + 4-LOM With Concussion Rifle 4-LOM adds one battle destiny with Jabba.
Jabba Desilijic Tiure + Boelo Cancel one opponent's battle destiny.
Jabba Desilijic Tiure + Ephant Mon + Chokk

front.gametext: While at Podrace Arena, once during your control phase may 'wager'. Both players draw destiny and add 2 if they have won a Podrace. Loser (lowest total) loses 1 Force. If you just won the wager and Bib Fortuna is present, you may retrieve 1 Force.
front.lore: Gangster and leader in control of Tatooine. The amount of credits Jabba earns from Podracing is said to be vast, but only Bib Fortuna knows the exact number.
front.title: •Jabba Desilijic Tiure

combo: Jabba The Hutt + 4-LOM With Concussion Rifle 4-LOM adds one battle destiny with Jabba.
Jabba Jabba The Hutt + Boelo Cancel one opponent's battle destiny.
Jabba The Hutt + Ephant Mon + Chokk

front.gametext: Deploy -2 at Tatooine or Nal Hutta. To use his landspeed requires +2 Force. May escort a captive. While at Audience Chamber, adds 1 to forfeit of all your other aliens and allows you to activate 1 Force for whenever you Force drain with an alien. Immune to attrition < 4.
front.lore: Jabba Desilijic Tiure. Male heir to Zorba the Hutt. Gangster. Leader of one of the largest criminal organizations in the galaxy. Over six hundred years old.
front.title: •Jabba The Hutt

rulings: +2 Force to move is <u>only</u> for landspeed. It is <u>not</u> for Elis Helrot, Docking Bay Transit, Shuttling, etc.
While Jabba at Audience Chamber, the 'adds 1 to forfeit' bonus and 'activate 1 Force' bonus are global, not limited to the Audience Chamber.
Dark can even Force drain for 0 at a location with no Light icons, then receive the 'activate 1 Force' bonus as a result.

combo: Jabba The Hutt (V) + Ephant Mon + Chokk Efficient Combo; Ephant Mon is an alien leader.
Bib Fortuna (EP1) is power 12 when Jabba uses 1 Force to double power.
Jabba The Hutt (V) + 4-LOM With Concussion Rifle 4-LOM adds one battle destiny with Jabba.
Jabba The Hutt (V) + Boelo Cancel one opponent's battle destiny.

front.gametext: While with your alien leader, Jabba is immune to attrition and may not be targeted by Interrupts or weapons. May deploy one Scum And Villainy from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. During battle, may use 1 Force to double the power of one other non-[Maintenance] alien present.
front.lore: Jabba Desilijic Tiure. Male heir to Zorba the Hutt. Gangster. Leader of one of the largest criminal organizations in the galaxy. Over six hundred years old.
front.title: •Jabba The Hutt (V)

rulings: While with a Dark alien leader, may not use Weapon Levitation.
Stunning Leader will exclude the alien leader, and then as a result will also exclude Jabba The Hutt (V).

front.gametext: If a Jabba's Palace site on table, deploy on table. The Camp is canceled. May deploy Nal Hutta from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Once per battle, may lose 1 Force; your battle destiny modifiers affect your total battle destiny instead. Once per game, may retrieve a non-[Maintenance] alien or [Independent] starship into hand. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Jabba has won the service of many of his guards and other henchbeings through games of chance.
front.title: •Jabba's Haven

rulings: If Revenge Of The Sith is on table and Dark loses 1 Force to make battle destiny modifiers affect total battle destiny instead, then the first Sith drawn for battle destiny will cause Revenge Of The Sith to add +2 to total battle destiny. The next Sith drawn for battle destiny will <u>not</u> cause Revenge Of The Sith to add another +2 (the cumulative rule prevents it).

front.gametext: Deploy on one of your gangsters or bounty hunters. Once during each of your control phases, if present with an opponent's smuggler or character of ability = 1, may use 3 Force. Opponent must use 5 Force or that character returns to opponent's hand.
front.lore: Jabba makes offers one cannot refuse. Smugglers, thieves and competitors who do not acquiesce have been rumored to wake up with a bantha's head in their bed.
front.title: •Jabba's Influence

front.gametext: Requirements: Gambler, gangster, smuggler or information broker at a Jabba's Palace site. Wild cards (1-6): Passenger Deck and deserts. Clone cards: Aliens and Jabba's Palace sites (gamblers and Jabba may use clones as 4). Stakes: One character weapon or non-unique alien.
front.lore: Jabba has won the service of many of his guards and other henchbeings through games of chance.
front.title: •Jabba's Palace Sabacc

canceledBy: B'omarr Monk cancels Jabba's Palace Dark Side game text where present
combo: Jabba's Palace: Audience Chamber + Gailid Gailid adds 1 to Force drains at Jabba's Palace sites.

front.gametext: Dark:  One per game you may deploy one alien here from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.  Light:  If you control, may use 4 Force to cancel Scum and Villainy. Immune to Revolution.
front.title: •Jabba's Palace: Audience Chamber

pulls: One alien from Reserve Deck once per game

canceledBy: B'omarr Monk cancels Jabba's Palace Dark Side game text where present

front.gametext: Dark:  Your droids deploy -1 here.  Light:  If you control, with a droid here, Force drain +1 here.
front.title: •Jabba's Palace: Droid Workshop

canceledBy: B'omarr Monk cancels Jabba's Palace Dark Side game text where present

front.gametext: Dark:  Whenever a bounty hunter delivers a captive here, retrieve 2 Force (once per captive).  Light:  If you control, may use 3 Force to release an imprisoned captive here.
front.title: •Jabba's Palace: Dungeon

canceledBy: B'omarr Monk cancels Jabba's Palace Dark Side game text where present

front.gametext: Dark:  Bib Fortuna deploys -3 here. If you control, with a Gamorrean here, Force drain +1 here.  Light:  If you control, Force drain +1 here and your aliens deploy -2 here.
front.title: •Jabba's Palace: Entrance Cavern

canceledBy: B'omarr Monk cancels Jabba's Palace Dark Side game text where present

front.gametext: Dark:  During your move phase, your aliens may move between here and any Jabba's Palace site.  Light:  While your Lando here, opponent's Lower Passages game text is canceled. Force drain -1 here.
front.title: •Jabba's Palace: Lower Passages

canceledBy: B'omarr Monk cancels Jabba's Palace Dark Side game text where present

front.gametext: Dark:  Dark Waters may deploy here. If a creature present, cards cannot move from here.  Light:  If your character here is 'eaten,' opponent retrieves Force equal to character's forfeit.
front.title: •Jabba's Palace: Rancor Pit

back.gametext: {Deploys only at start of game if Carbon Chamber Testing is on table to Security Tower, frozen and imprisoned, (instead of a Rebel from opponent's Reserve Deck). If You Can Either Profit By This... is on table, opponent does not deploy Han at start of game (relocate Jabba's Prize to Audience Chamber, flip Carbon Chamber Testing, and you may not move or transfer Jabba's Prize)}. May not be placed in Reserve Deck. Jabba's Prize is a persona of Han only while on table. If Jabba's Prize leaves table, place it out of play. May not be targeted by We're The Bait or Someone Who Loves You. While Jabba's Prize is at Audience Chamber, Jabba is power +3, defense value +3, and adds 3 to his immunity to attrition. If Jabba's Prize was just released, opponent may replace it with any Han from hand, Used Pile, or Reserve Deck; reshuffle (if not replaced, place Jabba's Prize out of play).
back.lore: Han Solo was frozen in carbonite to test the process Vader planned to use on Luke. When Boba Fett delivered Han to Jabba, the vile gangster called him his 'favorite decoration.'
back.title: •Jabba's Prize / Jabba's Prize

front.gametext: {Deploys only at start of game if Carbon Chamber Testing is on table to Security Tower, frozen and imprisoned, (instead of a Rebel from opponent's Reserve Deck). If You Can Either Profit By This... is on table, opponent does not deploy Han at start of game (relocate Jabba's Prize to Audience Chamber, flip Carbon Chamber Testing, and you may not move or transfer Jabba's Prize)}. May not be placed in Reserve Deck. Jabba's Prize is a persona of Han only while on table. If Jabba's Prize leaves table, place it out of play. May not be targeted by We're The Bait or Someone Who Loves You. While Jabba's Prize is at Audience Chamber, Jabba is power +3, defense value +3, and adds 3 to his immunity to attrition. If Jabba's Prize was just released, opponent may replace it with any Han from hand, Used Pile, or Reserve Deck; reshuffle (if not replaced, place Jabba's Prize out of play).
front.lore: Han Solo was frozen in carbonite to test the process Vader planned to use on Luke. When Boba Fett delivered Han to Jabba, the vile gangster called him his 'favorite decoration.'
front.title: •Jabba's Prize / Jabba's Prize

rulings: Must be used with Carbon Chamber Testing and the instructions must be followed at the start of game.
Despite being a captive, all of this card's text is applicable whenever appropriate.
If freed while You Can Either Profit By This... on table, Light flips that objective first, then retrieves 10 Force for the 0 power Han, and then finally may replace Jabba's Prize with a Han card.

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine; you may immediately deploy Passenger Deck from your Reserve Deck and reshuffle. May add 1 driver and 7 passengers. Your aliens deploy -1 aboard.
front.lore: Ubrikkian sail barge. Custom built for Jabba with an armored hull and weaponry. Top speed of 100 kph. Used by the Hutt crimelord on his many trips to Mos Eisley.
front.title: •Jabba's Sail Barge

rulings: May deploy Passenger Deck even though Jabba's Sail Barge is unpiloted.

front.gametext: May add 1 alien driver and 8 passengers. Your vehicle weapons deploy free aboard. Once per turn, may deploy Passenger Deck or a skiff here from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. While on Tatooine with a skiff, Force drain +1 here.
front.lore: Ubrikkian sail barge. Custom built for Jabba with an armored hull and weaponry. Top speed of 100 kph. Used by the Hutt crimelord on his many trips to Mos Eisley.
front.title: •Jabba's Sail Barge (V)

rulings: May deploy Passenger Deck or a skiff even if Jabba's Sail Barge is unpiloted.

front.gametext: Dark:  If you occupy, Sail Barge is immune to attrition.  Light:  Your characters may enter/exit here for 4 Force each.
front.title: •Jabba's Sail Barge: Passenger Deck

rulings: May deploy regardless of whether Jabba's Sail Barge is on table, and this site is not lost when Jabba's Sail Barge is lost.
This site is 'adjacent' to the site where the Jabba's Sail Barge vehicle is (for example, Expand The Empire can expand text to or from the Passenger Deck).
This site is 'related' to all sites on the same planet that Jabba's Sail Barge is on.
This site does <u>not</u> take on the name of the planet (e.g. it is not a Tatooine site, a character here is not 'on Tatooine' or 'on Cloud City' even if the Sail Barge is, etc).

front.gametext: Deploys and moves like a starfighter. May add 2 alien pilots and 6 passengers. Turbolaser Battery may deploy aboard as a 'react.' When Jabba aboard, moves for free and immune to attrition.
front.lore: Flying fortress of Jabba Desilijic Tiure. Reaches speeds of 800 kph in atmosphere. The crime lord installed hidden gunports as an unpleasant surprise for would-be pirates.
front.title: •Jabba's Space Cruiser

rulings: Third sentence refers only to a card with the exact title Turbolaser Battery, not Heavy Turbolaser Battery.
Third sentence only allows Turbolaser Battery to deploy aboard as a react, not during deploy phase.

front.gametext: May add 1 alien pilot and 6 passengers. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. When deployed, you may deploy an alien leader aboard from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Immune to attrition < 5.
front.lore: Flying fortress of Jabba Desilijic Tiure. Reaches speeds of 800 kph in atmosphere. The crime lord installed hidden gunports as an unpleasant surprise for would-be pirates.
front.title: •Jabba's Space Cruiser (V)

front.gametext: If your bounty hunter just fired a character weapon during a battle, add one battle destiny. OR During your deploy phase, deploy one character weapon on your bounty hunter from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: 'Klees ka tlanko ya oska.'
front.title: •Jabba's Through With You

pulls: One character weapon to deploy on your bounty hunter

front.gametext: Deploy on table. If Jabba just Force drained (or won a battle), stack top card of opponent's Lost Pile here; may draw top card of your Reserve Deck. If 4 or more cards here, may return this Effect and a character with Jabba at Audience Chamber to owner's hand. (Immune to Alter.)

front.lore: Imperial council member. Very cruel at heart. Has lusted for power his entire life. Predictable and controllable.
front.title: •Janus Greejatus

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. To deploy, requires 1 Force from each players' Force Pile. Power +1 on Tatooine. While with another Jawa, if opponent just initiated a Force drain at adjacent site, may use 2 Force to reduce it by 1.
front.lore: Every now and then, Jawas will pause in their scavenging duties to take in a Podrace. Many believe this is only because they want to be first to a crash scene.
front.title: Jawa

front.gametext: To deploy, requires 1 Force from each players' Force Pile. Cannot deploy otherwise. Deploy only on Tatooine, but may move elsewhere.
front.lore: Small, rodent-like scavenger species. Refurbish and sell droids. Nest in sandcrawlers. Considered to be pests by most species.

front.gametext: Deploy on your Jawa. May target a character or creature for free. Draw destiny. If destiny -1 > defense value, target hit. If destiny = 0, Jawa Blaster 'explodes' (weapon and character firing it are lost).
front.lore: Built from scavenged parts, Jawa blaster are not required to adhere to any design standards. An etching on this stock warns 'datinni greb zroom.'
front.title: Jawa Blaster

combo: Jawa Pack + First Strike (Psychobabble)

front.gametext: To deploy (on your side of table), requires 3 Force from both players' Force Piles. Cannot deploy otherwise. All your Jawas are forfeit +1.
front.lore: Jawas travel in packs for protection. They use ambush tactics against unwary droids in the canyons of the Jundland Wastes. 'Aeeeyaa!'
front.title: •Jawa Pack

front.gametext: Dark:  While you control, your superlaser weapon destiny draws are +1.  Light:  Unless Baze, Bodhi, Chirrut, or Saw here, Force drain -1 here.

front.gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on any alien (except Boba Fett or Jabba). May 'fly' (landspeed = 3). May use 2 Force to move as a 'react'.
front.lore: Mitrinomon Z-6 jet pack. Exhaust vents are used to maneuver in midflight. Gyro-stabilizer automatically applies counterthrust when landing.
front.title: •••Jet Pack

front.gametext: When in battle, if opponent draws more than one battle destiny, may cancel one. Once per turn, when firing a rifle or blaster, may target for free and add 2 to total weapon destiny. May be targeted by Hidden Weapons. May 'fly' (landspeeed = 3).
front.lore: Bounty Hunter and scout. Perfectionist. Equipped with mandalorian armor and a jet pack. He doesn't mind being mistaken for Boba Fett. Occasionally works for Black Sun.
front.title: •Jodo Kast

rulings: May cancel any opponent's battle destiny except the first one. This works even if the first destiny was substituted (e.g. by Darklighter Spin).

If firing a repeating weapon (e.g. Light Repeating Blaster Rifle), only the first shot can be made free. The text can be used to add 2 to weapon destiny on a repeat firing instead, but it won't be free.
Jodo is not a 'character with Mandalorian Armor' so if his game text is canceled, he may not use Hidden Weapons.

front.gametext: Use 3 Force if Luke was just 'hit' by a lightsaber swung by Vader. Opponent must choose: Place Luke in owner's Used Pile OR Luke may not be forfeited this battle and crosses to the Dark Side at the end of the turn if still on table (is no longer 'hit').
front.lore: '...And together, we can rule the galaxy as father and son!'
front.title: •Join Me!

combo: J'Quille + Nevar Yalnal

front.gametext: Power +2 on Hoth. At the start of a battle, may cause one opponent's character of ability < 3 present to be excluded from the battle. While at Audience Chamber, all your other Whipids are forfeit +2.
front.lore: Whiphid spy in league with Lady Valarian. Yearns for battle. Enjoys hearing the screams of his victims. Plotting to kill Jabba.
front.title: •J'Quille

combo: Judicator + Imperial Helmsman Draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

front.gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles and 4 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. Each of its weapon destiny draws is +2. Starfighters it 'hits' are power = 0.
front.lore: Incorporates latest design modifications from Kuat Drive Yards. Targeting computers outfitted with antenna locking, in-line calibration and helical-motion extrapolators.
front.title: •Judicator

front.gametext: Dark:  May not deploy to Bespin, Coruscant, Hoth, Kessel or Tatooine. Your aliens and creature vehicles are each power +1 here.  Light:  May not deploy to Bespin, Coruscant, Hoth, Kessel or Tatooine. Force Drain -1 here. Your attrition against opponent is -2 here.
front.title: <>Jungle

front.gametext: Deploy on any alien if Cantina, Mos Eisley or Jabba's Sail Barge on table. That alien may not use ability in battles (if Kabe, she also cannot 'steal'). Utinni Effect canceled by moving that alien to one of those sites without 'driving' a vehicle.
front.lore: Popular beverage served in many cantinas and tapcafes. Has intoxicating effect on many species. Favorite drink of Kabe, Chadra-Fan thief of Mos Eisley.
front.title: •Juri Juice

rulings: Can be canceled by moving to a Jabba's Sail Barge site.
Can be canceled by moving to a site where Jabba's Sail Barge is.
The affected alien may not apply ability toward drawing battle destiny.
The affected alien's ability works normally for all other purposes (even during battle) such as for checking defense value swinging a Jedi Lightsaber, or being targeted by Trample.

front.gametext: Dark:  Force drain +1 here. If you control, all Wookiees on table are forfeit -3.  Light:  Your starships with any Wookiee aboard are power and forfeit +2 here.
front.title: •Kashyyyk

rulings: LS Text: A permanent pilot Chewbacca (e.g. Han Chewie And The Falcon) is not a Wookiee so it does not receive forfeit +2.
LS Text: If the Wookiee aboard is forfeited first, the starship is no longer forfeit +2 when it is forfeited afterwards (as such, the forfeit +2 text is rarely utilized).

front.gametext: While at a Kashyyyk site: adds 1 to your Force drains there, is power +1 (or +2 if your Trandoshan is on Kashyyyk) and, once during each of your deploy phases, may deploy one site to Kashyyyk from Reserve Deck- reshuffle.
front.lore: Hunters who track down escaped Wookiee slaves and report on their location. The Empire and Trandoshans pay a high price for that kind of information.
front.title: Kashyyyk Operative

Keder The Black + Supreme Chancellor Valorum
Keder The Black + Nevar Yalnal

front.gametext: Deploys only to a site as an Undercover spy (-2 on Coruscant). During your control phase, may 'break cover' to target one character with politics present. Draw destiny. If destiny +1 > target's politics, target and Keder are lost.
front.lore: A highly paid assassin and spy, Keder has infiltrated the Senate disguised as a Coruscant Guard. The identity of his target and his employer remains a mystery to all but him.
front.title: •Keder The Black

rulings: His title does not make him a member of Black Squadron.

front.gametext: Dark:  Your starships deploy -1 here, -2 if Tarkin is aboard a starship here. If you control, Kessel Run is canceled.  Light:  Total ability of 6 or more required for you to draw battle destiny here.
front.title: •Kessel

rulings: (Light side text) Passengers do not count towards the 6 ability requirement. If the requirement is not met, Light does not get any battle destiny draws (even if they have multiple battle destiny adders such as Captain Han Solo, Life Debt, etc). However, 'draws if unable to otherwise' still works without 6 ability.

front.gametext: While at a Kessel site: adds 1 to your Force drains there, is power +1 (or +2 if your smuggler is on Kessel) and, once during each of your deploy phases, may deploy one site to Kessel from Reserve Deckreshuffle.
front.lore: Mercenaries that make a profit selling materials to the troops stationed on Kessel. Help the Empire prevent escape attempts by the prisoners there.
front.title: Kessel Operative

front.gametext: Deploy on your non-warrior character (except droids) to give that character [Warrior] skill. OR Deploy on your warrior. That character is power +1. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Assassins are highly valued by Jabba the Hutt and other gangsters. Prince Xizor's 'shadow killer,' has unknown but undoubtably lethal business in Mos Eisley.
front.title: Ket Maliss

underlyingCardFor: Shadow Collective / You Know Who I Answer To

front.gametext: Dark:  If you occupy with exactly 2 starships, your total power here is +2 and Tonnika Sisters anywhere are doubled.  Light:  If you occupy with exactly 2 starships, your total power here is +2.
front.title: •Kiffex

rulings: When Tonnika Sisters is doubled, it means that every printed number on the card (even in game text) is doubled (e.g. 2 becomes 4) and it also means that 'Twice' in game text becomes 'Four times'.
Tonnika Sisters is doubled globally (will deploy for 4, not 2).
Apply the doubling to Tonnika Sisters first, before any modifiers or other changes (e.g. if affected by Ket Maliss, double Tonnika Sisters to 4 power, then add +1 from Ket Maliss).

front.gametext: While at a Kiffex site: adds 1 to your Force drains there, is power +1 (or +2 if your spy is on Kiffex) and, once during each of your deploy phases, may deploy one site to Kiffex from Reserve Deck- reshuffle.
front.lore: Couriers. Watchful for any kind of activity by the Alliance or the Empire. Sell their information to anyone willing to buy.
front.title: Kiffex Operative

front.gametext: Use 5 Force to reveal opponent's hand. If opponent has no duplicate cards there, place this Interrupt in Used Pile. OtherwiseUSED: place a revealed card in opponent's Used Pile.  LOST: all cards opponent has two or more of are lost. (Immune to Sense.)
front.lore: Darth Sidious instructed Nute Gunray to dispose of the Jedi ambassadors. Rune Haako was not so confident.
front.title: •Kill Them Immediately

rulings: As a special exception to the rules, the USED and LOST functions are both immune to Sense.

front.gametext: If opponent just forfeited or lost a character, use 1 Force to regenerate one of your own characters. Retrieve the character closest to the top of your Lost Pile into your hand.
front.lore: A dejarik of a ferocious creature with incredible healing abilities. Extinct on the homeworld of Kintan, but used as a guard beasts by many Hutt gangsters.
front.title: Kintan Strider

front.gametext: When armed with a Force pike, adds one battle destiny. Once during each of your deploy phases, lose 1 Force or place Kanos and cards deployed on him in owner's Used Pile (if Emperor on table, may use 1 Force instead).
front.lore: Fiercely devoted Royal Guard. Feels deeply indebted to those who risk their life for him. Unaware of the extent of Palpatine's atrocities and cruelty.
front.title: •Kir Kanos

front.gametext: When deployed, may take a Royal Guard into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. During battle, if with an Imperial and present at a site, once per game may cancel a non-[Immune to Sense] Interrupt.
front.lore: Fiercely devoted Royal Guard. Feels deeply indebted to those who risk their life for him. Unaware of the extent of Palpatine's atrocities and cruelty.
front.title: •Kir Kanos (V)

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. Adds 1 to power of anything he pilots. Power = 1 + ability of opponent's highest-ability character present.
front.lore: Famous Klatooinian assassin. After disposing of a few more prisoners, plans to quit the killing business and become a full-time musician. Rises to the challenges he faces.
front.title: •Kithaba

front.gametext: Immediately lost if at same site as overprotective mother, Kal'Faln C'ndros. Cannot board starfighters or enclosed vehicles.
front.lore: A female insectoid Yam'rii. Very strong and easily angered. Known for stealth, but also has good technological aptitude. Meat eater. Loves eggs.
front.title: •Kitik Keed'kak

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. Power +2 when with Barada or defending a battle a a Jabba's Palace site. During a battle at same site, may forfeit a transport vehicle present to satisfy all remaining battle damage and attrition against you.
front.lore: Kadas'sa'Nikto. Barada's main assistant. In charge of repairing Jabba's skiffs. Gambler. Always tries to make it back to the palace to watch the Rancor get fed.
front.title: •Klaatu

front.title: •Knowledge And Defense

front.lore: 'A Jedi uses the Force for knowledge and defense, never for attack.'

front.gametext: Ferocity = 6 + two destiny. Habitat: deserts and Tatooine exterior sites. May not deploy to an occupied site. If defeated, opponent may draw destiny and retrieve Force equal to destiny draw.
front.lore: Krayt dragons have beautiful and valuable pearls inside them as a gizzard to grind up food. Their fierceness is legendary. Up to 10 meters tall and 30 meters long.
front.title: •Krayt Dragon

front.lore: Tusken Raiders, Jawas and other desert dwellers believe that krayt dragon bones possess mystical powers that can bring good or bad luck.
front.title: •Krayt Dragon Bones

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Once per turn, if Death Star orbiting a battleground, may peek at top two cards of your Force Pile and take one into hand. Once per game, may take a non-unique Star Destroyer into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Commander. Leader.
front.title: •Krennic, Death Star Commandant

front.gametext: Deploy on Kuat system. All your Imperial-class Star Destroyers are immune to attrition < 4. Once during each of your deploy phases, may deploy one Imperial-class Star Destroyer here from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter while you occupy Kuat.)
front.lore: Company that produces current generation of Star Destroyers, as well as Nebulon-B Frigates. Ship yards are extremely well defended.
front.title: •Kuat Drive Yards

front.lore: Company that produces current generation of Star Destroyers, as well as Nebulon-B Frigates. Ship yards are extremely well defended.
front.title: •Kuat Drive Yards (V)

front.gametext: Adds one destiny to total power when with a [First Order] shuttle. While present at a battleground, Honor Of The Jedi is suspended. Whenever a player loses a battle here, that player loses 2 Force. Immune to attrition < 4.
front.lore: Leader.
front.title: •Kylo Ren

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Permanent weapon is •Kylo's Lightsaber (may target a character for free; draw 2 destiny; target hit, its forfeit = 0, and opponent loses 1 Force if total destiny > defense value; otherwise you lose 1 Force).
front.lore: Leader.
front.title: •Kylo Ren With Lightsaber

rulings: If something prevents the target from being hit (e.g. Theed Palace Generator Core) neither player loses 1 Force.

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Permanent weapon is •Kylo's Lightsaber (may target a character for free; draw 2 destiny; target hit, its forfeit = 0, and opponent loses 1 Force if total destiny > defense value; otherwise you lose 1 Force).
front.lore: Leader.
front.title: •Kylo Ren With Lightsaber (AI)

rulings: If something prevents the target from being hit (e.g. Theed Palace Generator Core) neither player loses 1 Force.

front.lore: Blank.

front.lore: Blank.
front.title: •Kylo Ren's Lightsaber
