front.title: My Lord, Is That Legal? / I Will Make It Legal

front.gametext: Deploys only on Coruscant or to Emperor's site (or related site). When armed with a Force pike, adds one battle destiny. Your troopers and Royal Guards may 'react' to here for free. Adds 1 to defense value of other Royal Guards at same and related sites.
front.lore: Royal Guard leader. Remembers nothing of his past other than serving his Emperor. Early instructor of Kir Kanos and Carnor Jax.
front.title: •Myn Kyneugh

front.gametext: When deployed, may play a Defensive Shield from under your Starting Effect (as if from hand). While at opponent's battleground, Force drains here may not be reduced. Once per game, may use 1 Force to place opponent's just-played Interrupt out of play.
front.lore: Royal Guard leader. Remembers nothing of his past other than serving his Emperor. Early instructor of Kir Kanos and Carnor Jax.
front.title: •Myn Kyneugh (V)

front.gametext: Habitat: unlimited. Parasite: Starfighter. Host's power and hyperspeed are cumulatively -2; while both < 1, Mynocks randomly detach one at a time (cannot attach for remainder of turn). Moves like a starfighter.
front.lore: Silicon-based space borne lifeform. Frequently called a 'power sucker.' Feeds on energy such as stellar radiation and electrical discharges. Absorbs minerals from starship hulks.
front.title: Mynock

combo: Myo + Bounty Hunters = Protect your low forefeit bounty hunters by throwing Myo in the way.
Myo + Lone Warrior + Moment of Triumph = You only lose the destiny adders.

front.gametext: Power +1 if present with Lirin Car'n or any bounty hunter. If lost or forfeited as a result of a battle, Myo 'regenerates' (place on top of your Used Pile).
front.lore: A regenerating, primitive, violent, desert dwelling, fearless, mercenary-joining, Lirin Car'n-befriending, cyclopian Abyssin from Byss. Calling him 'monoc' will start a fight.
front.title: •Myo

front.gametext: Dark:  If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Naboo sites.  Light:  If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Naboo sites.
front.title: •Naboo

front.gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your warrior or battle droid. May target a character, creature, or vehicle using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny +1 > defense value.
front.lore: Weapons were confiscated by battle droids during the Trade Federation's occupation of Naboo. Considered superior to blasters manufactured in the Outer Rim.
front.title: Naboo Blaster

front.gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your warrior or battle droid. May target a character, creature, or vehicle using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit if destiny +2 > defense value.
front.lore: A large quantity of these blasters found their way onto the black market after the Trade Federation's blockade of Naboo failed.
front.title: Naboo Blaster Rifle

front.gametext: Deploy on table. During your draw phase, may use 3 Force: until end of next turn, opponent generates no Force at Naboo sites you control with a battle droid. Place Effect in Lost Pile if you have no battle droids on Naboo. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Battle droid armies require less credits to maintain than the average soldier. Trade Federation tactics are designed to take advantage of these numbers.
front.title: •Naboo Occupation

front.gametext: Dark:  Unless Gungan Energy Shield on table, your AATs are each power +2 here.  Light:  Once per game may take Gungan Energy Shield into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.title: •Naboo: Battle Plains

front.gametext: Dark:  If your battle droid present, Force drain +1 here.  Light:  If your Gungan present, Force drain +1 here.
front.title: •Naboo: Swamp

front.gametext: Dark:  During your move phase, may move your characters from here to any interior Naboo site.  Light:  Add 1 to each of your weapon destiny draws here.
front.title: •Naboo: Theed Palace Courtyard

front.gametext: Dark:  Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force.  Light:  Your docking bay transit from here requires 2 Force.
front.title: •Naboo: Theed Palace Docking Bay

pulledBy: Begin Landing Your Troops & Fighters Straight Ahead

front.gametext: Dark:  Your Dark Jedi are power +2 here.  Light:  Your Jedi are power +1 here. Force drain -1 here.
front.title: •Naboo: Theed Palace Generator

front.gametext: Dark:  Any characters of ability < 5 'hit' here (and all cards on them) are placed in owner's Used Pile.  Light:  Any characters of ability < 5 'hit' here (and all cards on them) are placed in owner's Used Pile.
front.title: •Naboo: Theed Palace Generator Core

front.gametext: Dark:  Once per game, may deploy a battle droid here from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.  Light:  Force drain -1 here.
front.title: •Naboo: Theed Palace Hallway

front.gametext: Dark:  If Haako or Gunray present, Force drain +1 here.  Light:  Unless Amidala present, Force drain -1 here.
front.title: •Naboo: Theed Palace Throne Room

combo: Nal Hutta + Vengeance Vengeance is power +2 at Nal Hutta.

front.gametext: Dark:  During your control phase, may search Reserve Deck, take one Bounty or Hutt Bounty into hand; reshuffle.  Light:  If you control, Force drain -1 here and opponent's Nal Hutta game text is canceled.
front.title: •Nal Hutta

front.gametext: While at a Nal Hutta site: adds 1 to your Force drains there, is power +1 (or +2 if your gangster or Rodian is on Nal Hutta) and, once during each of your deploy phases, may deploy one site to Nal Hutta from Reserve Deck- reshuffle.
front.lore: Strong-armed H'nemthe thugs working for the Hutts. Work alongside Rodians and other unscrupulous aliens.
front.title: Nal Hutta Operative

front.gametext: Deploy -1 to a mobile site (except on Cloud City). When defending a battle, power +1 (or +2 if also at an interior site). When in battle against an operative, prevents opponent from drawing more than one battle destiny.
front.lore: Navy troopers are assigned to defend key installations. Trained to protect against alien species and other insurgents.
front.title: Navy Trooper

front.gametext: Subtracts 3 from Force opponent retrieves for On The Edge and Off The Edge. When at Bunker, adds 2 to deploy cost of each opponent's character (except Ewoks, spies and scouts) to Endor sites (except Rebel Landing Site).
front.lore: Rendili native skilled at close-quarters combat. Worked with Trooper Vesden to monitor enemy activity on Endor.
front.title: •Navy Trooper Fenson

front.gametext: Forfeit +2 while with Hewex. When at Bunker (or aboard a Star Destroyer at Endor), cumulatively adds 1 to deploy cost of each opponent's starship and non-Ewok vehicle deploying to Endor (or to your mobile site orbiting Endor)
front.lore: Many Imperial Navy troopers receive technical as well as combat training, which they use to maintain the Empire's military facilities.
front.title: •••Navy Trooper Shield Technician

front.gametext: If present with a Scomp link when Never Tell Me The Odds just reached the top of your Reserve Deck, may 'shield' (add 3 to destiny number of) one of your characters at each location for remainder of turn.
front.lore: Counterintelligence agent assigned by ISB. Operates sensors designed to protect the control bunker from infiltration.
front.title: •Navy Trooper Vesden

rulings: Vesden may respond to Never Tell Me The Odds only once (not a separate response for each location).
If Vesden responds, Dark chooses one of their characters at every location to 'shield'. Ignore any locations where Dark has no characters.

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. When in a battle with at least two of your other Jawas, adds one battle destiny. When your total battle destiny at Nebit's site is greater than opponent's total battle destiny, Nebit reduces attrition against you by 3.
front.lore: Jawa leader responsible for organizing raids on rival Jawa factions. Detested warrior. Hates being 'frocked.'
front.title: •Nebit

pulledBy: Herat to deploy to same location

front.gametext: USED: Use 2 Force to deploy a unique (•) battleground not on table, from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.  STARTING: Deploy from your Reserve Deck one Effect which deploys on table (or your side of table) and has no deploy cost; reshuffle. Place Interrupt in Lost Pile.
front.lore: 'We must move quickly to disrupt all communication down there.'
front.title: •Neimoidian Advisor

pulls: A unique battleground not on table:
One Effect which deploys on table and has no deploy cost

front.gametext: Deploys -2 at Naboo. When deployed aboard your battleship, you may activate 1 Force. Adds 2 to the power of any starship he pilots. Forfeit +2 while piloting.
front.lore: Trade Federation Neimodian pilots are some of the most desired in the galaxy due to their willingness to follow orders.
front.title: Neimoidian Pilot

front.errataNotes: Added the word 'total' as a clarification. No gameplay change.
front.gametext: If both players have a spy at same site, draw destiny. Add 2 if opponent's spy is Undercover. Opponent's spy is lost if total destiny > 2.
front.lore: Immense Ranat scavenger from Aralia. Slyly spies for anyone willing to pay his price. Outcast. Works as a laborer for Hrchek, the Saurin droid trader.
front.title: Nevar Yalnal

cancels: A battle opponent has just reacted to
cards.counterpart: I Have A Very Bad Feeling About This

front.gametext: If opponent just deployed four or more characters to same location this turn, prevent all of those characters from battling this turn. OR if opponent just 'reacted' to a battle, cancel the battle.
front.lore: Dejarik of a Ng'ok war beast. Foul temper gives rise to bad feelings.
front.title: Ng'ok

rulings: First function is played as a response to opponent's just deployed fourth character (or fifth, sixth, etc).
This Interrupt may be played even if the unique card Ng'ok War Beast is on table.

front.gametext: Deploy on table. If your character, starship, or vehicle in battle is about to be lost before the damage segment, it is instead lost at end of battle (if forfeited, forfeit for 0). (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Dejarik.
front.title: •Ng'ok War Beast

rulings: The text 'if forfeited, forfeit for 0' means that a substituted forfeit value of 0 is applied. This cannot be circumvented by cards such as Sacrifice.

If a hit character is excluded from battle (e.g. by Clash Of Sabers), the character is excluded, then automatically lost due to being hit outside of battle. Ng'ok War Beast does not protect a character in that situation.

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Once per turn may use 1 Force to look through opponent's Lost Pile and place all docking bays you find there out of play. Once per game may deploy Sebulba from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: 'Your buddy here was about to be turned into orange goo. He picked a fight with a Dug. An especially dangerous Dug called Sebulba.'
front.title: •Ni Chuba Na??

front.gametext: May not carry or use devices or weapons. Once per turn, may use X Force, where X = 1, 2, or 3, to add twice X to his power for remainder of turn.
front.lore: Mercenary from Vodran. Niado's culture controls its environment through terraforming facilities. Enhanced adrenal glands allow for short bursts of incredible strength.
front.title: •Niado Duegad

front.gametext: Deploys only to a Jabba's Palace site. Power and forfeit +2 when defending a battle at a Jabba's Palace site.
front.lore: Several different types if Nikto were sold to Jabba by slavers. Compete with Weequay to prove themselves the stronger species.
front.title: Nikto

front.gametext: Power +3 when present with your musician. When present at the start of a battle, may cause one character of ability < X to move away for free (or that character is immediately lost) where X = the number of your musicians present.
front.lore: Guard from Corulag. Former bouncer at the Mos Eisley cantina. Assigned by Jabba to guard celebrities visiting Jabba's palace. Friend of Wuher. Loves juri juice.
front.title: •Nizuc Bek

front.gametext: Deploy on your side of table. While no Imperials are at any Jabba's Palace sites: Rebels are deploy +2, Revolution is canceled and your non-unique aliens are each forfeit +1. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: 'Zeet tu seet. Jabba no tuzindy honkabee.'
front.title: •No Bargain

front.gametext: USED: During your move phase, take one of your characters with politics at Galactic Senate into hand.  LOST: If you have a Republic character with politics in battle at a site, add one battle destiny; that character is power and politics = 0 until end of turn.
front.lore: It's not rare to see a senator using the system to forward his own personal agenda. Much goes on behind closed doors that the Senate never sees.
front.title: •No Civility, Only Politics

front.gametext: Deploy on table. You may immediately take top card of Lost Pile into hand. Effects, Epic Events, and Objectives are immune to Honor Of The Jedi. At each opponent's <> site, your characters and vehicles are each deploy -3 and your Force generation is +1. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Jabba's influence is not easily ignored. Neither are his voracious and vile appetites. Even Jedi soon learn this lesson.
front.title: •No Escape

pulls: Top card of Lost Pile into hand
rulings: If deployed by a Starting Interrupt (e.g. Prepared Defenses), that Interrupt is not yet in the Lost Pile and cannot be taken into hand.
If deployed during the start of game, may take top card of Lost Pile (if any) into hand. In this case Dark's starting hand will have 1 more card than usual.
Example: A Starting Interrupt deploys Naboo Occupation which is immediately lost, then No Escape to take Naboo Occupation into hand.

front.gametext: Plays on table. At opponent's <> site where opponent's creature present, you may deploy without presence or Force icons, and your Force generation there is +1.
front.lore: Jabba's influence is not easily ignored. Neither are his voracious and vile appetites. Even Jedi soon learn this lesson.
front.title: •No Escape

front.gametext: If Maul armed with a lightsaber in battle, use 2 Force to draw two destiny. Opponent draws two destiny. If any of your destinies equal any of opponent's destinies, opponent's Jedi is power = 0 for remainder of battle.
front.lore: Lightsaber duels are so fast and furious that Jedi don't plan their offensive strategy, but instead rely on instinct and their ability to sense an opponent's next strike.
front.title: •No Match For A Sith

rulings: Only targets a single Jedi (specify target during initiation).

back.gametext: No Money, No Parts, No Deal!:Deploy Watto's Junkyard and Mos Espa.{For} remainder of game, Watto's Junkyard is immune to Revolution. If Watto at Watto's Junkyard, opponent may use 8 Force to place Watto in Used Pile and you may retrieve up to 4 Force.{While} this side up, Qui-Gon is power +3. Opponent loses no more than 1 Force from your Force drains at Tatooine sites.{Flip} this card if Watto present at Watto's Junkyard and you occupy Mos Espa.You're A Slave?:{While} this side up, once during each of your deploy phases, may place a card from hand face down on your side of the table and opponent must choose to lose 2 Force (you place card in Used Pile) or use 2 Force (you deploy that card for free). If opponent uses 2 Force and you cannot deploy card, lose 2 Force and card is lost. Opponent's non-unique aliens are each deploy +3.{Flip} this card if Watto not present at Watto's Junkyard or you do not occupy Mos Espa.
back.title: No Money, No Parts, No Deal! / You're A Slave?

front.gametext: No Money, No Parts, No Deal!:Deploy Watto's Junkyard and Mos Espa.{For} remainder of game, Watto's Junkyard is immune to Revolution. If Watto at Watto's Junkyard, opponent may use 8 Force to place Watto in Used Pile and you may retrieve up to 4 Force.{While} this side up, Qui-Gon is power +3. Opponent loses no more than 1 Force from your Force drains at Tatooine sites.{Flip} this card if Watto present at Watto's Junkyard and you occupy Mos Espa.You're A Slave?:{While} this side up, once during each of your deploy phases, may place a card from hand face down on your side of the table and opponent must choose to lose 2 Force (you place card in Used Pile) or use 2 Force (you deploy that card for free). If opponent uses 2 Force and you cannot deploy card, lose 2 Force and card is lost. Opponent's non-unique aliens are each deploy +3.{Flip} this card if Watto not present at Watto's Junkyard or you do not occupy Mos Espa.
front.title: No Money, No Parts, No Deal! / You're A Slave?

rulings: (7-side) When LS chooses to lose 2 Force, this is not a cost, so it can be reduced (e.g. Honor The Jedi or It Could Be Worse may reduce the loss).
(7-side) A card that cannot deploy during the deploy phase (such as Disarmed or Fear Is My Ally) is considered a card Dark cannot deploy. Thus if Light uses 2 Force, Dark loses 2 Force and the card.

front.gametext: If opponent just deployed a Rebel to a Jabba's Palace site, (and you have no Imperials at a Jabba's Palace site), return Rebel to opponent's hand. Any Force used to deploy that Rebel remains used, and Rebel may not be deployed for the remainder of the turn.
front.lore: Jabba's Gamorrean guards keep a watchful eye for unwelcome guests.
front.title: None Shall Pass

rulings: Does not work if (for example) Mara Jade, The Emperor's Hand at a Jabba's Palace site.
If (for example) Luke is returned to hand, Light may not deploy any Luke persona card again that turn.

front.gametext: Non-pilot characters aboard starships are forfeit -4. Whenever a player's starship is 'hit', that player loses 1 Force (2 if starship was hit by Droid Starfighter Laser Cannons). At systems where you have only [Trade Federation] starships, all of those starships are immune to attrition < 4. At sites related to a system you occupy, your battle destinies may not be canceled by opponent.
front.title: •Nothing Can Get Through Our Shield

front.gametext: Your destroyer droids and battle droids are each forfeit +1 at same and related sites. While aboard Blockade Flagship, opponent's Jedi may not move or deploy to Bridge, and your destroyer droids are destiny +3 if drawn for battle destiny.
front.lore: Commanding Viceroy of the Trade Federation forces assigned to the blockade of Naboo. Takes for his own actions. Neimoidian leader.
front.title: •Nute Gunray

front.gametext: During battle, may cancel game text of a Republic character with ability with ability < 4 present. If with your Republic character (or character with 'Trade Federation' in lore), may add one battle destiny. Immune to attrition < 3.
front.lore: Commanding Viceroy of the Trade Federation forces assigned to the blockade of Naboo. Takes for his own actions. Neimoidian leader.
front.title: •Nute Gunray (V)

front.gametext: Your [Presence] droids and AATs are destiny +1 if drawn for battle or weapon destiny. Once per turn, may take Take Them Away into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Immune to attrition < X, where X = twice the number of [Presence] droids present.
front.lore: Neimoidian leader. Viceroy to the Trade Federation, but primarily under the influence of Darth Sidious. Ordered to take control of Naboo, and force the Queen to sign a treaty.
front.title: •Nute Gunray, Neimoidian Viceroy

front.gametext: Your [Presence] droids and AATs are destiny +1 if drawn for battle or weapon destiny. Once per turn, may take Take Them Away into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Immune to attrition < X, where X = twice the number of [Presence] droids present.
front.lore: Neimoidian leader. Viceroy to the Trade Federation, but primarily under the influence of Darth Sidious. Ordered to take control of Naboo, and force the Queen to sign a treaty.
front.title: •Nute Gunray, Neimoidian Viceroy (AI)

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. May deploy as a 'react' to a Jabba's Palace site or aboard a vehicle at a Tatooine site. Power +3 when defending a battle at a Jabba's Palace site.
front.lore: Kajain'sa'Nikto. Fiercely loyal to Jabba. Stands guard over the sail barge during the Hutt's many trips to Mos Eisley.
front.title: •Nysad

front.gametext: Deploy on a site. Adds 1 to the total weapon destiny of each of your automated weapons at same and adjacent sites. During battle, may add the power of one of your characters at an adjacent site you control to your total.
front.lore: Remote surveillance viewers with droid controllers supplement security. Can activate alarms and automated weapons when needed, bringing help to endangered locations.
front.title: Observation Holocam

rulings: A character at an adjacent site using this device to add power to a battle does not otherwise participate in the battle, and is not eligible to be forfeited.
An Imperial Trooper Guard at an adjacent site would not be defending in the battle and thus would not have +4 power to add from his game text.

front.gametext: May deploy with a pilot as a 'react' to any asteroid sector or cloud sector. May add one pilot. OS-72-10 deploys -2 aboard.
front.lore: Recalled to defend second Death Star during construction. Stationed aboard Thunderflare.
front.title: •Obsidian 10

pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!

front.gametext: Deploy -1 and power +3 at any cloud sector. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 2.
front.lore: TIE fighter modified for upper atmosphere maneuvers. Pilot nicknamed 'Winged Gundark' due to the number of kills earned in high-altitude battles.
front.title: •Obsidian 7

front.gametext: Deploy -1 and power +3 at any cloud sector. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.
front.lore: Modified TIE fighter. Used most often to pursue raiders attempting to take refuge in the upper atmosphere of nearby planets. Pilot previously stationed aboard Devastator.
front.title: •Obsidian 8

front.gametext: Deploy -1 at any cloud sector. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2 and adds 2 to power. Power +2 at non-unique cloud sectors. Boosted TIE Cannon may deploy aboard and fires free aboard.
front.lore: Modified TIE fighter. Specifically adapted for atmospheric engagement. Some are fitted with high-output solar panels to support improved weaponry.
front.title: •••Obsidian Squadron TIE

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When at a Death Star site, Imperial starships may move to the Death Star system as a 'react.'
front.lore: This Imperial Intelligence leader has a proven track record for predicting Rebel fleet movements. His coordination of starship maneuvers has saved many vulnerable bases.
front.title: •Officer Evax

cancels: An attempt by opponent to target your droid to be stolen, 'hit' or lost
combo: Self-Destruct Mechanism - Retarget a weapon to your droid, then cancel the targeting entirely.

front.gametext: Cancel an attempt by opponent to target your droid to be stolen, 'hit' or lost. Droid is protected from all such attempts for remainder of turn. OR Switch OFF any binary droid for remainder of turn.
front.lore: Mindless philosophy for an overweight glob of grease.
front.title: Oh, Switch Off

rulings: May even cancel the firing of a weapon that was retargeted to the droid by Self-Destruct Mechanism.
If canceling an attempt to fire a weapon at a droid, play during the response step (before weapon destiny is drawn).
The phrase 'Droid is protected' means that further attempts are not allowed (they are prevented, not canceled).

combo: Ominous Rumors + Security Precautions
Ominous Rumors + Colonel Dyer
Ominous Rumors + Endor: Bunker + Perimeter Patrol

front.gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on Endor system if opponent controls no Endor sites. Your Force drains are +2 at up to X other battleground systems, where X = number of Endor sites you occupy. Effect canceled if opponent controls three Endor sites. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Rumors of a new 'technological terror' filled the galaxy with dread.
front.title: •Ominous Rumors

front.gametext: Shuffle any player's Reserve Deck or Lost Pile or Used Pile.
front.lore: Difficult-to-play instrument which enhances music. Tech Mo'r plays one for Figrin D'an and the Modal Nodes in the Mos Eisley Cantina.
front.title: Ommni Box

front.gametext: USED: Shuffle any player's Reserve Deck or Lost Pile.  LOST: If It Could Be Worse was just played, it is canceled and you may use X Force to raise damage against opponent by X amount. OR If opponent just lost Force from a battle, play to increase loss by 1 Force.
front.title: Ommni Box & It's Worse

front.gametext: Target an opponent's character at Galactic Senate if you have a senator there with a matching agenda. For remainder of turn: your senator's politics is increased by target's current politics, and target's politics is then reduced to zero.
front.lore: A political agenda is no use without supporters. And in the world of politics, left and right often meet in the middle.
front.title: •On The Payroll Of The Trade Federation

combo: Bog-wing Bog-wing Mynock Mynock Nudj One-Arm Scurrier Sleen Vine Snake Vine Snake

front.gametext: Habitat: Hoth sites. Deploys only to Wampa Cave. For remainder of game, all wampas are selective creatures.
front.lore: When a wampa is wounded, the other members of its pack band together to repel the threat.
front.title: •One-Arm

front.gametext: May deploy -2 with a pilot as a 'react' to same location as any Imperial-class Star Destroyer. May add 1 pilot. Any starship cannon may deploy aboard. Immune to attrition < 4 when Jendon piloting.
front.lore: Designed to emulate Rebel starfighter advantages. Production began shortly before the Battle of Endor. Armed with laser cannons, ion cannons and missile launchers.
front.title: •Onyx 1

pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!

front.gametext: Deploys for free to any mobile system. May deploy with a pilot as a 'react'. May add 1 pilot. Any starship cannon may deploy aboard. Immune to attrition < 4 when Yorr piloting.
front.lore: Part of limited production run of TIE defenders. Testing of the prototype defender indicated the need for a more powerful hyperdrive, which was added for this production model.
front.title: •Onyx 2

pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!

front.gametext: May deploy as a 'react'. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. When deployed (except as a 'react'), may play a Defensive Shield from under your Starting Effect (as if from hand).
front.lore: Part of limited production run of TIE defenders. Testing of the prototype defender indicated the need for a more powerful hyperdrive, which was added for this production model.
front.title: •Onyx 2 (V)

cancels: Captures all Rebels transported by Nabrun Leids

front.gametext: If Nabrun Leids just completed a transport, use 2 Force. Nabrun is lost and all Rebels transported are captured. (Immune to Sense.) OR Prevent a just-deployed smuggler from moving this turn. OR Cancel a Kessel Run.
front.lore: Greedo cheskopokuta klees ruya Solo. Hoko yanee boopa gush Cantina. Cheeco wa Solo's anye nyuma Greedo vakee. Jabba kul steeka et en anpaw.
front.title: Oo-ta Goo-ta, Solo?

rulings: For each Rebel transported, Dark chooses a capture option: Seize with an eligible escort at the destination site, imprison there (if the destination site happens to be a prison), or escape (Rebel goes to Light's Used Pile).

front.gametext: USED: Cancel Nabrun Leids (Immune to Sense) OR Use 1 Force to take a Rodian (or a non-unique alien of your Rep's species) into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.  LOST: During your move phase, 'break cover' of an Undercover spy.
front.lore: Greedo cheskopokuta klees ruya Solo. Hoko yanee boopa gush Cantina. Cheeco wa Solo's anye nyuma Greedo vakee. Jabba kul steeka et en anpaw.
front.title: Oo-ta Goo-ta, Solo? (V)

combo: OOM-9 + Daultay Dofine

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. May add or subtract one from a just drawn Energy Shell weapon destiny draw here. While at Battle Plains, twice per game may take Open Fire! or Cease Fire! into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Officer battle droid who acted as a unit leader in the attack against the Gungans. Required advice from the Droid Control Ship in order to defeat the Gungan energy shield.
front.title: •OOM-9

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Cancels Sando Aqua Monster. While no card here, may place an opponent's just-drawn battle destiny face-up here. If opponent just drew battle destiny with the same card title as card here, place both cards in opponent's Lost Pile. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: With a vicious array of pointed teeth, the opee sea killer is a fearsome hunter. When outmatched in size, it uses small crevices to avoid bigger predators.
front.title: •Opee Sea Killer

front.gametext: Deploy on your AAT. Once during your control phase may use 3 Force to fire your AAT Laser Cannon on this AAT for free.
front.lore: When given the attack coordinates, AAT weaponry can be programmed to track and fire automatically for maximum destruction.
front.title: •Open Fire!

combo: Operational As Planned + Janus Greejatus

front.gametext: USED: Place one card from hand on top of Force Pile.  STARTING: If Endor system on table, take Death Star II system, Jerjerrod and any Effect into hand from Reserve Deck. When you draw your starting hand, draw only six more cards. Place Interrupt in Lost Pile.
front.lore: 'We shall double our efforts.'
front.title: •Operational As Planned

front.gametext: USED: Use 1 Force to deploy Krennic or a Jedha location from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.  STARTING: If Death Star on table, deploy Superlaser and up to two Effects that deploy on table and are always immune to Alter. Place this Interrupt in hand.
front.lore: 'We shall double our efforts.'
front.title: •Operational As Planned (V)

front.gametext: Plays on table. Your Immediate Effects may play for free. Whenever opponent cancels your card with Sense or Alter, place that canceled card in Used Pile.
front.lore: The Imperial fleet keeps a tight grip on the systems under its control. Abuses and excesses by local citizens are not tolerated.
front.title: •Oppressive Enforcement

combo: Opressive Enforcement + Twi'lek Advisor
Opressive Enforcement + There'll Be Hell To Pay + Tentacle
Opressive Enforcement + Dreadnaughts Destiny 4 support cards for a TIE deck.

front.gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Your Imperial capital starships are each destiny +1. Your Immediate Effects may deploy for free. Whenever opponent cancels your card with Sense or Alter, place that canceled card in Used Pile. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: The Imperial fleet keeps a tight grip on the systems under its control. Abuses and excesses by local citizens are not tolerated.
front.title: •Oppressive Enforcement

front.gametext: Dark:  Your Bounty Hunters are deploy -2 here.  Light:  (none)
front.title: •Ord Mantell

front.gametext: While at an Ord Mantell site: adds 1 to your Force drains there, is power +1 (or +2 if your bounty hunter is on Ord Mantell) and, once during each of your deploy phases, may deploy one site to Ord Mantell from Reserve Deck- reshuffle.
front.lore: Many Aqualish draft and maintain bounty hunting contracts for the Empire, the Hutts or anyone with credits. Fight against the Alliance to avoid losing their best customer.
front.title: Ord Mantell Operative

front.gametext: Deploy on any Yavin 4 site. Target one Imperial. When Imperial reaches target site, 'steal' necklace. Whenever necklace is present during Force drain: add 1 to Force drain and may then pass (for free) to an adjacent site you control (if any), and so on.
front.lore: Necklace worn by Princess Leia during the awards ceremony after the Battle of Yavin. A powerful artifact in the Alderaanian royal family for dozens of generations.
front.title: •Organa's Ceremonial Necklace

rulings: The term 'steal' on this Utinni Effect is simply flavor text meaning to place the Necklace card on the target Imperial. Stealing rules do not apply.
In order to pass Organa's Ceremonial Necklace to an adjacent site you control, you must immediately re-target (place it on) another one of your Imperials there.

canceledBy: Game text is canceled by Freon Drevan

front.gametext: Agendas: taxation, wealth. While in a senate majority, once per turn may take your just drawn battle destiny into hand. During opponent's deploy phase, may use X Force to place Taa in your Used Pile. (X = cards in opponent's Force Pile.)
front.lore: Obese Rutian Twi'lek senator. Once a tax collector, he has used his connections and political power to fuel a myriad of devious plots for whomever can make him the highest offer.
front.title: •Orn Free Taa

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. Functions as a leader if present with another Gamorrean. While at Audience Chamber, all your other Gamorreans are forfeit +2.
front.lore: Gamorrean in charge of the Gamorreans at Jabba's palace. Posted to stand guard at the entrance cavern. Assigned by Jabba to keep an eye on Tessek.
front.title: •Ortugg

front.gametext: While at a Jabba's Palace site, your other Gamorreans are deploy -1 and forfeit +3. Permanent weapon is •Ortugg's Ax (may target a character or creature for free; draw destiny; target hit, and its forfeit = 0, if destiny +1 > defense value).
front.lore: Gamorrean in charge of the Gamorreans at Jabba's palace. Posted to stand guard at the entrance cavern. Assigned by Jabba to keep an eye on Tessek.
front.title: •Ortugg (V)

front.gametext: Deploy -1 and power +3 at a cloud sector. Permanent pilot is •OS-72-1, who provides ability of 2, adds 2 to power and, at a cloud sector, may draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.
front.lore: Lead starfighter of Obsidian Squadron. Flown by Cive Rashon. Call sign 'Howlrunner.' She served in an elite TIE squadron aboard the Star Destroyer Avenger.
front.title: •OS-72-1 In Obsidian 1

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots (3 if any TIE). When piloting a TIE at a cloud sector, adds one battle destiny and makes that TIE immune to attrition < 4 (< 6 if Obsidian 10).
front.lore: Pilot of Obsidian 10. Has served aboard the Conquest, the Thunderflare and the Executor. Not interested in advancing his rank as it would remove him from the pilot's seat.
front.title: •OS-72-10

front.gametext: Deploy -1 and power +3 at a cloud sector. Permanent pilot is •OS-72-2, who provides ability of 2, adds 2 to power and, at a cloud sector, may draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.
front.lore: Piloted by Dodson Makraven, wingman of Cive Rashon. Experienced TIE pilot with many kills in atmospheric combat. Nicknamed 'Night Beast' for his many curfew violations.
front.title: •OS-72-2 In Obsidian 2

cancels: An attempt by opponent to move away from a battle

front.gametext: Deploy on table. If no senator here, you may place a senator here from hand to add 3 to any battle destiny just drawn. If a blockade agenda here, during your turn you may cancel a 'react' or an attempt by opponent to move away from a battle.
front.lore: Until it could be proven otherwise, the Trade Federation maintained that they were pursuing a legal means of protesting the taxation of outlying trade routes.
front.title: •Our Blockade Is Perfectly Legal

combo: Our First Catch Of The Day + Tractor Beam + In Range

front.gametext: Add 2 to a tractor beam destiny draw. OR Cancel The First Transport Is Away! or Hyper Escape.
front.lore: 'Sir, Rebel ships are coming into our sector.'
front.title: Our First Catch Of The Day

front.gametext: Deploy -1 to your [Independent Starship] starship. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting a [Independent Starship] starship, instead adds 3 to power and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. Suspends Asteroid Sanctuary at related sector.
front.lore: Smugglers and scouts employed by the ISB. Search the far reaches of the galaxy for Rebel activity and habitable worlds. Know all the smugglers' best hiding places.
front.title: Outer Rim Scout

front.gametext: During a battle, if you have weapons at at least 2 sites adjacent to that battle, add 3 to your total power and add one battle destiny. OR For remainder of turn, your biker scout at an exterior site is power +1 and adds 1 to each of that character's weapon destiny draws.
front.lore: Commander Igar's defense of Endor called for the use of speeder bikes to harass any attacking Rebels.
front.title: •Outflank

canceledBy: Hear Me Baby Hold Together (V) helps against a 0

front.gametext: Target any weapon (except a Gaderffii Stick or any Ewok weapon). Draw destiny. Weapon lost if destiny < weapon's destiny number. If destiny = 0, the character or starship carrying weapon is also lost.
front.lore: Weapons like lightsabers, turbolasers and blasters run on powerful energy cells or generators. Occasionally, these cells overheat causing the weapon to unexpectedly explode.
front.title: Overload

rulings: May even target weapons not carried by a character or starship (such as a vehicle weapon, artillery weapon, automated weapon, etc).
May target a card with a permanent weapon, but only has a result if the destiny draw = 0 (character or starship with the permanent weapon is lost); otherwise nothing happens.

combo: Overseeing It Personally + Emperor Palpatine or The Emperor

front.gametext: Deploy on Emperor. While at a battleground planet site you control, at each related site where an Imperial is present, your Force drains are +1.
front.lore: Though reluctant to leave Coruscant. Emperor Palpatine occasionally finds it necessary to personally put lagging Imperial operations back on schedule.
front.title: •Overseeing It Personally

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

combo: Overseeing It Personally + Emperor Palpatine or The Emperor

front.gametext: Deploy on your leader. Opponent may not cancel or reduce Force drains at same battleground. If on Emperor, may place Effect in Lost Pile to retrieve an Imperial leader.
front.lore: Though reluctant to leave Coruscant. Emperor Palpatine occasionally finds it necessary to personally put lagging Imperial operations back on schedule.
front.title: •Overseeing It Personally (V)

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

front.gametext: During your deploy phase, target a system where your total power is more than double opponent's total power and opponent has no Jedi or starship weapon. Place all opponent's starships there (and cards on them) in owner's Used Pile.
front.lore: When the Empire amasses its fleet, the only option for the Alliance is retreat.
front.title: Overwhelmed

rulings: Cannot be played where opponent has no power total (no active cards with power).
If successfully played, sends away inactive targets such as a starship utilizing Landing Claw.

The player playing Overwhelmed chooses the order to send cards to Used Pile, including the 'cards on them' such as devices. However, if a card is selected to go to Used Pile while there are still other cards on it, place the selected card and the cards on it in owners' Used Pile(s) simultaneously (per Leaves Table rules, the owner of that group of cards then determines the order).

combo: OWO-1 With Backup + Daultay Dofine

front.gametext: Requires +2 Force to use Landspeed. Power +1 for each of opponent's Jedi present. While with a battledroid at a site, draws two battle destiny if unable to otherwise. Opponent's Force drains are -1 at adjacent sites.
front.lore: Trade Federation battle droid leader assigned to take a squad and destroy what was left of the Jedi ambassadors. His mission went unaccomplished.
front.title: •OWO-1 With Backup

combo: P-59 + Daultay Dofine

front.gametext: Permanent weapon is Twin Cannons (may target a character or vehicle for free; draw destiny; if destiny +1 > defense value, target hit and opponent loses 2 Force). Draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise. Immune to attrition < 4.
front.lore: Trade Federation destroyer droid squad leader. Charged with removing the threat posed by Qui-Gon Jinn and Obi-Wan Kenobi. Found the Jedi hard to kill, but forced their retreat.
front.title: •P-59

rulings: 'Draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise' even works if P-59 is the passenger of any vehicle or starship (and even if the vehicle or starship is unpiloted).

combo: P-60 + Daultay Dofine

front.gametext: Permanent weapon is Twin Cannons (may target a character or vehicle for free; draw destiny; if destiny +2 > defense value, target hit and opponent loses 1 Force). While with a destroyer droid at a site, adds one battle destiny.
front.lore: Trade Federation droideka led by unit commander P-59. Assisted in the attempt to keep the Jedi ambassadors from breaching the battleship's command center.
front.title: •P-60

front.gametext: Agendas: ambition, taxation. While in a senate majority, opponent's non-unique starships and non-unique vehicles are each deploy +2 and power -1. Argente is politics +X, where X = number of opponent's senators at same site.
front.lore: A senator known for his ability to deflect blame. It is rumored that Argente receives kickbacks from a few corporations to thwart other companies' developments.
front.title: •Passel Argente

front.gametext: Power +1 at Coruscant or Bespin. May add 1 driver and 1 passenger. May deploy or move as a 'react.' At cloud sectors, may move and be targeted by weapons like a starfighter.
front.lore: Small, enclosed patrol fighter used on many worlds to help maintain order. A cheaper alternative to the Bespin Motors cloud car.
front.title: Patrol Craft

combo: Perimeter Patrol + Closed Door
Perimeter Patrol + Closed Door + Bad Feeling Have I + Navy Trooper Fensom

front.gametext: Deploy on Bunker. While you control Bunker, each time opponent deploys a vehicle, starship or Rebel to an Endor site (except Rebel Landing Site), that card cannot move or battle for remainder of turn and opponent must lose 1 Force. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Heavy Imperial patrols on Endor forced the Rebels to deploy covertly. The required stealth measures created many complications.
front.title: •Perimeter Patrol

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

front.gametext: Cause one Rebel Trooper to be immediately lost. OR If a Dark Jedi is present at a battle you have just won, use 1 Force to attempt to choke any opposing character present. Draw destiny. If destiny > target's ability, target is lost.
front.lore: Darth Vader often used physical means of 'persuasion' to get information. Captain Antilles of Tantive IV chose to die rather than reveal the location of the stolen Death Star plans.
front.title: Physical Choke

front.gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Opponent may not 'react' away from a battle where you have a blaster present. Also, if you have a blaster present when opponent cancels a battle, draw destiny, opponent loses Force equal to destiny draw. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Heavy blaster fire hampered Han's attempts to open the Back Door to the Endor control bunker.
front.title: •Pinned Down

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points
rulings: Works with permanent weapon blasters (e.g. Boba Fett With Blaster Rifle).

front.gametext: Use 3 Force to reveal opponent's hand. All cards opponent has 3 or more of in hand are lost. OR Use 1 Force to 'repair' your Podracer. OR Target a Podracer. Draw destiny. If destiny > Podracer's destiny number, target Podracer is 'damaged.'
front.lore: Pit droids are used by Podracer pilots to assist in the maintenance of their racer. While a high standard is usually maintained, sometimes things can get out of hand.
front.title: •Pit Crews

front.gametext: While at Podracer Bay, once during each of your control phases may lose 1 Force to target your Podracer. Place target's top race destiny in Lost Pile, and draw one race destiny. During any control phase may use 1 Force to 'repair' your Podracer.
front.lore: Manufactured by Serv-O-Droid on Cyrillia. Collapses into a compact form when hit on the nose.
front.title: Pit Droid

front.gametext: If your scout is battling opponent's scout, spy or operative, add one battle destiny. OR If you have a spy or scout at Bunker or any prison, place out of play one captured spy of ability < 3 or captured operative there. Retrieve Force equal to double that captive's forfeit.
front.lore: The Emperor's defense of the forest moon of Endor appeared to work with devastating effectiveness.
front.title: •Pitiful Little Band

cancels: Asteroid Sanctuary unless present with opponent's starship

front.gametext: Deploy on table. You may add up to 5 to destiny of each TIE Bomber drawn for weapon or battle destiny. You may add 1 to Proton Bomb weapon destiny draws. Asteroid Sanctuary is canceled unless present with opponent's starship. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: The Empire crushes resistance with massive orbital bombardment. The coordinated attack of a TIE bomber wing reduces a planet's surface to rubble.
front.title: •Planetary Subjugation

front.gametext: USED: If you just verified opponent's Reserve Deck, search that Reserve Deck and place one Interrupt found there out of play.  LOST: Lose 1 Force to remove a race destiny (random selection) from any Podracer and place it in owner's hand.
front.lore: Podracing demands constant attention to many variables as well as all opponents. Failure to do so can often result in reduced performance.
front.title: •Podracer Collision

combo: Point Man + Boring Conversation Anyway + Tentacle

front.gametext: Cancel Demotion, Restricted Deployment, Commence Recharging, Logistical Delay, They're On Dantooine, Asteroid Sanctuary, Scramble, Order To Engage, No Disintegrations, Asteroids Do Not Concern Me, Report To Lord Vader or What Is Thy Bidding, My Master?
front.lore: In a military situation, on a regional or galactic scale, commands sometimes get misinterpreted. A local commander giving orders is far more reliable.
front.title: Point Man

cancels: Keep Your Eyes Open (in battle at a site)
Keep Your Eyes Open (V) (in a battle at a site)

front.gametext: USED: Move a trooper as a 'react' to a battle where you have a leader. OR During any draw phase, place a card from hand under your Used Pile to take any one card into hand from Force Pile; reshuffle.  LOST: During a battle at a site, cancel Keep Your Eyes Open.
front.lore: In a military situation, on a regional or galactic scale, commands sometimes get misinterpreted. A local commander giving orders is far more reliable.
front.title: Point Man (V)

combo: Ponda Boba + Dr. Evazan + Wuher + Cantina + Stunning Leader
Ponda Boba + Hound's Tooth + Moment Of Triumph

front.gametext: Power +3 when battling at same site as Dr. Evazan, unless opponent has a lightsaber present. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots.
front.lore: A male Quara (or fingered Aqualish). Thug, smuggler and partner of Dr. Evazan. Has a poor quality cybernetic arm replacement.
front.title: •Ponda Baba

cards.conceptBy: (Original concept by Mike Raveling - Minnesota States 2008)

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots.  At same site, non-Jedi Luke may not swing a lightsaber at aliens (or return aliens to hand using his game text). During battle, if with a smuggler, may add one destiny to attrition or make that smuggler forfeit = 0.
front.lore: A male Quara (or fingered Aqualish). Thug, smuggler and partner of Dr. Evazan. Has a poor quality cybernetic arm replacement.
front.title: •Ponda Baba (V)

rulings: The 'during battle' text is used during the weapons segment. If adding a destiny to attrition, this schedules it to be drawn in the power segment (and will occur even if the conditions are no longer met later).
The 'may not return aliens to hand' text refers to Master Luke.

front.gametext: Deploy on your smuggler or use 2 Force to deploy on your warrior. May deploy on Ponda Baba as a 'react.' May target a character or creature using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Target hit, and forfeit = 0, if destiny +1 > defense value.
front.lore: High-powered, short-barreled blaster. Modified Imperial blaster pistol. Kept concealed by the Aqualish mercenary.
front.title: •Ponda Baba's Hold-out Blaster

front.gametext: Deploy on any warrior. When that warrior fires a blaster rifle or artillery weapon, adds 1 to each of that weapon's destiny draws. Also, may add 1 to power of one droid present.
front.lore: Larger assault weapons require troops to carry their own power sources. Both light and efficient, these units produce ample power for most combat needs.
front.title: Portable Fusion Generator

front.gametext: When driving a vehicle, that vehicle is power +3 and moves for free. While at Audience Chamber, all your other Skrillings are power +2 and forfeit +1.
front.lore: Skrilling smuggler. Supplied Jabba's henchmen with weapons when he was Hermi Odle's predecessor. An excellent driver.
front.title: •Pote Snitkin

front.gametext: While driving a vehicle, adds one battle destiny and your total ability here may not be reduced. At same and related sites, Skrillings are power and forfeit +2, and, once per game, your just-lost transport vehicle may be 'recycled' (place in Used Pile).
front.lore: Skrilling smuggler. Supplied Jabba's henchmen with weapons when he was Hermi Odle's predecessor. An excellent driver.
front.title: •Pote Snitkin (V)

rulings: To use his 'recycled' text, the just-lost transport vehicle must have been lost from same or related site.
Cannot 'recycle' a vehicle he is aboard, unless something permits Pote to 'jump off' (e.g. Skiff). Otherwise, vehicle and Pote are lost simultaneously so Pote cannot save it.

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Once during each of your turns, may deploy one Boelo, Bib, Ephant Mon, Jabba's Sail Barge, Jabba's Space Cruiser, or Hutt Influence from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Also, your aliens aboard Jabba's Sail Barge are immune to attrition < 6. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Jabba runs his organization out of a palace built around a B'omarr monastery. His fortress near the border of the western Dune Sea is safe from enemies in Mos Eisley.
front.title: •Power Of The Hutt

front.gametext: During a battle, target opponent's character or vehicle present with two (or more) of your weapons. Add all weapon destiny draws together. Apply that total separately for each weapon in an order of your choosing.
front.lore: 'Only Imperial stormtroopers are so precise.'
front.title: Precise Attack

front.gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on table. Any card which is 'hit' may not be used to satisfy attrition. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: 'Sir, we just lost the main rear deflector shield. One more direct hit on the back quarter and we're done for!'
front.title: Precision Targeting

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Your Force drains at Hoth sites may not be canceled. Once per turn, if you just deployed an AT-AT to a Hoth site, you may deploy (at -2) a Star Destroyer to the Hoth system (or vice versa) from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Ruthless and well-equipped for both air and ground assault, Vader's feared Death Squadron came to the icy Rebel Base with total domination in mind.
front.title: •Prepare For A Surface Attack

pulls: A Star Destroyer to the Hoth system if an AT-AT was just deployed to a Hoth site (or vice versa)

front.gametext: Deploy on table. AT-AT Cannons deploy -1, fire for free, and add 1 to armor. During your control phase, may take a non-[Jabba's Palace] vehicle weapon (without 'lost' in game text), [Hoth] device, or [Hoth] Epic Event into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Ruthless and well-equipped for both air and ground assault, Vader's feared Death Squadron came to the icy Rebel Base with total domination in mind.
front.title: •Prepare For A Surface Attack (V)

combo: Prepare the Chamber + Carbonite Chamber Console + 3 Ugnaughts + Carbon Freezing

front.gametext: USED: Add 2 to Carbon Freezing destiny.  LOST: If one of your Ugnaughts is defending in a battle, add one battle destiny.
front.lore: Coolant emitted by the TCF32 Carbonite Encasement Apparatus is rumored to have a mildly euphoric effect on Ugnaughts. Individuals on TCF32 duty are regarded with envy.
front.title: •Prepare The Chamber

front.gametext: USED: Add 1 to your battle destiny just drawn.  STARTING: Deploy up to three Effects if each of them deploys for free, is always immune to Alter and has 'deploy on table' (or 'deploy on your side of table') in its game text. Place Interrupt in Lost Pile.
front.lore: Since the debacle at Yavin, the Emperor places a premium on the security of his costly war machine.
front.title: •Prepared Defenses

rulings: The Effects must be unconditionally immune to Alter according to their own game text (ignore other cards).
May deploy Mobilization Points even if Don't Do That Again is on table.
Deploy and resolve each Effect one at a time.
May deploy Naboo Occupation, which is immediately lost, then deploy No Escape to take it into hand. In this case Dark's starting hand will have 1 more card than usual.

combo: Presence Of The Force + Endor Shield (V) + Endor Three Force icons for you, none for the Light Side. Opportunity to drain for three.

front.gametext: Deploy on any location to add one [Dark Side Force] and one [Light Side Force].
front.lore: A location is affected by the history of the events which occur there. The Force '...binds the galaxy together' and has an ebb and flow.
front.title: ••Presence Of The Force

front.gametext: If opponent just lost a starship in a battle you won, deploy on your participating starfighter. Once during each of opponent's move phases, opponent loses 1 Force (2 if starfighter is a TIE/ln). Also, that starfighter is power +2. (Immune to Control.)
front.lore: Imperial starships that perform with distinction are highly publicized in an attempt to make the pilots look like heroes to the citizens of the Empire.
front.title: •Pride Of The Empire

front.gametext: If you just deployed a pilot aboard a Black Squadron TIE, deploy on that pilot; pilot's game text may not be canceled. During your turn, may take a Black Squadron pilot into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. If pilot just won a battle, retrieve a Black Squadron pilot.
front.lore: Imperial starships that perform with distinction are highly publicized in an attempt to make the pilots look like heroes to the citizens of the Empire.
front.title: •Pride Of The Empire (V)

combo: Wounded Warrior - Prevent battle destiny draws by getting opponent under 6 ability.

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When in battle at a site, draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise and total ability of 6 or more required for opponent to draw battle destiny here. Immune to attrition < 5 when Vader not here.
front.lore: Falleen gangster and leader. Black Sun agent. Dark Prince of the Black Sun crime syndicate. Fortifies his personal defenses with information gathered by his agents.
front.title: •Prince Xizor

rulings: Passengers aboard starships or enclosed vehicles do not count towards the 6 ability requirement. If the requirement is not met, Light does not get any battle destiny draws (even if they have multiple battle destiny adders such as Captain Han Solo, Life Debt, etc). However, 'draws if unable to otherwise' still works without 6 ability.

front.gametext: Deploy on your Probe Droid. Adds 2 to X for that droid. OR Use 1 Force to deploy on one of your other droids. When at a site you control, once during each of your control phases, you may peek at one card randomly selected from opponent's hand.
front.lore: A probe droid encodes and scrambles messages before using its telescoping antennae to transmit information through hyperspace.
front.title: Probe Antennae

combo: Probe Droids + Nevar Yalnal

front.gametext: Deploys only if a Star Destroyer on table. Once during each of your control phases, may peek at X cards randomly selected from opponent's hand, where X = number of [Light Side Force] icons at same site. May Force drain, initiate battle and be battled.
front.lore: Arakyd Viper probe droid. Has sensors specifically designed to detect traces of Rebel activity. Equipped with an auto-destruct mechanism. A highly durable spy droid.
front.title: Probe Droid

front.gametext: Deploy on your probe droid. May target an artillery weapon (use 5 as defense value), character or creature for free. Draw destiny. Artillery weapon lost if destiny > defense value. Character or creature hit if destiny > defense value.
front.lore: Although a probe droid's primary defense is stealth, many models can be equipped with a laser cannon to enhance the droid's combat and sabotage capabilities.
front.title: Probe Droid Laser

front.gametext: Use 2 Force to search any Lost Pile and place X non-unique cards there out of play, where X = number of Probe Droids on table. OR If your only character on a planet is a Probe Droid, your cards are deploy -1 to related sites for remainder of turn.
front.lore: Probe droids use electromagnetic, seismic, acoustic, olfactory and optical sensors. They report their findings using an omnisignal unicode.
front.title: Probe Telemetry

front.gametext: Draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. Power +2 if with opponent's smuggler or Wookiee. During your move phase, may use 1 Force to 'break cover' of opponent's Undercover spy at same site. Immune to attrition < 3.
front.lore: Spy.
front.title: •Probot

rulings: 'Draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise' even works if Probot is the passenger of any vehicle or starship (and even if the vehicle or starship is unpiloted).

combo: Program Trap + U-3PO (Yoo-Threepio)

front.gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on an opponent's droid (except R2-D2 and C- 3PO), 1 on your droid. When either player draws a destiny matching the number of characters at same site, droid 'explodes' (all characters present are lost).
front.lore: Imperial slicers embed a secret command in a droid's primary performance banks. A predetermined trigger causes a power overload, destroying the droid and anything nearby.
front.title: •Program Trap

front.gametext: Cancel Anger, Fear, Aggression when it is inserted or revealed. OR If your opponent just initiated a battle or Force drain, opponent must choose to use 2 Force, or cancel that battle or Force drain.
front.lore: 'Luke.' 'Father.' 'Son, come with me.'
front.title: •Projective Telepathy

front.gametext: If you initiate a battle where present, you must predict the winner before the battle starts. If correct, randomly retrieve one lost card. If incorrect, lose 1 Force. Immune to attrition < 3.
front.lore: Renowned female psychic. Predictor of doom. Agent for Governor Aryon of Tatooine. Tailed Jabba and his thugs to Docking Bay 94 when they confronted Han Solo.
front.title: •Prophetess

front.gametext: Deploy on a bomber: When present during a Force drain, may target a related interior site. Draw destiny. Site 'collapsed' if destiny > 4. OR May fire in a Bombing Run battle. Draw destiny. All characters, starships and vehicles with that destiny number at same site are lost.
front.lore: Proton-scattering energy warheads. Especially effective against ray and energy-shielded targets. Ineffective against particle deflector.
front.title: Proton Bombs

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot (must be a smuggler or bounty hunter) and 1 passenger. Immune to attrition < 3 if Dengar piloting. Deploy -3 when deploying with Dengar. Boosted TIE Cannon may deploy aboard.
front.lore: Old Corellian Engineering Corporation starfighter. Has outdated Class Three hyperdrive, but high sublight speed capability. Easy to maintain. Owned by Dengar.
front.title: •Punishing One

pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot. Corellians deploy -2 aboard. When deployed, may place an Admiral's Order in owner's Used Pile. While a Corellian piloting, power + 2 and immune to attrition < 3 (<5 if Dengar).
front.lore: Old Corellian Engineering Corporation starfighter. Has outdated Class Three hyperdrive, but high sublight speed capability. Easy to maintain. Owned by Dengar.
front.title: •Punishing One (V)

pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!

front.gametext: USED: Target a Rebel at a Death Star (or Executor) site. For remainder of turn, target may not use its game text and may not apply ability toward drawing battle destiny. (Immune to Sense.)  LOST: Retrieve into hand up to two cards with 'Death Star' in title.
front.lore: 'We have an emergency alert in detention block AA-twenty three.'
front.title: •Put All Sections On Alert

front.gametext: If present at a non-shielded site, your Imperials may deploy there (regardless of location deployment restrictions). When at a planet site, Tactical Support, Imperial Reinforcements and Full Scale Alert are Used Interrupts.
front.lore: Nicknamed 'squidheads.' Quarren share their watery homeworld with the Mon Calamari. Betrayed their planet to the Empire. Dwell on the past. Rarely look to the future.
front.title: Quarren

front.gametext: Deploy on a site where Maul just defeated Qui-Gon in lightsaber combat. Place Qui-Gon out of play. While Obi-Wan at this site, his lightsaber combat total is +2 and opponent loses 1 Force at the end of each of your turns. (Immune to Control.)
front.lore: While Qui-Gon spent years maintaining peace, Maul was sharpening his combat skills. Those years of training came to fruition in one fateful moment.
front.title: •Qui-Gon's End

front.gametext: Deploy on your side of table. During your draw phase, you make use 2 Force to search through your Lost Pile. Take one Hidden Weapons into hand or take any one blaster and immediately deploy it (for free).
front.lore: Boba Fett's helmet has infrared capabilities, a motion tracking system, a macrobinocular viewer, an internal comlink and a broadband antenna. He doesn't miss a thing.
front.title: Quick Reflexes

pulls: Any one blaster from Lost Pile

combo: Quietly Observing + Aurra Sing

front.gametext: Deploy on Aurra Sing. While Aurra is alone at a site, your total ability here = 0. During your move phase, may lose Effect to target an opponent's lightsaber present. Draw destiny. If destiny > 3, Aurra may 'steal' that lightsaber.
front.lore: On her assignment to kill Sharad Hett, Aurra used her patience and cunning to help track down the Jedi Master.
front.title: •Quietly Observing

rulings: If the player has at least one unique alien in hand, then searching Reserve Deck is optional.

Player may search Reserve Deck, then decide to use only cards from hand (even if Reserve Deck had valid options). As long as at least one unique alien is revealed from hand or Reserve Deck, no verification occurs.
If player searched Reserve Deck and can't complete the action, only Reserve Deck is verified.  A judge may be called to check the hand for any unique aliens.

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Aurra, Bossk, and Cad are destiny +2. Once per game, may reveal up to two unique (•) aliens from hand and/or Reserve Deck (reshuffle); for remainder of game, those cards are assassins and Black Sun agents. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: On her assignment to kill Sharad Hett, Aurra used her patience and cunning to help track down the Jedi Master.
front.title: •Quietly Observing (V)

front.gametext: Adds 2 to the power of anything he pilots. While piloting Meson Martinet, it is defense value +2. Forfeit +2 while present with Sidon. If your Rep is a pirate (or you did not deploy an Objective), Force drain +1 here.
front.lore: Gabdorin pirate.
front.title: •Quiggold

front.gametext: When aboard a capital starship, adds 1 to power and hyperspeed, and that starship is immune to attrition < 3. Too large to go aboard a starfighter.
front.lore: Typical of the old model astromechs still used on capital starships and large freighters. Has armored Mark II reactor drone shell. R1-G4 was abandoned after owner was captured.
front.title: R1-G4 (Arone-Geefour)

front.gametext: When in battle aboard your capital starship at a system or sector, adds 1 to total attrition against opponent for each of your piloted TIEs present in that battle.
front.lore: Combat communications astromech. Coordinates starfighter attack vectors. Broadcasts target acquisition data to gunnery systems.
front.title: •R2-A5 (Artoo-Ayfive)

front.gametext: While aboard any starfighter, adds 1 to power, maneuver and hyperspeed. When at a Scomp link during your draw phase, may use 1 Force to peek at top three cards of your Reserve Deck.
front.lore: R2 units are known for expertise in computer uplinking. R2-Q2 spent several decades serving with an Imperial reconnaissance fleet in the Expansion Region.
front.title: R2-Q2 (Artoo-Kyootoo)

combo: R3-T6 (Arthree-Teesix) + Deflector Shield Generators ona Star Destroyer
R3-T6 (Arthree-Teesix) + R1-G4
R3-T6 (Arthree-Teesix) + Death Star + Death Star: Central Corridor The Death Star moves at a Hyperspeed of 2.

front.gametext: While aboard your capital starship, adds 1 to power and 2 to hyperspeed, and that starship is immune to attrition < 4. While at Death Star: Central Core, hyperspeed of Death Star system = 2.
front.lore: R3 units have larger memory and more advanced circuitry than their R1 predecessors, allowing for more efficient astrogation plots. R3-T6 served on the Death Star.
front.title: •R3-T6 (Arthree-Teesix)

front.gametext: While aboard a non-creature vehicle, adds 1 to power, maneuver and landspeed. May drive transport vehicles.
front.lore: Typical multiple-use droid. Controls and repairs vehicles and computers. R4-M9 was once used by the Empire to pull data from Tantive IV's computer banks.
front.title: R4-M9 (Arfour-Emmnine)

front.gametext: While aboard any starship, adds 1 to power and maneuver. During your control phase, if aboard your starship damaged by an ion cannon, restores armor/maneuver and hyperspeed.
front.lore: Seldom used for navigation purposes, R5 units are known for their ability to perform hull maintenance and repair damage caused by ionization.
front.title: R5-A2 (Arfive-Aytoo)

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything she pilots. During a battle involving Rachalt, whenever opponent draws an Interrupt for destiny may use 2 Force to cause that Interrupt to be lost. While armed with a weapon at a site, Force drain +1 here.
front.lore: Strange female Snivvian who frequents the cantina daily. Betrayed her loved ones, who then left her on Tatooine to die. Everything she's ever cared about is now gone or dead.
front.title: •Rachalt Hyst

front.gametext: May deploy with a driver (must be Barada, Klaatu, or a non-unique alien) as a 'react'. May add 1 driver and 3 passengers. May move as a 'react'. If lost, any characters aboard may 'jump off' (disembark).
front.lore: Barada and Klaatu strip down and rebuild old skiffs to race on the Dune Sea. Jabba allows the practice to continue for now.
front.title: Racing Skiff

front.gametext: Dark:  All your troopers are destiny +1 (+2 if you control). Tactical support is used interrupt.  Light:  If you occupy, opponent's Raithal game text is canceled.
front.title: •Raithal

front.gametext: While at a Raithal site: adds 1 to your Force drains there, is power +1 (or +2 if your gambler or tax collector is on Raithal) and, once during each of your deploy phases, may deploy one site to Raithal from Reserve Deck- reshuffle.
front.lore: Opportunists work with corrupt governments and Raithal casino operators. Keep the Empire informed of local Alliance activity, for a price.
front.title: Raithal Operative

front.gametext: Dark:  Devastator is power +1 here and may move to or from here for free.  Light:  Tantive IV is power +1 here.
front.title: •Ralltiir

back.gametext: Ralltiir Operations:Deploy Ralltiir system.{While} this side up, once during each of your deploy phases, may deploy from Reserve Deck to Ralltiir one site or non-unique Imperial; reshuffle. At Ralltiir locations, each Rebel is deploy +2.{Flip} this card if Imperials control at least three Ralltiir sites and opponent controls no Ralltiir locations.{Place} out of play if Ralltiir is 'blown away.'In The Hands Of The Empire:{While} this side up, opponent's Force drains are -1. At Ralltiir locations, each Rebel is deploy +2. At all locations, add X to your total battle destiny, where X = number of Ralltiir locations your Imperials occupy. Once during each of your control phases, you may use 2 Force to take any one card into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.{Flip} this card if opponent controls at least two Ralltiir locations.{Place} out of play if Ralltiir is 'blown away.
back.title: Ralltiir Operations / In The Hands Of The Empire

front.gametext: Ralltiir Operations:Deploy Ralltiir system.{While} this side up, once during each of your deploy phases, may deploy from Reserve Deck to Ralltiir one site or non-unique Imperial; reshuffle. At Ralltiir locations, each Rebel is deploy +2.{Flip} this card if Imperials control at least three Ralltiir sites and opponent controls no Ralltiir locations.{Place} out of play if Ralltiir is 'blown away.'In The Hands Of The Empire:{While} this side up, opponent's Force drains are -1.
