Once during each of your control phases, you may use 2 Force to take any one card into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.{Flip} this card if opponent controls at least two Ralltiir locations.{Place} out of play if Ralltiir is 'blown away.
front.title: Ralltiir Operations / In The Hands Of The Empire

underlyingCardFor: Ralltiir Operations / In The Hands Of The Empire (V)

front.gametext: * Ferocity = 8 + destiny. Habitat: Rancor Pit and exterior planet sites. Deploys only to the rancor pit or to where Malakili is the only character. Moves towards another Rancor whenever possible.
front.lore: Indigenous to Dathomir, but found on several dozen worlds throughout the galaxy. Vicious predator. Sometimes kept as pets by eccentrics and crime lords.
front.title: Rancor

front.gametext: Where present, adds X to Force opponent must use to initiate battle, where X = number of musicians present. May target one non-droid character resent in battle. Draw destiny. If destiny > defense value, target is power = 0 this battle.
front.lore: Shawda Ubb musician from Manpha. Plays growdi. Real name Rapotwanalantonee. When cornered in a fight, he can spit a paralyzing poison.
front.title: •Rappertunie

front.gametext: Your characters may move from here using their landspeed for free. During your control phase, may place Vaca in Used Pile to take Lana Dobreed into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Coruscant taxi driver who barely makes enough money to get by. Will try any trick in the book to get an extra credit from his customer.
front.title: •Rayno Vaca

front.gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your side of table. During your control phase, you may return any cards from your hand to the top of your Used Pile.
front.lore: The Death Star has many terminals coupled to the main reactor for power distribution throughout the immense space station.
front.title: Reactor Terminal

front.gametext: Deploy on a Rebel Base system if you occupy at least two related battleground sites. During each of your control phases, opponent loses 1 Force for each related battleground sit you occupy. Canceled if opponent controls this system. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: 'General, prepare your troops for a surface attack.'
front.title: •Rebel Base Occupation

front.gametext: Thrice per battle at same site, if you just drew a battle destiny of 3, may use 3 Force to add 3 to that destiny.
front.lore: Gran convicted of murder. Exiled from his homeworld. Smuggler and bounty hunter. Slowly going insane. Fond of making things explode. Plotting to kill Jabba.
front.title: •Ree-Yees

front.gametext: Non-[Maintenance] bounty hunters here are immune to Clash Of Sabers and Rebel Barrier. Whenever you draw a destiny of 3, may choose: activate 1 Force, draw bottom card of Used Pile, or place a card from hand on top of Used Pile.
front.lore: Gran convicted of murder. Exiled from his homeworld. Smuggler and bounty hunter. Slowly going insane. Fond of making things explode. Plotting to kill Jabba.
front.title: •Ree-Yees (V)

front.gametext: Once during each of your control phases, may lose 1 Force to take one vehicle, droid, weapon or device from opponent's Lost Pile or Crash Site Memorial into hand to use as your own.
front.lore: Ranat thief and scavenger from Aralia. Regularly trades with Jawas. Adept at pilfering items without alerting the owner. Willing to steal anything, even trash.
front.title: •Reegesk

front.gametext: If opponent just initiated a battle, you may do one of the following: Add one destiny to your total power only. OR if you have a character weapon present, select one opponent's character present to lose all immunity to attrition for remainder of battle.
front.lore: 'Only your hatred can destroy me.'
front.title: •Release Your Anger

front.gametext: If your piloted starship armed with a starship weapon is in a battle, lose 1 Force to reduce the power of one opponent's starship in that battle to zero. OR Place one opponent's starship just 'hit' in Lost Pile.
front.lore: When tailed by a TIE fighter, Rebel pilots are often forced to focus on escaping the TIE's firing arc.
front.title: •Relentless Pursuit

underlyingCardFor: There Are Many Hunting You Now

front.gametext: Deploy on opponent's non-droid character at same or adjacent site as your scout. During each of your control phases, if your scout is at this site (and not Undercover), opponent loses 2 Force (or 3 Force if that scout is also a biker scout).
front.lore: Biker scouts commonly work as a team to track enemies of the Empire. A pair of scouts on speeder bikes is difficult to elude.
front.title: •Relentless Tracking

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

front.gametext: Dark:  If you control, once during each of your control phases, may use 3 Force to retrieve a Victory-class Star Destroyer.  Light:  Force drain -1 here. If you occupy, opponent's Rendili game text is canceled.
front.title: •Rendili

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

front.gametext: Deploy on Rendili system. Your Victory -class Star Destroyers are deploy -2 here. Each of your Turbolaser Batteries deploys free, fires for free and adds 1 to each of its weapon destiny draws. (Immune to Alter while you occupy Rendili.)
front.lore: Responsible for early Imperial space supremacy. Rendili designs provide extremely stable weapons platforms for capital ship weapons.
front.title: •Rendili StarDrive

front.gametext: If any bounty hunter is defending a battle alone, add one battle destiny. OR If Bossk, Greedo or Boba Fett is defending a battle alone, add two battle destiny.
front.lore: Rek guza kias n'ek kriesuk zief. Rek res fesruk T'doshok kulesuk luk g'razzurg koref selukra fes k'nel. Kren'ef, T'doshok res luk rek grien forek res fel luraken.
front.title: •Res Luk Ra'auf

rulings: Works with either player's Boba Fett.

front.gametext: Adds 1 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Black 2, Black 3 or Black 4, also adds 1 to maneuver and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.
front.lore: Injuries kept Lord Vader's best TIE wingman out of the primary wave of starfighters. He remains on reserve duty, ready to replace lost pilots.
front.title: ••Reserve Pilot

front.gametext: Deploy on your side of table. While you occupy at least 3 battlegrounds or opponent occupies no battle grounds, you lose no more than 2 Force from each Force drain or insert card. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Oola had to choose between giving in to Jabba's constant advances or resisting him and inciting his wraith.
front.title: •Resistance

front.gametext: Plays on table. While you occupy at least 3 battlegrounds or opponent occupies no battlegrounds, you lose no more than 2 Force from each Force drain or 'insert' card.
front.lore: Oola had to choose between giving in to Jabba's constant advances or resisting him and inciting his wrath.
front.title: •Resistance

canceledBy: He Can Go About His Business - Defensive Shield
He Can Go About His Business (V) - Defensive Shield

front.gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on any war room at a Rebel Base. Target a Rebel with forfeit > 4 or an opponent's leader. Opponent may not initiate a battle or a Force drain at same location as target. Utinni Effect canceled when reached by target.
front.lore: 'Headquarters personnel, report to command center.'
front.title: •Responsibility Of Command

front.gametext: Deploy on any droid at any site. Droid cannot move and cannot utilize its 'game text.' During your deploy phase, Restraining Bolt may be transferred (for free) to another droid at same site.
front.lore: Affixed to droid's special recessed socket by using a fusion welder. Bolts can override a droid's circuits, freezing it in place if the droid tries to disobey orders.
front.title: Restraining Bolt

rulings: May not be deployed on an opponent's Undercover spy.
The phase 'cannot utilize game text' means the droid's game text is canceled (e.g. the game text cancelation can be prevented by Pride Of The Empire (V), in which case the droid still cannot move).
This device may only deploy on (or transfer to) a droid that is at a site.
This device may even deploy an opponent's droid.
The owner of the Restraining Bolt may transfer it to a droid present with it at a site, even an opponent's droid.

If stolen by a non-droid character (e.g. using Swilla Corey), that character carries it but the Restraining Bolt is inactive while it is on a non-droid character. Even while stolen and inactive, the new owner may still transfer it (see above rulings for transfer details).

If stolen by a droid character (e.g. using Retractable Arm), the droid character carrying the stolen Restraining Bolt is then affected by it (droid cannot move and droid's game text canceled. The new owner of the stolen Restraining Bolt may transfer it (see above rulings for transfer details).

canceledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever - Defensive Shield
You Cannot Hide Forever (V) - Defensive Shield
Your Insight Serves You Well - Defensive Shield
Your Insight Serves You Well (V) - Defensive Shield

front.gametext: Insert face up in your Reserve Deck. When Effect reaches top it is lost, along with all opponent's 'insert' cards there. Reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.) OR Deploy between two mobile sites. Opponent's characters may pass only if aboard a Lift Tube or opponent uses +1 Force each.
front.lore: In an effort to direct Luke toward Vader, Captain Bewil used his control of hatchways and lift tubes to cut off Luke's support, limiting his options and resources.
front.title: Restricted Access

rulings: If face up in Reserve Deck for any reason, it is active (not part of Life Force).

front.gametext: During your deploy phase, use X Force to rearrange all interior Death Star sites, where X = total number of those sites. All cards at a given site move along with that site. OR Cancel On The Edge.
front.lore: Strategically retracted bridges can frustrate enemy movement, forcing routing plans to be rearranged.
front.title: Retract The Bridge

front.gametext: Use 4 Force to deploy on your side of table. A starship you just lost may be placed here. Holds one starship at a time. During your deploy phase, may use X Force to bring starship to hand, where X = deploy cost of that starship.
front.lore: Imperial codes demand that damaged starships return to base for repair. Some captains with only minor damage to their ships resent this order.
front.title: •Return To Base

front.gametext: If Emperor on Death Star II, take Vader into hand from a location you control (cards on him go to owner's hand). OR During your control phase, if Vader escorting Luke or Leia at a site you control, relocate Vader (with captive) to Death Star II: Docking Bay. (Immune to Sense.)
front.lore: 'I sense you wish to continue your search for young Skywalker.'
front.title: •Rise, My Friend

underlyingCardFor: The First Order Was Just The Beginning

front.gametext: At the beginning of opponent's move phase, target an opponent's character alone at a mobile site and select an adjacent site. Opponent must choose to move target there for free (target cannot move for remainder of turn), lose target or lose 2 Force.
front.lore: There are many different paths to becoming a Jedi, each with its own risks and consequences. A student must choose wisely.
front.title: •Rite Of Passage

front.gametext: Habitat: planet sites. Landspeed = 2. Ferocity +2 when present at Bluffs or any canyon.
front.lore: Fast-moving, insect-like pest. Scavengers in rocky, secluded habitats. Hides in shadows and attacks when surprised. Nearly 1 meter long.
front.title: Rock Wart

front.gametext: Adds 1 to power of each of your bounty hunters and smugglers (but subtracts 1 from Greedo's power) at same site. Adds 1 to power of anything he pilots.
front.lore: Thuku is a typical male Rodian. Sent to hunt down Greedo by Navik the Red, head of the Chattza tribe. Rodians enjoy 'the hunt,' so many are employed as assassins.
front.title: •••Rodian

front.gametext: Deploy on an asteroid sector and specify starting direction. Every move phase, moves to next adjacent asteroid sector (reversing direction as necessary). Where present, adds 2 to asteroid destiny. May be targeted by starship weapons (defense value = 3).
front.lore: 'We're gonna get pulverized if we stay out here much longer.'
front.title: <>Rogue Asteroid

front.gametext: Take any non-unique destroyer droid into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. OR During your deploy phase, relocate your destroyer droid to an adjacent site.
front.lore: The Colicoids from Colla IV modeled destroyer droids after themselves in that they can roll up into a ball and move swiftly into a conflict.
front.title: •Rolling, Rolling, Rolling

front.gametext: May add 2 'riders' (passengers). Ability = ¼. When 'ridden' by a Jawa, moves for free and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.
front.lore: Beast of burden often used by Jawas. Excellent sense of smell. Poor vision. Slow moving. Tough hide. Easily startled by fast-moving speeders.
front.title: Ronto

combo: Accelerate may be used in conjunction with this card.

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Each of your non-unique troopers on Endor or Death Star II is forfeit +1. When opponent just used a weapon to target your character aboard a piloted vehicle, that character may use that vehicle's defense value.
front.lore: When away from the Imperial Palace on Coruscant, the Emperor is protected by legions of troops. Typically this force includes soldiers trained to fight in the local environment.
front.title: •Royal Escort

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

front.gametext: Deploys only on Coruscant or to Emperor's site (or related site). When armed with a Force pike and defending a battle, adds one battle destiny. Emperor may not be targeted by weapons unless all Royal Guards present with Emperor are 'hit.'
front.lore: Member of Emperor's Royal Guard. Completely subservient. Royal Guards must fight one of their own to the death in order to complete their training.
front.title: Royal Guard

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. Power +3 while armed with a Gaderffi Stick. Where present, each of your banthas is power and forfeit +2 unless a Weequay is at a related site. When 'riding' a bantha, adds one battle destiny.
front.lore: Tusken Raider who tends to the banthas used by URoRRuR'R'R's tribe. Expert in wielding a gaffi stick. Attacked Luke Skywalker in the Jundland Wastes.
front.title: •RR'uruurrr

front.gametext: Once per game, may take Jawa Blaster or a card with 'sandcrawler' in title or game text into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. During opponent's turn, if present at a Tatooine battleground and there is more than 1 Force in opponent's Force Pile, you may use 1 Force in opponent's Force Pile.
front.lore: Jawa
front.title: •R'tic H'weei

combo: Rune Haako + Darth Vader + Grand Moff Tarkin
Rune Haako + Sim Aloo
Rune Haako + Macroscan + Sunsdown
Rune Haako + Yeb Yeb Adem'thorn Destiny of zero for your opponent. (Lord Helmet)

front.gametext: While in battle, may choose one number. If next card opponent draws for destiny this battle has a printed destiny number matching this choice, that destiny is reduced to zero. If you just initiated a battle at same or adjacent site, retrieve 1 Force.
front.lore: Trade Federation settlement officer serving as legal council to Viceroy Gunray. Reputed to have one of the sharpest legal minds in all of the Republic. Neimoidian.
front.title: •Rune Haako

front.gametext: While at Theed Palce Throne Room, your attrition against opponent in battles at same and related Naboo sites is +X, where X = number of battle droids present at that site. While with a battle droid, Haako is power and defense value +2.
front.lore: The Trade Federation's only Neimoidian leader to have ever encountered a Jedi Knight. Assumed Daultay Dofine's responsibilities after Dofine questioned their Sith Lord's plans.
front.title: •Rune Haako, Legal Counsel

front.gametext: While at Theed Palce Throne Room, your attrition against opponent in battles at same and related Naboo sites is +X, where X = number of battle droids present at that site. While with a battle droid, Haako is power and defense value +2.
front.lore: The Trade Federation's only Neimoidian leader to have ever encountered a Jedi Knight. Assumed Daultay Dofine's responsibilities after Dofine questioned their Sith Lord's plans.
front.title: •Rune Haako, Legal Counsel (AI)

front.gametext: Power and forfeit +2 at a Coruscant site. May retrieve 1 Force each time your deploy a musician to same site. Once during each of your turns, may use 1 Force to 'charm' one male of ability < 3 present- male is forfeit = 0 for remainder of turn.
front.lore: Musician. Raised by Ortolans. Grew up on the streets of Coruscant. Rescued from the Black Sun crime cartel by Lando Calrissian.
front.title: •Rystall

rulings: May respond to her own deployment.
This character is female.

combo: Saber 1 + SFS L-s9.3 Laser Cannons

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot. Fel deploys -1 aboard. When firing SFS L-s9.3 Laser Cannons, may use 1 Force to make X = 3. Immune to attrition < 5 when Fel piloting.
front.lore: TIE interceptor serial number 000004. Assigned to Baron Soontir Fel of the fighting 181st. Bears the Saber Squadron bloodstripe, representing a minimum of 10 kills.
front.title: •Saber 1

pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot. When Phennir piloting, immune to attrition < 4 and adds 1 to forfeit of each other Saber Squadron pilot in same battle.
front.lore: TIE interceptor flown by Major Phennir. Assigned to protect Avenger at the Battle of Endor. Responsible for the logistics of Saber Squadron.
front.title: •Saber 2

pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot. Cannons are deploy -2 aboard. Immune to attrition < 3 when DS-181-3 piloting.
front.lore: TIE interceptor assigned to fly on the wing of Baron Fel. Often ordered to remain at a distance from Fel to give the Baron maneuvering room during combat.
front.title: •Saber 3

pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!

front.gametext: May deploy with a pilot as a 'react' to a battle where you have a TIE (for free if TIE is in Saber Squadron). May add 1 pilot. Immune to attrition < 4 when DS-181-4 piloting.
front.lore: TIE interceptor often assigned to fly in a reserve position during battle. The bloodstripe of the 181st denotes the 10 kills scored by DS-181-4.
front.title: •Saber 4

pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!
rulings: To use the react text, you must have a piloted TIE there. It's even possible that other TIE was itself just deployed as a react a moment earlier.
When using the react text to deploy for free, the pilot is also free.
When using Saber 4's text to deploy it and a pilot for free, and Goldenrod on table, must use 2 Force for the pilot (but 0 for Saber 4).

front.gametext: Reduce your battle damage by 5 by losing from hand a starship, vehicle or character. OR If your character's forfeit was just reduced to 0, restore it to normal. (Immune to Sense.)
front.lore: Jabba's minions could be expected to be sacrificed to save the Hutt, to destroy one of the Hutts enemies or to provide the Hutt and his minions with a good laugh.
front.title: •Sacrifice

front.gametext: Opponent may initiate battle at same site for free. At same or adjacent site, whenever an opponent draws a card for battle destiny, if it is: Even, opponent must use 1 Force (if possible); Odd, destiny card is lost. (AH-hahahahaha!)
front.lore: Male Kowakian. Prankster. Humiliates others for Jabba's amusement. His life depends on making Jabba laugh at least once per day.
front.title: •Salacious Crumb

rulings: Zero is an even number.
If the destiny is not a whole number (e.g. a card with destiny 0.5), it is neither even nor odd, so no result.
When a destiny card is lost, this does not affect the destiny value (e.g. a battle destiny draw of 5 is still a 5 after the card is lost).

front.gametext: Deploys only to a Tatooine site. May add 1 driver and 7 passengers. Cannot move to mobile sites. Adds 1 to forfeit of each Jawa at same exterior site.
front.lore: Warren-like enclosed homes for Jawa tribes. Protect against Tusken Raiders, krayt dragons, etc. 36 meters longs, 17 meters tall. Originally mining vehicles. No two look alike.
front.title: Sandcrawler

front.gametext: Dark:  Deploy on your sandcrawler. Each Jawa is forfeit +2 here. 'Nighttime conditions' here.  Light:  Your characters may enter/exit here for 1 Force each. 'Nighttime conditions' here.
front.title: •••Sandcrawler: Droid Junkheap

rulings: Must deploy to a specific Sandcrawler on table (may be unique or non-unique, and must belong to Dark).  This site, and any cards at it, are lost when that Sandcrawler is lost.
This site is 'adjacent' to the site where the Sandcrawler vehicle is (for example, Expand The Empire can expand text to or from here).
This site is 'related' to all sites on the same planet that the Sandcrawler is on.
This site does <u>not</u> take on the name of the planet (e.g. it is not a Tatooine site, a character here is not 'on Tatooine' or 'on Cloud City' even if the Sandcrawler is, etc).

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Cancels Colo Claw Fish. While no card here, you may draw destiny and place it face-up here. If you are about to draw a card for weapon or battle destiny, you may instead use card here, then place it in Lost Pile. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Huge creature that is feline in nature and moves on its hind legs. Slow movement makes it difficult for the monster to feed but whenever a confrontation arises it always wins.
front.title: •Sando Aqua Monster

rulings: When a player uses the card from Sando Aqua Monster instead of drawing a weapon or battle destiny, they are performing a substituted destiny draw. The destiny value from the card on Sando is used, and it cannot be modified, canceled or reset and does not count towards limits on the number of destinies that may be drawn.

Although the substituted destiny value from Sando Aqua Monster may not subsequently be modified (e.g. by Prepared Defenses), the destiny value of the stacked card could have already been subject to global modifiers (e.g. the Senate objectives can make senators globally destiny +2 or +3). Such global modifiers affect the card while it is on Sando, so they apply when the destiny substitution occurs.

front.gametext: Deploys only to Tatooine or any desert. Immune to Sandwhirl. Power -1 when not on Tatooine.
front.lore: Equipped for harsh, high-temperature environments. Primarily assigned to search-and-destroy missions, but sometimes beaks up local disputes or recover stolen droids.
front.title: Sandtrooper

front.gametext: Deploy on a Desert. Specify starting direction. All characters (except Jawas and Tusken Raiders) present at same non-interior site are missing. During your control phase, moves to next adjacent site (reversing directions as necessary), but lost if at an interior site.
front.lore: Called 'Teeth Of The Wind' by Tusken Raiders. Only those familiar with Tatooine's vast deserts can navigate successfully during its furious onslaught.
front.title: <>Sandwhirl

front.gametext: * Ferocity = 4 + destiny. Habitat: Great Pit Of Carkoon. If Sarlacc eats a captive, may retrieve 1 Force for each of your aliens here. Anything eaten by Sarlacc is placed out of play.
front.lore: Very patient predator in the Dune Sea. Tentacles can grab prey up to four meters away. Digests victims for 1000 years. Often fed prisoners by Jabba the Hutt.
front.title: •Sarlacc

front.gametext: Deploys -1 for each other Sith character here (limit - 4). Once per game, may exchange a card in hand with a Sith character in Lost Pile. Immune to attrition < 3.
front.lore: Dathomirian.
front.title: •Savage Opress

rulings: Does not count himself for the 'Deploys -1' text.
May declare that you are using the exchange action, then review cards in Lost Pile before selecting a card from hand to exchange.

front.gametext: Use 1 Force to glance at the cards in the opponent's hand for 10 seconds. You may move any one Rebel you find there to the top of opponent's Used Pile.
front.lore: Imperials use sensitive equipment to search captured ships for shielded compartments. Scanning crew BT-445 planned to search the Millennium Falcon.
front.title: Scanning Crew

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot. Power +3 during a Bombing Run battle. When proton bombs aboard 'collapse' a site, opponent loses 1 Force for each rebel just lost.
front.lore: Scimitar bombing group TIE bomber. Equipped with advanced targeting system to increase damage during planetary bombardment.
front.title: •Scimitar 1

pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot. Power +3 during a Bombing Run battle. Once per game, you may deploy one Proton Bombs from Reserve Deck on this starfighter; reshuffle.
front.lore: TIE bomber repaired after being struck by an asteroid in the Anoat system. Stationed aboard second Death Star battle station.
front.title: •Scimitar 2

pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!

front.title: Scout Blaster

Scout Recon + Colonel Dyer + Commander Igar

front.lore: Familiarity with native terrain is essential to a scout garrison. Imperial command can also put this type of information to effective use.

front.gametext: USED: Cancel Solo Han or Warrior's Courage or I Know.  LOST: If Han and Leia are in a battle together, draw two destiny. Subtract that amount from opponent's attrition and total power (cannot fall below zero).
front.lore: 'But you didn't see us alone in the south passage. She expressed her true feelings for me.' 'My...Why you stuck-up, half-witted, scruffy-looking NERF HERDER!'

front.lore: A relief in Nal Hutta sandstone. Hand-carved by slaves of the great Hutt artist Dreyba. Commissioned by Jabba to illustrate his vast influence. Titled 'Ne Ganna Dateel Jabba.'
front.title: •Scum And Villainy

Works while (for example) Darth Vader piloting an Independent starship.

front.lore: TIE fighter garrisoned aboard second Death Star. Part of Scythe Squadron, a TIE group with upgraded SFS Pw702 maneuvering jets to increase performance in tight quarters.
front.title: •Scythe 1

front.title: •Scythe 3

front.lore: Scythe Squadron TIE fighters are modified TIE/lns assigned to defend the second Death Star during construction. Their pilots fly frequent training missions within the Death Star.
front.title: •••Scythe Squadron TIE

front.lore: Manufactured by the Baktoid Combat Automata, battle droids are used by the Trade Federation throughout the galaxy in order to secure and protect sites of strategic importance.

front.gametext: Lose a droid to cancel all attrition against you at same site this turn. OR Re-target an opponent's weapon to one of your droids at same site. If droid is 'hit', use original target's forfeit number.
front.lore: ''Fraid there's not much left...I didn't hit it that hard. It musta had a self-destruct.'
front.title: Self-Destruct Mechanism

front.gametext: Deploy on Galactic Senate. While you have a senate majority, your Force generation here is +3, and your Force generation at Coruscant locations is immune to This Place Can Be A Little Rough. Place Effect in Lost Pile if opponent controls this location.
front.lore: Used to monitor and record events inside the Galactic Senate. By law, hovercams are required to be present in every Senate session, a law Senator Palpatine opposed.
front.title: Senate Hovercam

front.gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on any Tatooine site (except docking bay). Target any trooper on Death Star. When target reaches Utinni Effect, attrition +1 against opponent in all Tatooine battles as long as target remains at same site as Utinni Effect.
front.lore: Vader sent Imperial stormtroopers to the surface of Tatooine in search of the stolen Death Star plans. 'There'll be no one to stop us this time.'
front.title: •Send A Detachment Down

front.gametext: If opponent just played an Interrupt (or just initiated a 'react'), target one of your characters on table. Draw destiny. If destiny < ability of target, that Interrupt (or 'react') is canceled. OR Cancel Alter.
front.lore: A Sith Lord can use the Force to reach out and find what he seeks.
front.title: Sense

front.gametext: Cancel one Interrupt (or one 'react') by drawing a destiny < ability of your highest-ability character on table. OR Cancel one Alter card just played.
front.lore: 'I sense something. A presence I've not felt since...'
front.title: Sense

front.gametext: USED: Target your highest-ability character and one just-played Interrupt. Draw destiny. If destiny < ability of target character, cancel target Interrupt.  LOST: Use 3 Force. Each player places hand onto Reserve Deck (if possible), then places Used Pile onto Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Each player then draws cards from Reserve Deck equal to the number of cards just placed from hand onto Reserve Deck (if any).
front.title: Sense & Uncertain Is The Future

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot, 4 passengers and 2 speeder bikes. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. Any starship cannon may deploy here. Takes off and lands for free.
front.lore: Modified light freighter. Length 20 meters. Heavily armored for a landing craft. Has ion cannon mounts. Often carries speeder bikes for reconnaissance purposes.
front.title: Sentinel-Class Landing Craft

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots (or 3 to any speeder bike). When in a battle with your other biker scout, may draw one battle destiny and subtract that amount from opponent's attrition and total power.
front.lore: Wakeelmui native. Former employee of Sienar Fleet Systems missile division. Stormtrooper biker scout with dreams of transferring to 181st Imperial Fighter Group.
front.title: •Sergeant Barich

rulings: Barich's action can only be initiated if attrition exists (opponent successfully completed a battle destiny draw, even if it was a 0).
Barich's action is initiated in the power segment after battle destinies (and any attrition destinies) are drawn.
Barich's action subtracts from attrition against his owner (Dark).

combo: Sergeant Elsek on Bike + Avarik on Speeder Bike

front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of any speeder bike he pilots. When in battle with Avarik, adds 2 to your total battle destiny. When forfeited at same site as your other biker scout, also satisfies all remaining attrition and battle damage against you.
front.lore: Stormtrooper biker scout. Kuat native. Avarik's partner since graduation from Corulag academy. Often forced to cover for partner's rash decisions.
front.title: •Sergeant Elsek

rulings: When his text is applied, satisfies all remaining attrition even if there is no battle damage, and vice versa.
If prevented from being used to satisfy attrition (e.g. Crack Shot), his text still satisfies all remaining battle damage, but not attrition.

front.gametext: May deploy -1 as a 'react' to any forest, jungle or exterior Endor site. Adds 3 to power of any speeder bike he pilots. When vehicle he drives or pilots is targeted by High-speed Tactics or Get Alongside That One, adds 2 to your destiny draw.
front.lore: Cocky stormtrooper from an Outer Rim forest planet. Confident biker scout and hunter. Relies on superior balance and strength to operate his speeder bike.
front.title: •Sergeant Irol

front.gametext: When in a battle on Hoth, immune to attrition < 3 and adds 2 to attrition against opponent. Your snowtroopers are deploy -1 to same Hoth site. Power -1 when not on Hoth.
front.lore: Leader of most brutal snowtrooper plotoon in the battle of Hoth. Cunning planner. Coordinates attacks and manages troop movements.
front.title: •Sergeant Major Bursk

front.gametext: When in a battle with another Death Star trooper, adds one battle destiny. Your Death Star troopers are deploy -1 to same Death Star site. Trooper Charge targeting at same or related site is a Used Interrupt. Power -1 when not on Death Star.
front.lore: Commander of a platoon of Death Star troopers. Maintains security around the detention block area. Often serves as Lt. Shann Childsen's attache.
front.title: •Sergeant Major Enfield

front.gametext: Deploys for free on Cloud City if your Lando is at a related location. Power +2 on Cloud City. When in battle at a Cloud City site, adds 1 to your total battle destiny for each of your other Cloud City troopers in that battle.
front.lore: Tyrannical squad commander on Cloud City. Treats his fellow Cloud City troopers with disdain. Enemy of Utris M'Toc.
front.title: •Sergeant Merril

rulings: The phrase 'on Cloud City' means at a Cloud City site, not the Bespin: Cloud City sector.

front.gametext: While on Hoth, makes all your snowtroopers immune to Ice Storm. When in battle on Hoth with another snowtrooper, adds one battle destiny. Precise Attack targeting at same or related site is a Used Interrupt. Power -1 when not on Hoth.
front.lore: Commanded a squad of snowtroopers in the Battle of Hoth. Trains snowtroopers in extreme-weather survival tactics. Originally from Ukio.
front.title: •Sergeant Narthax

rulings: This card is not a commander ('commanded' doesn't count).

front.gametext: Permanent weapon is E-web Blaster (may target a character, landed starfighter, or vehicle for free; if targeting a starfighter or vehicle, add one destiny to attrition; otherwise, subtract 3 from target's immunity to attrition (if any) until end of turn).
front.lore: Snowtrooper.
front.title: •Sergeant Narthax With E-web Blaster

front.gametext: While Tarl is the trooper targeted by Spice Mines of Kessel, that Utinni Effect is immune to Alter and Tarl adds 4 to Force retrieved when completed. Subtracts 3 from Force opponent retrieves with Noble Sacrifice.
front.lore: Took part in the capture of the Rebel Blockade Runner Tantive IV. Stormtrooper trained on Corulag. Corellia native.
front.title: •Sergeant Tarl

front.gametext: Deploys -2 on Death Star. When in battle, adds 1 to your total battle destiny for each of your Death Star troopers present. While on Death Star, adds 1 to each of your Force drains at a battleground related to system Death Star orbits.
front.lore: Senior watch trooper at Death Star's command center. Monitors external sensor data, scanning for Rebel activity. Vigilant in his duties.
front.title: •Sergeant Torent

front.gametext: May deploy for free to a battle you just initiated at a battleground site.
front.lore: Stormtrooper assigned to Colonel Dyer's command. His unit was recommended to Commander Igar by Governor Yount of the Wakeelmui garrison.
front.title: •Sergeant Wallen

combo: Set for Stun + Scanning Crew Send a Rebel back into the hand then scan it right into the Used Pile.
Set For Stun + M'iiyoom Onith

front.gametext: Use 2 Force to target one opponent's character. Draw destiny. If destiny > character's ability, character immediately returns to opponent's hand. (Also, any cards deployed on character return to owners' hands.)
front.lore: '...bring me the passengers. I want them alive!' Imperial soldiers use blaster stun settings to intimidate or to capture prisoners for questioning and interrogation.
front.title: Set For Stun

rulings: Completed Jedi Tests that are 'on table' due to Mind What You Have Learned are treated as being on the apprentice (so they are returned to hand along with the apprentice).
Incomplete Jedi Tests are lost when the apprentice leaves table
If Save You It Can on table, the apprentice returns to hand first, then the Jedi Tests on table are suspended (so they are not returned to hand).

rulings: On the 7-side, a Force drain would be +1 where Dark has a Victory-class, Resurgent-class or Interdictor-class Star Destroyer.  A Force drain would be +2 where Dark has an Imperial-class or Super-class.
If Dark has both types at the same system (e.g. a Victory-class Star Destroyer for Force drain +1, with an Imperial-class Star Destroyer for Force drain +2), the Force drain is +2.

A common online 'misprint' of the 7-side states that 'Your Force drains at battleground systems where you have a Star Destroyer are each +2 (or +1 if that Star Destroyer is Victory-class).' but the correct text found on all physical copies of the card is 'Your Force drains at battleground systems where you have a Star Destroyer are each +1 (or +2 if that Star Destroyer is Imperial- or Super-class).'

front.lore: TIE cannon mass produced at Wakeelmui system. Campatable with multiple TIE models for ease of deployment.

front.title: SFS L-s9.3 Laser Cannons

front.lore: Using the power of the dark side, Vader caused Luke to lose his confidence and question his sense of direction.
front.title: •Shattered Hope
