front.gametext: May add 1 pilot and 1 passenger, or 2 passengers. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1.
front.lore: Limited production, light reconnaissance starship. Minimal armor and weapons. Long-range sensor and communications array. Scouts for Rebel activity.
front.title: TIE Scout

front.gametext: If opponent just initiated a Force drain at a system, cloud sector or asteroid sector, you may 'react' by deploying TIEs and pilots to that location (at normal use of the Force).
front.lore: Several TIEs were assigned to patrol Cloud City prior to the Imperial occupation of Bespin. Their instructions were to herd any vessels attempting to escape toward the Executor.
front.title: •TIE Sentry Ships

cards.conceptBy: (Original concept by Michael Erisman - PC Volunteer Award 2008)

front.gametext: USED: If you just drew a starship for destiny, take that starship into hand to cancel and redraw that destiny.  LOST: Use 3 Force to retrieve a starship into hand.
front.lore: Several TIEs were assigned to patrol Cloud City prior to the Imperial occupation of Bespin. Their instructions were to herd any vessels attempting to escape toward the Executor.
front.title: •TIE Sentry Ships (V)

front.gametext: Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. You may deploy cards to same system or sector as a 'react'.
front.lore: Reconnaissance starfighter. Often deployed first to gather detailed information on enemy starship movement before full fleet engagement.
front.title: TIE Vanguard

cancels: Suspends Honor Of The Jedi while in a senate majority

front.gametext: Agenda: wealth. While in a senate majority, your Force generation is +2 at battlegrounds you control, and Honor Of The Jedi is suspended. Once during your deploy phase, may draw bottom card of your Force Pile into hand.
front.lore: Quarren senator elected by the people of Mon Calamari. Has amassed considerable wealth through a multitude of political deals, but still moves to gain more.
front.title: •Tikkes

front.gametext: Deploy on opponent's side at same site as one of your mining droids. 'Explodes' at beginning of your next turn. Draw destiny. That number of opponent's characters there are immediately lost (owner's choice). Timer Mine is also lost.
front.lore: A timer-activated explosive device designed to be placed by a mining droid. Originally used in ore and spice mines for demolition. Altered for military use.
front.title: Timer Mine

rulings: Timer Mines are not allowed to use docking bay transit.

canceledBy: If Vul Tazaene present with Tonnika Sisters, Vul and Tonnika Sisters are lost
combo: Tonnika Sisters + Kiffex
Tonnika Sisters + Nevar Yalnal

front.gametext: Twice during each of your control phases, may use 2 Force to draw 2 destiny for 2 chances at a destiny = 2. If successful, may steal or destroy up to 2 weapons or 2 devices present.
front.lore: Twins. Thieves. Con artists. Spies. Swindlers. Double agents. Brea and Senni use their natural charm to sway the unwary on the fringe of society.
front.title: •Tonnika Sisters

rulings: This is a combo card.
Can only steal cards that can be carried by characters, not (for example) Proton Torpedoes.
Can steal (or destroy) Han's Toolkit from a character, vehicle, or starship.
The weapons/devices must be present, but Tonnika Sisters do not need to be present.
May steal/destroy up to two weapons or up to two devices, but not one of each.
Cards with multiple warrior icons can still only escort one captive at a time.

front.gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your side of table. Non-creature vehicles at marker sites under 'nighttime conditions' are power = 0, maneuver = 0 and landspeed = 0.
front.lore: 'We're having some trouble adapting them to the cold.'
front.title: Too Cold For Speeders

front.gametext: Agendas: ambition, taxation, wealth. While in a senate majority, once per turn may add 1 to your total attrition in battle for each character with an ambition agenda at Galactic Senate.
front.lore: Female senator and member of her planet's ruling class. Her original optimism in the political process has been eroded by witnessing bribery, corruption and petty bickering.
front.title: •Toonbuck Toora

front.gametext: USED: Cancel Never Tell Me The Odds if it was just inserted or revealed. (Immune to Sense).  LOST: Target a droid at Droid Workshop that you have captured or stolen. Droid is lost. Retrieve Force equal to droid's forfeit (doubled if stolen).
front.lore: 'We have been without an interpreter since our master got angry with our last protocol droid and disintegrated him.'
front.title: •Torture

combo: Tractor Beam + In Range + Our First Catch Of The Day
Tractor Beam + Captain Lennox + Besieged
Tractor Beam + Flawless Marksmanship
Tractor Beam + I Want That Ship
Tractor Beam + Ion Cannon

front.gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your Star Destroyer. At the end of a battle at same system or sector, may target an opponent's starship present (except Mon Calamari Star Cruiser) using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Target captured if destiny > defense value.
front.lore: Captures enemy vessels for boarding. When used in conjunction with an ion cannon, tractor beams can ensnare even the most maneuverable starships.
front.title: Tractor Beam

combo: Trade Federation Battleship + Naboo + Neimoidian Pilots Neimoidian Pilots deploy free and activate 1 Force each time they deploy. How often do you have more active Force after your deploy phase than before?

Trade Federation Battleship + Droid Starfighters + Battle Deployment Each player's ships are power -2 at systems where he doesn't have both a capital ship and a starfighter. Since Trade Federation Battleships and Droid Starfighters are meant to go together, you already have that covered. Does your opponent?
Trade Federation Battleship + Sil Unch

front.gametext: May add 4 pilots, 4 passengers, 2 vehicles and 4 starfighters. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. While with any starfighter, draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise.
front.lore: Massive cargo vessels that were converted by the Trade Federation into armed battleships. Each is equipped with a large contingent of droid starfighters and battle droids.
front.title: Trade Federation Battleship

combo: Federation Droid Control Ship + Neimodian Pilot + Tey How + Droid Starfighter Power 12 plus 2 battle destiny. Add a few more pilots and/or ships to maintain control of a system while Tey How reduces your Force loss to drains at systems within 2 parsecs.
Federation Droid Control Ship + Sil Unch

front.gametext: May add 4 pilots, 4 passengers, 2 vehicles, and 4 starfighters. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. While a droid starfighter here, adds one battle destiny.
front.lore: These heavily modified battleships are used to control and direct the Trade Federation's automated army. Easily identified by its array of sensors and antennae.
front.title: <>Trade Federation Droid Control Ship

front.gametext: May add 2 pilots and 6 vehicles. Deploys and moves like a starfighter. While at a site, once during your deploy phase may take an MTT into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: C-9979 landing craft designed to transport and unload Multi Troop Transports and its battle droid cargo as rapidly as possible.
front.title: Trade Federation Landing Craft

front.gametext: Use 2 Force to target a starship at same system as your [Trade Federation] starship armed with a weapon. Target is forfeit = 0 until end of turn. OR During battle, add X to your total power, where X = armor of one of your [Trade Federation] starships in that battle.
front.lore: Organizations as wealthy as the Trade Federation can afford large amounts of military hardware, all purchased under the guise of protecting their commercial interests.
front.title: •Trade Federation Tactics

front.gametext: USED: Cancel an attempt to use a weapon to target your capital starship. LOST: Re-target On Target to an opponent's capital starship armed with a weapon. OR Take Blockade Support Ship or Invisible Hand into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Organizations as wealthy as the Trade Federation can afford large amounts of military hardware, all purchased under the guise of protecting their commercial interests.
front.title: •Trade Federation Tactics (V)

combo: Trample + any piloted AT-AT or AT-ST present at a site
Trample + Walker Garrison

front.gametext: If you have a piloted AT-AT or AT-ST present at a site, target opponent's character, 'crashed' vehicle or unpiloted vehicle without armor present. Draw destiny. Character lost if destiny > ability. Vehicle lost if destiny < 7.
front.lore: The enormous feet of a walker are designed for mobility on many types of terrain. They also can be used by merciless pilots to crush the Rebellion.
front.title: Trample

front.gametext: Power and Forfeit +1 at same site as a Wookiee or while Bossk at Audience Chamber. When in battle at same site as a bounty, adds 1 to attrition against opponent.
front.lore: Trandoshans refer to themselves as T'doshok. Hate Wookiees. Many have come to work for Jabba, attempting to emulate the success of Bossk.
front.title: Trandoshan

front.gametext: If you have no characters at Rancor Pit at the end of your deploy phase, target a character (even a captive) at Audience Chamber. Draw destiny. If destiny +2 > ability, target relocated to Rancor Pit, and, if captive, released to the Light Side of Rancor Pit (not Used Pile).
front.lore: 'Boscka!'
front.title: •Trap Door

combo: Trinto Duaba + Monnok
Trinto Duaba + Dune Sea Sabacc (or any Sabacc really) + Voyeur Play Sabacc to get cards in their used pile, then the other 2 Interrupts to make them lose force/other cards. (maxbeedo)

front.gametext: If there are cards in the opponent's Used Pile during your battle phase, draw one destiny. All cards there with the same destiny number are lost.
front.lore: A Stennes Shifter, a near-human race. Have ability to blend unnoticed into crowds. Trinto profits from turning lawbreakers over to Imperial authorities.
front.title: Trinto Duaba

front.gametext: If a battle was just initiated at a site, each of your troopers present is power +2 and immune to attrition for remainder of turn.
front.lore: An assault of stormtroopers caused Leia, Chewie and Lando to retreat. When working together, the troopers' powerful onslaught can appear unstoppable.
front.title: Trooper Assault

front.gametext: Select one of your troopers in a battle to make a 'charge.' If that trooper is a Death Star Trooper, it is power +3 this battle. If any other trooper, power +2. However, that trooper must be forfeited at end of battle.
front.lore: Imperial troopers are fearless and totally indoctrinated. Backed by the most powerful weapons and starships in the galaxy, they tend to consider themselves invincible.
front.title: Trooper Charge

front.gametext: While he is on Tatooine, Local Trouble and Look Sir, Droids are Used Interrupts. Opponent may select target when using Friendly Fire at same site as Felth.
front.lore: Dispatched to Tatooine to apprehend renegade droids fleeing the Tantive IV. Suspected to have misgivings about Imperial methods. Allegedly shot his commander in the back.
front.title: •Trooper Davin Felth

combo: Blendin + Trooper Assault + Trooper Charge : Power *8* if you initiate the battle, all at the cost of zero Force! Makes a great surprise for your opponent in a 'react' deck.  Blendin + Lone Warrior : Leave him alone at a site and give him defensive cards. Then, if your opponent chooses not to let him participate in a battle, the battle is just cancelled.

front.gametext: Deploys only on Cloud City, but may move elsewhere. Power +2 when participating in a battle you initiate. Opponent may use 2 Force to 'bribe' (exclude) Blendin from battle.
front.lore: Corrupt captain of the Cloud City Wing Guard. Began working during the administration of Baron Raynor. Easily bribed. Keeps the peace through intimidation.
front.title: •Trooper Jerrol Blendin

rulings: The phrase 'on Cloud City' means at a Cloud City site, not the Bespin: Cloud City sector.

front.gametext: Requirements: A gambler or trooper at a site. Wild cards (2-7): Imperial and Rebel leaders. (Troopers may use weapons as wildcards.) Clone cards: Locations and droids. Stakes: One transport vehicle without armor or one character weapon.
front.lore: Sabacc is a popular game for off-duty Imperial stormtroopers throughout the galaxy.
front.title: •Trooper Sabacc

front.gametext: May add 7 passengers. Once per turn, may deploy a battle droid leader to same site from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Immune to attrition < 3 (< 5 if your AAT or STAP present).
front.lore: Primary command liaison transport. Contains the majority of officer battle droids. Has priority to unload as soon as the area is secured. Enclosed.
front.title: •TT-6

front.gametext: May add 4 passengers and 3 STAPs. Once per turn, may deploy a STAP to same site from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Immune to attrition < 3 (< 5 if your AAT or STAP present).
front.lore: Auxiliary mobilization supply transport. Coordinates with the Droid Control Ship to determine whether additional STAPs are needed in any given area. Enclosed.
front.title: •TT-9

combo: Turboaser Battery + Ion Cannon
Turbolaser Battery + Rendili StarDrive

front.gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on your Star Destroyer or any mobile system. May target a starship using 2 Force. Draw two destiny. Subtract 2 if targeting a capital starship. Otherwise, subtract 5. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.
front.lore: High-powered blasters. Require power generators, cryogenic cooling units and large crews. More effective against capital starships than starfighters.
front.title: Turbolaser Battery

cancels: Any attempt to place a 'hit' starship
vehicle or droid in the Used Pile rather than the Lost Pile

front.gametext: USED: Cancel any attempt to place a 'hit' starship, vehicle or droid in the Used Pile rather than the Lost Pile. OR Cancel Han's Toolkit.  LOST: Cancel Crash Site Memorial.
front.lore: 'Turn it off! Turn it off! Off! TURN IT OFF!'
front.title: Turn It Off! Turn It Off!

underlyingCardFor: Turn It Off! Turn It Off! (V)

front.gametext: Play a Defensive Shield from under your Starting Effect. OR If opponent just deployed a [Maintenance] card, it may not battle for remainder of turn. OR Cancel Out Of Commission (if attempting to place a card out of play). (Immune to Sense.)
front.lore: 'Turn it off! Turn it off! Off! TURN IT OFF!'
front.title: Turn It Off! Turn It Off! (V)

front.gametext: While at Podrace Arena, if opponent just placed race destiny on their Podracer, once per turn may use 3 Force to 'shoot' (no other Tusken Raiders may 'shoot' this turn.) Draw destiny. If destiny > 3, place race destiny in opponent's hand.
front.lore: Tusken Raiders are constantly taking bets to see who can hit the most Podracers on the Boonta Eve racetrack.
front.title: Tusken Raider

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. Power +1 if another non-unique Tusken Raider present. If you have four or more non-unique Tusken Raiders present, your total power here is +2.
front.lore: 'Sand People.' Ride banthas. Wield gaderffi (gaffi) sticks. Wear eye protectors and breath masks. Violent, nomadic, desert survival experts. 'Urrrg! Ur Ur Uur!'
front.title: Tusken Raider

combo: Tusken Scavengers + Skrilling

front.gametext: Use 1 Force to draw destiny. If destiny < the number of Tusken Raiders on table, you may scavenge (search through) the opponent's Used Pile. All vehicles, weapons or devices you find there are lost.
front.lore: 'Sand People always ride single file to hide their numbers.' They frequently attack strangers as they scavenge for useful equipment. Looted Luke's landspeeder.
front.title: Tusken Scavengers

front.gametext: USED: Use 3 Force to search your Reserve Deck and take one Effect of any kind into hand; reshuffle.  STARTING: Deploy from your Reserve Deck one Effect which has no deploy cost; reshuffle. Place Interrupt in the Lost Pile.
front.lore: 'He's no Jedi.'
front.title: •Twi'lek Advisor

front.gametext: If Audience Chamber on table, deploy Passenger Deck or a pit from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. OR Deploy an alien leader or Twi'lek to Audience Chamber from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: 'He's no Jedi.'
front.title: •Twi'lek Advisor (V)

back.errataNotes: Original card had Premium icon instead of Episode I and Tatooine icons, and the underlying card was I Will Find Them Quickly, Master.
back.gametext: Twin Suns Of Tatooine:Deploy Tatooine system and a non-Jabba's Palace Tatooine site. {For} remainder of game, you may not deploy Jabba's Palace sites or Sandwhirl. {While} this side up, once per turn, may use 1 Force to deploy a Tatooine battleground site from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. {Flip} this card if you control two Tatooine battleground sites (at least one with a Dark Jedi) and occupy Tatooine system, and opponent controls no Tatooine sites.Well Trained In The Jedi Arts:{While} this side up, once per game, may deploy Tatooine Occupation from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Once during your control phase, may peek at the top two cards of your Reserve Deck; take one into hand and shuffle Reserve Deck. For opponent to move a character or vehicle from same site as your Dark Jedi requires +1 Force. {Flip} this card if opponent controls more Tatooine sites than you.
back.title: Twin Suns Of Tatooine / Well Trained In The Jedi Arts

front.errataNotes: Original card required the started Tatooine site to be a battleground. Original card had Premium icon instead of Episode I and Tatooine icons.
front.gametext: Twin Suns Of Tatooine:Deploy Tatooine system and a non-Jabba's Palace Tatooine site. {For} remainder of game, you may not deploy Jabba's Palace sites or Sandwhirl. {While} this side up, once per turn, may use 1 Force to deploy a Tatooine battleground site from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. {Flip} this card if you control two Tatooine battleground sites (at least one with a Dark Jedi) and occupy Tatooine system, and opponent controls no Tatooine sites.Well Trained In The Jedi Arts:{While} this side up, once per game, may deploy Tatooine Occupation from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Once during your control phase, may peek at the top two cards of your Reserve Deck; take one into hand and shuffle Reserve Deck. For opponent to move a character or vehicle from same site as your Dark Jedi requires +1 Force. {Flip} this card if opponent controls more Tatooine sites than you.
front.title: Twin Suns Of Tatooine / Well Trained In The Jedi Arts

combo: Tyrant + Imperial Helmsman Draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

front.gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles and 4 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 1. When using Tractor Beam, adds 1 to destiny draw.
front.lore: Assigned to Admiral Ozzel's Death Squadron. Attempted to capture Rebel starships fleeing the Hoth system.
front.title: •Tyrant

combo: U-3PO (Yoo-Threepio) + Program Trap
U-3PO (Yoo-Threepio) + Nevar Yalnal
U-3PO (Yoo-Threepio) + E Chu Ta

front.errataNotes: Significantly reworded for clarification and standardization. No gameplay change.
front.gametext: Deploys only to a site as an Undercover spy. If Undercover at a battle, adds his power to Light Side. If U-3PO just had his 'cover broken,' Light Side may steal him.
front.lore: This protocol droid served in the House of Alderaan's Diplomatic Corps. Imperials altered its programming for espionage, making the droid an unwitting spy for the Empire.
front.title: •U-3PO (Yoo-Threepio)

rulings: While undercover, adds his power to Light but does not participate in the battle.
Light may choose not to accept this droid when its cover is broken, in which case it becomes a non-Undercover droid for its current owner.

front.gametext: May add 1 driver and 2 passengers. May move as a 'react.'
front.lore: Enclosed repulsorlift landspeeder. Micro-thrusters placed around spherical hull. Seats three. Extremely maneuverable. Top speed of 160 km per hour.
front.title: Ubrikkian 9000 Z001

front.gametext: Power +2 at Trash Compactor, Droid Junkheap, Incinerator or Carbonite Chamber. Functions as a leader if present with another Ugnaught. Where present, other Ugnaughts are forfeit +2 and double their bonus to Carbon-Freezing destiny.
front.lore: Ugnaught assigned to determine how to use carbon-freezing on humans. Placed in charge or the Ugnaught workers on Cloud City. Formerly enslaved by humans.
front.title: •Ugloste

combo: Ugnaughts + Prepare The Chamber + Carbonite Chamber Console + Ugloste A guaranteed freezing draw.

Ugnaughts + weapons + bounty hunters. These guys can serve as the ultimate armorers. You don't have to worry about hanging on to combinations of weapon cards until you actually have the warriors to use them.

front.gametext: When at Carbonite Chamber, cumulatively adds 1 to each Carbon- Freezing destiny draw. During your control phase, may lose 1 Force from hand to search your Lost Pile and take one weapon or device into hand.
front.lore: Cheap manual labor from Gentes in the Anoat system. Make up Cloud City's second largest population. Responsible for maintenance and menial chores throughout the city.
front.title: Ugnaught

combo: Umpass-Stay + Nevar Yalnal

front.gametext: Power +2 at a Jabba's Palace site. Each of your other musicians at same site is power +2 and immune to attrition < 3. Immune to attrition < 4.
front.lore: Klatooinian born into slavery to Desilijic Hutt clan on Shawti. Musician. Works as a spy for Jabba at his desert fortress while playing drums for visiting bands.
front.title: •Umpass-stay

front.gametext: Use 3 Force. Each player places hand onto Reserve Deck (if possible), then places Used Pile onto Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Each player then draws cards from Reserve Deck equal to the number of cards just placed from hand onto Reserve Deck (if any).
front.lore: Even a Jedi cannot always foresee future events.
front.title: Uncertain Is The Future

front.gametext: Deploy on your spy at a site and cross spy to opponent's side. Spy is now Undercover. During your deploy phase, may voluntarily 'break cover' (lose Effect) if at a site. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: The Empire maintains a network of spies attempting to infiltrate the Rebel Alliance or misinform their operatives.
front.title: Undercover

rulings: If the character is persona replaced by a non-spy version, Undercover is lost and the character ceases to be Undercover.

The Undercover character prevents the opponent from Force draining at same site, and allows the owner to deploy to same site even without presence or Force icons. These benefits are the same even if the Undercover character is a droid.
The Undercover character is inactive (for example it does not participate in battles) but outside of battle it may be targeted by Interrupts and anything that could make it dueled, hit, or lost.
The owner may voluntarily break cover during their deploy phase.
If the character's cover is broken (either voluntarily or by another card such as Corran Horn), then Undercover is lost.

front.gametext: Use 2 Force to search your Reserve Deck and take one Interrupt into hand. Shuffle, cut and replace.
front.lore: 'Sir! Sir! I've isolated the reverse power flux coupling!'
front.title: •Unexpected Interruption

front.gametext: During your turn, target an opponent's unpiloted starship present at a system, or an opponent's unpiloted vehicle. Target is lost (along with any cards aboard it). OR Cancel Hyper Escape, Power Pivot, or Out Of Commission.
front.lore: With mounting pressure from superior forces, the Rebellion sometimes has to abandon its crippled equipment in order to simply get its personnel out alive.
front.title: •Unsalvageable

front.gametext: Deploys only on on Tatooine. When at same site as another Tusken Raider, may draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.
front.lore: Leader of a Tusken Raider tribe. Unafraid of machines. Skilled hunter and marksman. Raids moisture farms for water. Roams the Jundland Wastes in search of unwary travelers.
front.title: •URoRRuR'R'R

front.gametext: May add 2 'riders' (passengers). Ability = ½. Adds 1 to power of each of your Tusken Raiders and other banthas present. When ridden by URoRRuR'R'R, adds one battle destiny.
front.lore: Raised by RR'uruurr for personal use by URoRRuR'R'R. Alpha male of his bantha herd. Has trampled many Jawas. Nicknamed 'Rrr'ur'R.
front.title: •URoRRuR'R'R's Bantha

front.gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on URoRRuR'R'R or Chief Bast, 3 on your non-droid character. May target a character or creature using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Subtract 1 if targeting a character. Add 2 if targeting a creature. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.
front.lore: Owning a hunting rifle is an important status symbol in Tusken culture. URoRRuR'R'R scavenged this weapon from a starship wreck near Anchorhead.
front.title: •URoRRuR'R'R's Hunting Rifle

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. While at Tusken Canyon, Jundland Wastes or same Tatooine site as UroRRuR'R'R, adds 2 to each of your battle destiny draws at Tatooine sites where you have a Tusken Raider.
front.lore: Fierce Tusken Raider. Ransacks homes and moisture farms on the borders of Mos Espa.
front.title: •Ur'Ru'r

cancels: Any Interrupt or Effect with 'Jawa' in the card name

front.gametext: If one of your Jawas is at the same location as any Utinni Effect, 'steal' that Utinni Effect into your hand, to use or lose as your own. OR Cancel any Interrupt or Effect with 'Jawa' in the card name.
front.lore: The Jawa who shot R2-D2 with an ionization gun called to his companions, 'Utinni!', the Jawa word for 'come here!'
front.title: Utinni!

combo: Vader + I Have You Now Add one battle destiny (two if Rebel is Luke) if a Dark Jedi and a Rebel with ability > 2 are involved in the same battle.
Vader + Force Field Cancels an attempt to target a Dark Jedi with a character weapon.

front.gametext: Must deploy on Death Star, but may move elsewhere. May not be deployed if two or more of opponent's unique (•) characters on table. If in a losing battle, draw destiny. If destiny > 4, 'choke' (lose) one Imperial present (your choice).
front.lore: Sought to extinguish all Jedi. Former student of Obi-Wan Kenobi. Seduced by the dark side of the Force.
front.title: •Vader

front.gametext: USED: Add 1 to your just-drawn lightsaber weapon destiny draw.  LOST: If a duel was just initiated, place the top card of your Used Pile on top of your Reserve Deck.
front.lore: Anger and aggression fuel the dark side of the Force.
front.title: •Vader's Anger

front.gametext: Vader follows (using landspeed for free) an opponent's character that just moved from same site. OR If Vader in battle alone, your total battle destiny is +1 for each character in battle. OR If Vader in battle, cancel Dodge, It's A Trap!, or Obi-Wan's Journal.
front.lore: Anger and aggression fuel the dark side of the Force.
front.title: •Vader's Anger (V)

rulings: Vader may only follow a character if their destination is within range of his landspeed.
Vader may even follow a character moving across his site.
Vader may not follow a vehicle, even if there is a character inside.
If Vader is aboard a vehicle, he may not disembark it to follow. The entire vehicle may not follow either.
Total battle destiny +1 counts all characters in the battle (including Vader).
If Dark did not successfully complete any battle destiny draws, there is no total battle destiny and so it is not possible for this Interrupt to add to total battle destiny.

front.gametext: Deploy on a Rebel of ability > 2. If subsequently captured, seized by a bounty hunter and then transferred to a prison where Vader is present, retrieve Force equal to character's forfeit (+4 if Luke) and lose Effect. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: 'We would be honored if you would join us.'
front.title: •Vader's Bounty

front.gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on one of your Imperials or aliens. Immune to attrition < 5. When in battle, adds 1 to each of your battle destiny draws.
front.lore: A symbol of the Dark Lord of the Sith, and of the seductive power of the dark side.
front.title: •Vader's Cape

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot. If Vader is pilot, Custom TIE is immune to attrition < 4.
front.lore: TIE advanced x1 prototype. First of a limited production run leading to the development of the TIE Interceptor. At Vader's insistence a hyperdrive was installed.
front.title: •Vader's Custom TIE

matching: Darth Vader, Dark Lord Of The Sith
pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot. Vader deploys -2 aboard. While Vader piloting, immune to attrition < 5, and during battle, may cancel game text of a passenger (or pilot of ability < 4) here.
front.lore: TIE advanced x1 prototype. First of a limited production run leading to the development of the TIE Interceptor. At Vader's insistence a hyperdrive was installed.
front.title: •Vader's Custom TIE (V)

matching: Darth Vader, Dark Lord Of The Sith
pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!
rulings: May only cancel the game text of a character card (not a permanent pilot or permanent passenger).
An astromech slot counts as a type of passenger slot. For example if the character card R2-D2 is in the astromech slot of the starship card Red 5, Vader's Custom TIE (V) can cancel R2-D2's game text.

front.gametext: If Vader is defending a battle alone at a site, add 1 to power and add one battle destiny. OR If any other Imperial with ability > 2 is defending a battle alone at a site, add one battle destiny.
front.lore: Darth Vader's armored mask and life-support system provide him with extraordinary physical protection in duels and battles, in addition to his Dark Jedi combat skill.
front.title: •Vader's Eye

underlyingCardFor: I Will Finish What You Started

front.gametext: Deploy on Vader. May add 1 to Force drain where present. May target a character or creature for free. Draw two destiny. Target hit, and its forfeit = 0, if total destiny > defense value.
front.lore: Custom-built by Darth Vader. After the Clone Wars, he wielded this weapon while hunting down the last of the Jedi. Cuts through almost anything except another lightsaber blade.
front.title: •Vader's Lightsaber

matchingWeapon: Darth Vader, Dark Lord Of The Sith
pulledBy: I Will Finish What You Started

front.gametext: During your move phase, if Vader moves to Luke's site from an adjacent site, begin a duel between them. Each adds two destiny to power. Winner retrieves lost Force equal to the difference. Loser loses same amount of Force, plus the character.
front.lore: Vader sought to hunt down and destroy all Jedi. After completing the circle with Obi-Wan, he turned his attention to the young Skywalker.
front.title: •Vader's Obsession

rulings: The destinies are 'duel destinies' (e.g. for The Ebb Of Battle or Deep Hatred).
Vader cannot duel a captive Luke (such as a Luke that's been captured via Bring Him Before Me or There Is Good In Him).

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot and 4 passengers. Permanent pilot aboard provides ability of 2. Moves for free. While Vader aboard, opponent must have ability > 5 to draw battle destiny at same system. May not Talon Roll.
front.lore: Customized transport of Lord Vader. Employs advanced sensor jamming gear. Modified with enhanced tactical displays constructed to the Dark Lord's specifications.
front.title: •Vader's Personal Shuttle

matching: Darth Vader, Dark Lord Of The Sith
underlyingCardFor: Colonel Jendon In Vader's Personal Shuttle

cancels: You lose no force to Uncontrollable Fury or You Must Confront Vader
cards.conceptBy: (Original concept by Nate Meeker - World Champion 2006)

front.gametext: May add 2 pilots and 4 passengers. Vader deploys -3 aboard. While Vader piloting at a battleground, maneuver +2 and you lose no Force to Uncontrollable Fury or You Must Confront Vader.
front.lore: Customized transport of Lord Vader. Employs advanced sensor jamming gear. Modified with enhanced tactical displays constructed to the Dark Lord's specifications.
front.title: •Vader's Personal Shuttle (V)

matching: Darth Vader, Dark Lord Of The Sith
pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!

front.gametext: Deploys -3 to a site with 'Vader' in game text. Once during your turn, may activate 1 Force. Once per game, may take a card with 'Vader' in title into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Blank.
front.title: •Vanee

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. During your control phase, if at a Jabba's Palace site, may use 2 Force to make a 'wager'. Both players draw one destiny. Player with lower number loses 1 Force.
front.lore: Kajain'sa'Nikto scout. Sold by his family into slavery to Jabba. Gambler. Plays sabacc with his fellow Nikto.
front.title: •Vedain

front.gametext: Must deploy on Hoth, but may move elsewhere. May not be deployed if three or more of opponent's unique (•) characters on table. Snowtroopers at same site are forfeit +1.
front.lore: General of the AT-AT assault armor division sent by Darth Vader to crush the Rebellion on Hoth. Cold and ruthless.
front.title: •Veers

front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. Leader. Once per turn, may reveal from hand to deploy 6th Marker or Blizzard 1 to Hoth from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Deploys free aboard Blizzard 1. While piloting Blizzard 1, adds one destiny to total power.
front.lore: General of the AT-AT assault armor division sent by Darth Vader to crush the Rebellion on Hoth. Cold and ruthless.
front.title: •Veers (V)

front.gametext: Deploy at same exterior site as your mining droid. 'Explodes' if starfighter (use 5 as defense value) or non-creature vehicle deploys or moves to or across same site. Draw destiny. Target lost if destiny +2 > defense value. Vehicle Mine is also lost.
front.lore: Launches and detonates when activated by a passing metallic mass or the repulsorlift field of an approaching speeder. The shrapnel can hit even the quickest craft.
front.title: Vehicle Mine

front.gametext: When at a site you control, allows your Seekers to deploy free there. Also allows your Seekers to move for free and to ignore any or all potential target(s) whenever you choose.
front.lore: Assigned by Jabba to work with Hermi Odle. Former technician for the Empire. Developed a method to remotely control seekers. Plotting to kill Jabba.
front.title: •Velken Tezeri

front.gametext: Adds 2 to the power of anything he pilots. Smuggler. While present at a pit, adds 1 to your Force drains here. Unless 'hit' (or Gamall Wironicc here), your other characters here may not be targeted by lightsabers. May not target Luke with weapons.
front.lore: Assigned by Jabba to work with Hermi Odle. Former technician for the Empire. Developed a method to remotely control seekers. Plotting to kill Jabba.
front.title: •Velken Tezeri (V)

combo: Vengeance + Imperial Helmsman Draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

front.gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 1 vehicle and 6 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. Your TIE/lns are forfeit +2 at same location. Power +2 at Nal Hutta.
front.lore: Part of Darth Vader's Death Squadron. Support vessel for the fleet's starfighters. Cargo areas converted into hangar space for additional TIE fighters.
front.title: •Vengeance

front.gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 1 vehicle, and 6 TIEs. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. Whenever you win a battle here, opponent loses 1 Force.
front.lore: Part of Darth Vader's Death Squadron. Support vessel for the fleet's starfighters. Cargo areas converted into hangar space for additional TIE fighters.
front.title: •Vengeance (V)

front.gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on any alien warrior. Adds 1 to power. May target a character using 1 Force. Both players draw destiny. Target immediately excluded from battle if warrior's power + your destiny > target's power + opponent's destiny.
front.lore: SoroSuub BD-1 Cutter vibro-ax. Powered by an ultrasonic generator concealed in the shaft. Jabba's skiff guards use them to prod victims into the Sarlacc's nest.
front.title: Vibro-Ax

rulings: The destiny drawn by the owner of Vibro-Ax is a weapon destiny.
The destiny drawn by the owner of the targeted character is <u>not</u> a weapon destiny.

combo: Victory-Class Star Destroyer + Imperial Helmsman Draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

front.gametext: May add 4 pilots, 6 passengers, 1 vehicle and 3 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. Adds 1 to your total power in battles at related planet sites.
front.lore: Commissioned by the Old Republic at end of the Clone Wars, Rendili StarDrive's Victory-class starship is atmosphere-capable but has a low sublight speed.
front.title: Victory-Class Star Destroyer

front.gametext: Deploys for free on Coruscant. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. While at a non-Coruscant battleground site and Vengeance Of The Dark Prince is on table, Force drain +1 here. Forfeit +2 when present with Xizor or another Vigo.
front.lore: One of Xizor's hand-picked lieutenants. Ascended as Black Sun agent from gangster to manager. Earned title of Vigo from old Tionese for 'nephew'.
front.title: •••Vigo

front.gametext: Deploys -1 to Coruscant. While present with Xizor, forfeit +2 and opponent's spies may not deploy to same non-battleground site. Once per game, may use 1 Force to deploy a non-war room battleground planet site (or system) not already on table from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: One of Xizor's hand-picked lieutenants. Ascended as Black Sun agent from gangster to manager. Earned title of Vigo from old Tionese for 'nephew'.
front.title: •••Vigo (V)

pulls: Battleground planet site or system (except a war room)

front.gametext: Habitat: planet sites (except Hoth). Attacks a character by attaching. X starts at 0. Every move phase, draw destiny; each time destiny > ability, add 1 to X. Character is power -X (eaten if power = 0).
front.lore: Found on various planets throughout the galaxy. Hides among hanging vines, dropping on unsuspecting travelers that pass beneath. Kills its victims through gradual constriction.
front.title: Vine Snake

front.gametext: Permanent Pilot provides 1 ability. May add Xizor as pilot (suspends permanent pilot). Xizor deploys -3 aboard. When Xizor piloting, adds one battle destiny and immune to attrition < 5.
front.lore: Prototype designed by MandalMotors to Prince Xizor's exacting specifications. Contains four separate power generators to power advanced flight controls and engines.
front.title: •Virago

combo: Visage + Imperial Helmsman Draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.

front.gametext: May deploy even with out presence or Force icons (except to Rendezvous Point).  May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles and 4 TIEs.  Has ship-docking capability.  Permanent pilot provides ability of 1.
front.lore: Outfitted to chart unknown expanses of Outer Rim. Staff includes galactic cartography contingent. Considered a joke assignment by most lower-ranked Naval officers.
front.title: •Visage

front.gametext: Lose 2 Force to deploy on Executor: Holotheatre or Death Star: Conference Room. At the end of each player's turn, each player must lost 1 Force. Effect canceled if opponent controls this site. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Palpatine's hologram. Imposing. Ominous. Intimidating. Instrument for the evil Emperor's sinister reach across the galaxy. Used on a secret frequency of the Imperial HoloNet.
front.title: •Visage Of The Emperor

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. Power +3 when defending a battle. If with your Advosze during your control phase, may search Reserve Deck, take one vehicle weapon into hand and reshuffle. Your vehicle weapons deploy free at same site.
front.lore: Kajain'sa'Nikto. Keeps Jabba's vehicles and starships well armed. Has hidden several weapon caches on board Jabba's sail barge.
front.title: •Vizam

front.gametext: During your control phase, draw destiny. If destiny > 2, draw up to X cards (maximum 4) from Reserve Deck, where X = your total politics at Galactic Senate minus opponent's total politics at Galactic Senate.
front.lore: With enough political support, any number of devious plans can be put into motion.
front.title: •Vote Now!

front.gametext: Plays on table. While you have 12 or fewer cards in hand, opponent may not remove cards from your hand (except with Grimtaash). Once per turn (even at start of turn), may target a [Coruscant] Political Effect; it is suspended for the remainder of the turn.
front.lore: Blank.
front.title: •Vote Of No Confidence

combo: Voyeur + Trinto Duaba + Dune Sea Sabacc (or any Sabacc really) Play Sabacc to get cards in their used pile, then the other 2 Interrupts to make them lose force/other cards. (maxbeedo)

front.gametext: Name an Interrupt card. Opponent must reveal entire Used Pile, without shuffling. Then you choose:USED: Opponent must lose 1 Force for each copy of that Interrupt found there.  LOST: Each copy of that interrupt found there is lost.
front.lore: As there are very few local authorities on Dagobah, peeping Nav Computers can get away with just about anything.
front.title: ••Voyeur

combo: Wakeelmui + Sienar Fleet Systems Retrieve 1 Force each time you deploy a TIE. Once per turn may relocate a TIE just lost from table to Used Pile.

front.gametext: Dark:  If Kuat is on table, Force generation +2 for you here.  Light:  If you occupy, all TIEs deploy +1 (+2 if you control). Your movement to here requires +1 Force.
front.title: •Wakeelmui

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

front.gametext: If you have a piloted AT-AT present at a site, target opponent's artillery weapon at same or adjacent exterior site. Draw destiny. Target lost if destiny +1 > forfeit. Also, one opponent's character at same site as target (random selection) lost if destiny +1 > 6.
front.lore: Before an AT-AT's troops can disembark to engage the enemy, the walker must first destroy the Rebel traitors' defensive emplacements.
front.title: Walker Barrage

front.gametext: If Veers is at an exterior Hoth site, use 2 Force to search your Reserve Deck and take one AT-AT into your hand. OR If you have 3 AT-ATs at three different Hoth sites, your Force drains are +2 at Hoth locations this turn.
front.lore: When efficiently deployed, a squadron of AT-ATs can quickly take control of a wide area, making it easy for imperial forces to dominate a planet.
front.title: Walker Garrison

front.gametext: If you have a piloted AT-AT present at a site, target any number of opponent's troopers present at same or adjacent exterior site. Draw destiny. If destiny > number of troopers targeted, they are lost.
front.lore: Walkers are capable of incinerating entire infantry units in seconds. Rebel troops refer to the deadly barrage as the 'wall of fire.'
front.title: Wall Of Fire

combo: Wampa + Cold Feet

front.gametext: * Ferocity = 3 + destiny. Habitat: Hoth sites. Deploy only to Wampa Cave or unoccupied marker site. Defeated characters are eaten or relocated to Wampa Cave (opponent of victim chooses).
front.lore: Sly, carnivorous beast which stalks the snow-packed tundra. Wampas frequently drag their prey to an ice cave for storage. They always prefer to devour their victims alive.
front.title: Wampa

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. May use 1 Force to take one tractor beam, Our First Catch Of The Day or Besieged into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Hard-working Avenger signal officer. Coordinates and tests tractor beam operations. Apprises Executor of his ship's activities and relays orders from the flagship to his captain.
front.title: •Warrant Officer M'Kae

pulls: Our First Catch Of The Day

front.gametext: During a battle at a system or sector, if you are about to draw a card for battle destiny, you may instead use the maneuver number of your starfighter in that battle.
front.lore: 'Fighters above you, coming in!'
front.title: •Watch Your Back!

front.gametext: May 'fly' (landspeed = 2). Once during each of your turns, may take Watto's Chance Cube into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Toydarian junk dealer. Skilled gambler. Won Shmi and Anakin in a Podrace bet with Gardulla the Hutt. Jedi mind tricks don't work on him, only money.
front.title: •Watto

front.gametext: May 'fly' (landspeed = 2). Once during each of your turns, may take Watto's Chance Cube into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Toydarian junk dealer. Skilled gambler. Won Shmi and Anakin in a Podrace bet with Gardulla the Hutt. Jedi mind tricks don't work on him, only money.
front.title: •Watto (AI)

front.gametext: Deploy on table if all of your race totals = 0. When a player wins a Podrace, adds 5 to the amount retrieved. When a player loses a Podrace, adds 5 to the amount lost. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Fortunes are won and lost every day on the Outer Rim. Watto is a master at getting his cut.
front.title: •Watto's Box

front.gametext: If Watto is in a battle at a site, draw destiny. If destiny is odd, your total battle destiny = 0 this battle. If destiny is even, add two battle destiny.
front.lore: 'We'll let fate decide, huh?'
front.title: •Watto's Chance Cube

rulings: Zero is an even number.
If the destiny is not a whole number (e.g. a card with destiny 0.5), it is neither even nor odd, so no result.

combo: We Have A Prisoner + Corporal Vandolay Corporal Vandolay makes We Have A Prisoner a Used Interrupt while at a mobile site

front.gametext: Use 1 Force if opponent's character is about to be lost or forfeited from battle. It is captured instead (character is first restored to normal). OR Use X Force to capture all characters on board a captured starship, where X = twice the number of characters.
front.lore: 'You are part of the Rebel Alliance, and a traitor. Take her away!'
front.title: We Have A Prisoner

cards.counterpart: We Wish To Board At Once

front.gametext: Use 3 Force to take one Effect of any kind into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. OR Deploy a Blockade Flagship site from your Reserve Deck; reshuffle. OR Take one Interrupt with the word 'Podracer(s)' in it's game text into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: 'This turn of events is unfortunate.'
front.title: •We Must Accelerate Our Plans

pulls: One Interrupt with Podracer(s) in game text

combo: Operational as Planned + Desperate Counter + Combat Response + Major Mianda or Scythe 3 + SFS L-s7.2 TIE Cannon + We Shall Double Our Efforts!

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Adds 1 to X on That Thing's Operational. At Death Star II sectors, opponent's starfighters are maneuver -5. When opponent is attempting to 'blow away' Death Star II, subtract 2 from opponent's total. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: 'I hope so, Commander, for your sake...'
front.title: •We Shall Double Our Efforts!

combo: Weapon Levitation  Control = Who said anything about 'Sense' ?
Weapon Levitation + opponent's Polarized Negative Power Coupling = You SEE your Used Pile, you know what cards go there.
Weapon Levitation + many weapon cards in your deck = many weapons on the table fast, destiny 4 card recycled each time.
Weapon Levitation + many characters of ability >3 = You do not need your own weapons if you have enough Weapon Levitations.

front.gametext: USED: Search your Used Pile, take one weapon into hand and reshuffle.  LOST: If a battle was just initiated, one of your characters of ability > 3 present may 'steal' one character weapon present.
front.lore: Vader confiscated Han's blaster, his ship, his Wookiee, his girl and his only hope of escape.
front.title: •Weapon Levitation

front.gametext: Deploy on any docking bay. Target a weapon deployed on a starfighter or vehicle. That weapon cannot be fired. Utinni Effect canceled when reached by target.
front.lore: 'Luke, we've got a malfunction in fire control. I'll have to cut in the auxiliary.'
front.title: •Weapon Malfunction

cards.counterpart: Only Jedi Carry That Weapon - Defensive Shield

front.gametext: Plays on table. For opponent to steal a weapon from target character using a non-[Episode I] card, must first draw destiny. If destiny +1 > target's ability, weapon is stolen. Otherwise, attempt fails and stealing card is placed out of play.
front.lore: In order to use his double-bladed weapon Maul trained under Darth Sidious for years.
front.title: •Weapon Of A Sith

front.gametext: USED: If a lightsaber was just used to enhance a Force drain, place it in owner's Used Pile.  LOST: Place any or all of you devices and character weapons on table in your Used Pile.
front.lore: When Vader dueled Luke at Cloud City, he fought a son trained by his former master and a weapon constructed by his former self.
front.title: •Weapon Of An Ungrateful Son

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Any character here may be captured or rescued by a player's starship or vehicle controlling Cloud City during that player's control phase. Character here lost if new character arrives. Effect lost if Cloud City lost. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Not a good place to hang around.
front.title: •Weather Vane

front.gametext: Adds immunity to attrition < 2 to all your vehicles and droids at same location. Also, if 'treadwell' droid is at a docking bay, adds immunity to attrition < 3 to all your starfighters at the related system and related sectors.
front.lore: Standard treadwell droid. This one, also known as 'Eyesixsixtoo', is typical of the thousands of droids which repair and maintain heavy machinery and starfighters.
front.title: WED15-I662 'Treadwell' Droid

front.gametext: * Forfeit value begins at 7. When 'forfeited,' droid remains in play, but forfeit value is reduced by the amount of attrition or battle damage absorbed. Droid lost when forfeit value reaches zero.
front.lore: Multi-armed maintenance droid fiercely loyal to the Empire. Specializes in extending effective operational life of Imperial resources. Nicknamed for an insect from Eriadu.
front.title: •WED15-l7 'Septoid' Droid

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. Deploy -1 to same site as any Weequay. When at same site as any Weequay, (except Weequay Guards), may draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.
front.lore: Weequay are extremely fierce warriors. Species name means, 'follower of Quay'. Very religious. Communicate through pheromones. Smell really bad.
front.title: •••Weequay Guard

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. When present at the start of a battle, may sacrifice (lose) one of your Banthas present: adds 2 to power of each Weequay there for remainder of turn. (May not sacrifice if Tusken Raiders present outnumber Weequay present).
front.lore: To maintain religious practices, Weequay hunters capture banthas. The beasts are then sacrificed as part of a battle ceremony. Tusken Raiders tend not to appreciate this.
front.title: •••Weequay Hunter

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. May fire one weapon during your control phase (at double use of Force). May use 2 Force to 'assassinate' any character just 'hit' by Weequay Marksman (victim is immediately lost).
front.lore: Patient and quiet. Jabba uses many of his Weequay henchmen as assassins. Use womp rats for target practice during their religious ceremonies.
front.title: •••Weequay Marksman

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. Power +2 When defending a battle or when with another Weequay in battle. Adds 3 to power of any Skiff he drives.
front.lore: Many of the Weequay at Jabba's palace work for Barada. Enjoy racing their skiffs. Dislike the Nikto guards at Jabba's palace.
front.title: •••Weequay Skiff Master

front.gametext: Deploy on your side of table. While you have fewer than 13 cards in your hand, your non-unique cards in hand (except effects of any kind and any interrupts) are immune to Grimtaash. (Immune to Alter while you occupy 2 battlegrounds).
front.lore: Most of Jabba's guards had been sold to the Hutt and were too scared (or too dumb) to leave. Jabba assigned his best guards to watch over his most prized possessions.
front.title: •Well Guarded

front.gametext: Plays on table. Cancels Frozen Assets and Beggar. Each player may play only one card with 'sabacc' in title each turn. You may cancel an opponent's card with 'sabacc' in title by losing 1 Force from hand.
front.lore: Qui-Gon was not one to leave the success of an elaborate plan to chance.
front.title: •We'll Let Fate-a Decide, Huh?

front.gametext: Deploy on your general or commander. When battling, adds 1 to your total battle destiny (or 2 if Igar). Once during each of your control phases, may take one Imperial Propaganda into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Your Force drains are +1 at holosites.
front.lore: Imperial officers often simulate large-scale battles with hologram games to improve their tactical ability. Those who excel at these games often mark themselves for advancement.
front.title: •Well-earned Command

pulledBy: You Cannot Hide Forever & Mobilization Points

front.gametext: Everything in Trash Compactor is crushed (lost).
front.lore: Trash compactors crush waste before it is jettisoned into space. Magnetically sealed to prevent leakage. R2-D2 saved the day by shutting down compactor 3263827.
front.title: We're All Gonna Be A Lot Thinner!

front.gametext: Once during battle, target a participating starfighter present with your droid starfighter. Draw destiny. If destiny > target's defense value, target 'hit.' OR If opponent's starfighter was just 'hit' where your droid starfighter is present, activate up to 4 Force.
front.lore: Complex recursive algorithms are used by Trade Federation starships to seek out and destroy enemies within targeting range.
front.title: ••We're Hit, Artoo

front.gametext: Each pilot deploys -1 (or -2 if an admiral) aboard a capital starship.  Each capital starship with a pilot character aboard is immune to attrition < 4 (or adds 2 to immunity if starship already has immunity).  During each of your control phases, opponent loses 1 Force for each battleground site your general or commander controls that is related to a system you occupy.
front.title: •We're In Attack Position Now

front.gametext: Deploy on Han, Leia or Chewie if captured or 'frozen.' Target Luke. Luke may not attempt Jedi Tests. Also, during each of opponent's draw phases, opponent loses 2 Force (3 if captive is 'frozen'). Utinni Effect canceled when reached by target. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: 'He doesn't want you at all, he's after somebody called, uh...Skywalker.' 'Luke?' 'Lord Vader has set a trap for him.' 'And we're that bait!' 'Yeah, well, he's on his way.'
front.title: •We're The Bait

front.gametext: Deploy on table. While no card here, may cancel a Force drain by placing a non-unique destroyer droid here from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. During your deploy phase, may use 5 Force to deploy (for free) a destroyer droid from here, as if from hand.
front.lore: When two Jedi are attempting to breach your bridge, even a destroyer droid's response time seems far too slow.
front.title: •Where Are Those Droidekas?!

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Non-unique destroyer droids are deploy -1 and forfeit +1. While all your characters at sites are destroyer droids and Neimoidians, opponent's characters are defense value -1 (to a minimum of 3) for each destroyer droid present. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: When two Jedi are attempting to breach your bridge, even a destroyer droid's response time seems far too slow.
front.title: •Where Are Those Droidekas?! (V)

front.gametext: Power +2 on Hoth. Forfeit +2 under nighttime conditions. When at a site, if opponent cancels Sunsdown at the related system, causes Effect to go to Used Pile, and you may retrieve 2 Force.
front.lore: Whipids originate from Toola in the Kaelta system, a planet extremely distant from its sun. Accustomed to hunting for prey in the near dark and the bitter cold.
front.title: Whiphid

combo: Why Didn't You Tell Me? + cheap characters of 2 Power, such as DS-61-2 = One of the more annoying things that happens in a game is when your opponent notices you've played a 2 Power pilot and sacrifices Yoda. Why Didn't You Tell Me? gets rid of that fairly easily.

front.gametext: USED: Cancel Noble Sacrifice, Gift Of The Mentor or Old Ben.  LOST: If Luke is defending a battle, draw one destiny. Subtract that amount from opponent's attrition and total power (cannot fall below zero).
front.lore: Lacking foresight, Luke suffered the consequences of rushing into battle unprepared.
front.title: •Why Didn't You Tell Me?

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Once during each of opponent's turns, if you occupy a battleground site, may activate 1 Force. While opponent has a non-unique alien or non-unique starfighter in battle, opponent may not draw more than two battle destiny. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Darth Sidious' command was merciless and direct. He left no room for misinterpretation.
front.title: •Wipe Them Out, All Of Them

front.gametext: Plays on table. While opponent has a non-unique alien or non-unique starfighter in battle, opponent may not draw more than two battle destiny.
front.lore: Darth Sidious' command was merciless and direct. He left no room for misinterpretation.
front.title: •Wipe Them Out, All Of Them

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. Your Jawa Pack is not unique, is doubled, deploys free (or for 6 Force from each player) and cumulatively affects your Jawa's forfeit. While at Audience Chamber or Jawa Camp, all your other Jawas are power +2.
front.lore: Male Jawa. Leader of a large tribe of Jawas. Plotting with Jabba to take control of a neighboring tribe's territory.
front.title: •Wittin

pulledBy: Herat to deploy to same location

front.gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. May add 1 driver and 7 passengers. While your Jawa is aboard, this vehicle and your Jawas at same site are immune to attrition < 3. Power +2 if Wittin at same site.
front.lore: Patrols the Dune Sea searching for lost droids and other items worth scavenging. Armor reinforced to protect against krayt dragon attacks. Enclosed.
front.title: •Wittin's Sandcrawler

front.gametext: * Ferocity = destiny. Habitat: exterior planet sites. Ferocity +1 for each other womp rat at same site. Lost if 'bullseyed' by Luke's T-16 Skyhopper present.
front.lore: Carnivorous rodents. Typically found in Beggar's Canyon. About the size of an average thermal exhaust port.
front.title: •••Womp Rat

front.gametext: Deploys only at Tatooine. Power +2 when defending a battle at a Jabba's Palace site. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots (3 if piloting an [Independent Starship] starship or if Jabba is aboard).
front.lore: Kadas'sa'Nikto. One of Jabba's best pilots. Often pilots Jabba's space yacht. Smuggler. Prefers to be flying combat starfighters.
front.title: •Wooof

front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. May deploy with any cruiser using Combat Response. While aboard a piloted [Independent] starship, opponent's battle and weapon destiny draws here are -1.
front.lore: Kadas'sa'Nikto. One of Jabba's best pilots. Often pilots Jabba's space yacht. Smuggler. Prefers to be flying combat starfighters.
front.title: •Wooof (V)

cancels: Leia's game text for remainder of turn
combo: Prince Xizor - Prevent battle destiny draws by getting opponent under 6 ability.

front.gametext: Cancel Leia's game text for remainder of turn. OR If your weapon (except a lightsaber) just 'hit' an opponent's character, for remainder of turn that character is power = 0 and may not apply ability toward drawing battle destiny.
front.lore: 'Oh, Princess Leia, are you all right?'
front.title: •Wounded Warrior

front.gametext: During a battle, if opponent drew more than two battle destiny, cancel all but two of those destiny draws (your choice). OR If your non-unique alien is in a battle, cancel game text of one Rebel present for remainder of turn. OR Cancel Clash Of Sabers.
front.lore: When blaster fire from the barge's gun hit Chewie's skiff, his leg was injured by shrapnel. This setback distracted the Rebels, causing them to momentarily lose their advantage.
front.title: •Wounded Wookiee

rulings: May be played in response to any opponent's battle destiny draw except the first two draws (if played 'early' it does not affect the subsequent draws).

When counting how many battle destinies the opponent has drawn so far, count all battle destiny draws, even canceled ones. Then choose 2 non-canceled draws to remain non-canceled, and cancel the rest.
After playing this Interrupt, it is too late to then play a response to an individual destiny draw (e.g. you cannot cancel all but 2 draws, then use Grand Moff Tarkin to cancel another).
If opponent had a 'Draw X and Choose Y destinies' scenario, only the chosen destinies are counted and targeted; the others are ignored entirely.

front.gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on opponent's side of table. All opponent's warriors are deploy +1.
front.lore: Imperial troopers use tactics to strand and cut off fugitives. Only daring and unpredictable actions gave Luke and Leia a chance to escape.
front.title: •Wrong Turn

front.gametext: If at the beginning of your control phase any weapons or droids are present at same site, all of them are lost. If in the Cantina, all weapons and droids there are immediately lost.
front.lore: Gruff, surly, no-blasters-allowed bartender. Hates droids. 'We don't serve their kind here.' Wants to concoct the perfect drink for Jabba so he can work as his personal bartender.
front.title: •Wuher

front.gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on opponent's just deployed character at same site as a Black Sun agent; character may not battle this turn. If character is about to leave table or be captured, peek at opponent's hand, retrieve 1 Force, and lose this Immediate Effect.
front.title: •Xizor's Bounty

rulings: The Force retrieval is not considered to be 'collecting a bounty' such as for Thermal Detonator.

front.gametext: Dark:  Once per game, may exchange an alien in hand with a non-spy Black Sun agent in Lost Pile.  Light:  Once per game, if you control, may retrieve a Corellian.
front.title: •Xizor's Palace: Sewer

front.gametext: Dark:  If Falleen's Fist at Coruscant and your Black Sun agent here, Force drain +1 here.  Light:
front.title: •Xizor's Palace: Uplink Station

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Once per turn, may take a just drawn race destiny into hand. Once during a battle Yade is in at a system may use 2 Force to draw destiny. If destiny is odd, add one battle destiny; if even, destiny into hand.
front.lore: Corellian gambler with an addiction to Podrace betting. Has lost most of his belongings to Gardulla. Still operates as a smuggler of black market weaponry.
front.title: •Yade M'rak

rulings: Zero is an even number.
If the destiny is not a whole number (e.g. a card with destiny 0.5), it is neither even nor odd, so no result.
When the draw is even, Yade takes that same even-numbered destiny card into hand (not a new destiny draw).

front.gametext: Target a creature vehicle at same site as a creature. If ferocity > target's maneuver + landspeed, creature vehicle is eaten, cumulatively adding 2 to creature's ferocity.
front.lore: 'Steady. Hey! Steady, girl. Hey, what's the matter? You smell something?'
front.title: Yaggle Gakkle

front.gametext: Dark:  If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Yavin 4 sites.  Light:  If you control, for each of your starships here, your total power is +1 in battles at Yavin 4 sites.
front.title: •Yavin 4

front.gametext: Dark:  Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force.  Light:  Your docking bay transit from here requires 1 Force.
front.title: •Yavin 4: Docking Bay

front.gametext: Dark:  An Imperial alone here battles at power +2 and is immune to attrition.  Light:
front.title: •Yavin 4: Jungle

combo: Yeb Yeb Adem'thorn + senate majority + a 6 on opponent's Reserve Deck Not any more...
Yeb Yeb Adem'thorn + senate majority + only one card in opponent's Reserve Deck No destiny for your opponent!
Yeb Yeb Adem'thorn + Rune Haako Destiny of zero for your opponent. (Lord Helmet)

front.gametext: Agendas: trade, wealth. While in a senate majority, once during your turn, may peek at top card of opponent's Reserve Deck; return that card or lose 1 Force to make it lost.
front.lore: Senator who opposes the taxation of trade routes. Some say that a recent move from his homeworld to a luxurious Coruscant abode is evidence of his corruption.
front.title: •Yeb Yeb Adem'thorn

canceledBy: Twilight Is Upon Me (unless canceling Uncontrollable Fury)

front.gametext: Use 2 Force to target a character present with your warrior with a lightsaber. Target cannot move or battle until end of your next turn. OR Use 1 Force to search your Reserve Deck, take one I Am Your Father into hand and reshuffle. OR cancel Uncontrollable Fury.
front.lore: 'It is useless to resist. Don't let yourself be destroyed as Obi-Wan did.'
front.title: •You Are Beaten

rulings: Works with a character with a permanent lightsaber weapon (even if their game text has been canceled).

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Opponent's Jedi are defense value -1. Never Tell Me The Odds is canceled. You may place Effect in Lost Pile to take one [Endor] or [Death Star II] Effect that deploys for free into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. (Immune to Alter.)
