front.lore: General Veers' AT-AT. Enclosed. Equipped with highly sophisticated communications gear. Employs an experimental targeting system.
front.title: •Blizzard 1 (V)

rulings: Immune to Under Attack and attrition < 4 does not require Veers piloting (but does require Blizzard 1 be piloted).

front.gametext: Once during battle, may use 1 Force to make Burg power +2 for remainder of turn. Once during battle, opponent may use 1 Force to make Burg power -2 for remainder of turn. At the end of each of your turns, use 1 Force or place Burg in Used Pile.
front.lore: Devaronian mercenary.
front.title: •Burg

rulings: Both players may use Burg's text in the same battle, for a net result of +0 power.
Burg's end of turn text occurs after recirculating.

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots (3 if Avenger). Once per game, may take Apology Accepted into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. While out of play, your total battle destiny is +1 where you have an Imperial captain. If just lost, place him out of play.
front.lore: Able leader and captain of the Avenger. Was given his command by Admiral Ozzel. Treated with suspicion by Darth Vader and the Emperor, who distrust Ozzel's close advisors.
front.title: •Captain Needa (V)

rulings: Needa's text only places himself out of play if just lost from table (not from hand or Life Force).

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Rebel Barrier is a Lost Interrupt. If opponent just canceled a battle (or just moved a character, starship, or vehicle away from a battle), opponent loses 1 Force. If Landing Claw just lost, place it out of play.
front.lore: Imperial stormtroopers adopt strict security measures. Excellent communications and sheer numbers can hinder Rebel movement across entire territories.
front.title: •Close The Blast Doors!

rulings: To determine who canceled a battle, look at the owner of the card that canceled it (e.g. Projective Telepathy is Dark canceling a battle).
Excluding a character, which subsequently results in a battle ending immediately, is not a player canceling a battle.

front.gametext: While present at Galactic Senate, all characters without politics here are forfeit = 0 (except Coruscant Guards) and neither player may draw more than one battle destiny here.
front.lore: Coruscant Guards are an elite force whose assignments include the protection of important political figures, as well as the policing of Coruscant's higher profile city districts.
front.title: Coruscant Guard (V)

rulings: If a player has 'Draws two battle destiny if unable to otherwise' then they may still draw two.

front.gametext: During your deploy phase, a unique (•) Imperial of ability < 3 here may make a regular move. When deployed, may place a unique (•) ISB agent here in Used Pile to deploy (for free) a non-Tarkin ISB agent with a different title here from Used Pile; reshuffle.
front.lore: ISB leader.
front.title: •Deputy Director Harus Ison

rulings: May even place himself in Used Pile for his 'When deployed' action.

front.gametext: Dark: If Imperials control three battlegrounds, Force drain +1 here.  Light: If Tarkin here, your starships deploy +1 here.
front.title: •Eriadu (V)

front.gametext: If deployed to a site where opponent has more than four characters, opponent loses 2 Force. Jedi here are defense value -1 for each of your Mandalorians here. While armed (or with a Mandalorian), opponent may not move away from (or cancel) battles here.
front.lore: Mandalorian leader. Death Watch assassin.
front.title: •Gar Saxon

rulings: Cannot use Hidden Weapons.
Note the second sentence looks for your Mandalorian, but the third sentence looks for any Mandalorian.
(Third sentence) When his condition is met during battle, blocks all types of opponent's movement away from the location, including relocating (e.g. Path Of Least Resistance).

front.gametext: During battle with an information broker (or during an attack), adds one destiny to total power. Once per game, may deploy a creature (or a blaster or rifle without 'lost' in game text) here from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Dowutin mercenary.
front.title: •Grummgar

pulls: A blaster without 'lost' in game text
A rifle without 'lost' in game text
rulings: Grummgar must be participating in the attack to add a destiny to power.
An information broker is needed during battle, not during an attack.

front.gametext: Dark:  AT-ATs move to and from here for free. During your first turn, AT-ATs may not deploy here.  Light: T-47s are power +1 here. If you have two piloted T-47s here, Force drain +1 here.
front.title: •Hoth: North Ridge (4th Marker) (V)

rulings: Regardless of who goes first in the game, AT-ATs may not deploy here during Dark's first turn of the game.

front.gametext: Once during opponent's turn, if with an Imperial on Cloud City, may activate 1 Force. Once during your turn, if with an alien on Cloud City, may draw top card of Reserve Deck. Once per game, may place a non-[Immune to Alter] Effect in owner's Used Pile.
front.lore: Scoundrel and gambler. Petty administrator of a small Tibanna gas mining operation. Easily coerced. Has problems of his own. Had dealings with the Tonnika sisters - twice.
front.title: •Lando Calrissian, Vader's Broker

rulings: May be deployed even if opponent's Lando is also on table, and vice versa.
Cards that target Lando (without specifying whose) may target either player's Lando.
The phrase 'on Cloud City' means at a Cloud City site, not the Bespin: Cloud City sector.

front.gametext: Dark:  [Set 13] Maul ignores [Set 13] objective deployment restrictions here.  Light: Opponent's weapons here may not target Ezra.
front.title: •Malachor: Sith Temple Gateway

rulings: Allows Set 13 Maul to deploy here even if Dark is playing the Set 13 objective Hunt Down And Destroy The Jedi (V).
No special interaction with the Set 13 objective Shadow Collective, as Set 13 Maul could deploy regardless in that case.

front.gametext: LOST: Deploy Kessel or [Set 17] Eriadu from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. STARTING: If Ralltiir Operations on table, deploy Insignificant Rebellion and up to two Effects that deploy on table, deploy for free, and are always immune to Alter. Place Interrupt in hand.
front.lore: A ruthless ruler of Outer Rim Territories. Grand Moff Tarkin used the Death Star to destroy Alderaan, creating the doctrine of rule by fear.
front.title: •Moment Of Triumph (V)

rulings: Works with Ralltir Operations or Ralltir Operations (V).
Can deploy any version of Insignificant Rebellion (even if it is not normally free).

front.gametext: During battle, may place an Imperial of ability < 4 from your Lost Pile out of play to add X to attrition against opponent, where X = that character's ability. Except during battle, may lose Valin Hess to target an opponent's Undercover spy here; target is lost.
front.lore: Leader.
front.title: •Officer Valin Hess

rulings: Placing an Imperial out of play to add to attrition occurs during the power segment, after all destinies have been drawn.
An Imperial cannot be placed out of play if there is no attrition (no battle destiny was drawn, or the draws were all canceled).
If the undercover spy is somehow prevented from being lost (e.g. Droid Shutdown), Hess is still lost.

front.gametext: Agendas: ambition, taxation. While in a senate majority, if your only [Coruscant] Political Effect on table is not This Is Outrageous!, it may not be canceled or suspended. Argente is politics +X, where X = number of opponent's characters here.
front.lore: A senator known for his ability to deflect blame. It is rumored that Argente receives kickbacks from a few corporations to thwart other companies' developments.
front.title: •Passel Argente (V)

rulings: Deploying Passel does not unsuspend an already suspended political effect.
If there are 2 political effects but one is suspended, Passel will protect the active political effect (unless it is This Is Outrageous).

front.gametext: When forfeited at same location as Han or Vos, may satisfy all remaining battle damage against you. Unless opponent occupies a battleground site, doubles X on Secret Plans and cancels It Could Be Worse.
front.lore: Female Crimson Dawn leader. Corellian gangster.
front.title: •Qi'ra, Top Lieutenant

rulings: Doubles X on Secret Plans means (for example) to retrieve 2 Force, Light must use 4 Force (instead of 2).

cards.counterpart: The Force Is Strong In My Family

front.gametext: Deploy on table (only at start of game) and choose an apprentice: Maul: Deploy Desert Landing Site. Dooku: Deploy Invisible Hand: Bridge. Vader: Deploy Vader's Castle. You may not deploy Dark Jedi except [Episode I] Sidious and the chosen apprentice. Your [Episode I] Sidious and the chosen apprentice gain [Sith]. A Sith Legend, Always Two There Are, and Sith are destiny +2. If a Jedi was just lost from same location as your Dark Jedi, opponent loses 1 Force. Opponent may not cancel or reduce Force drains at their battlegrounds where you have a Dark Jedi.
front.title: Revenge Of The Sith

rulings: If unable to deploy the required location, this card fails to deploy and Rise Of The Sith fails to play.

'Opponent may not reduce Force drains' prevents an opponent's card from applying a Force drain -1 modifier (e.g. Projection Of A Skywalker). The following still work:
  • Harc Seff, It Could Be Worse, and We're Doomed may reduce loss from Force drains.
  • Great Warrior and Menace Fades may cancel the Force drain bonuses.
  • Ultimatum may limit the amount of Force lost to Force drains.

front.gametext: LOST: Raise your converted location to the top. STARTING: If your starting location was a battleground, deploy Revenge Of The Sith and up to three Effects that deploy for free and are always immune to Alter. Place Interrupt in hand.
front.lore: Blank.
front.title: ••Rise Of The Sith

rulings: If you used an Objective, you do not have a starting location and cannot play the Starting function of this card.

(Used function) Activation is determined at the beginning of the turn. If a converted location is raised to the top during the activate phase, it will <u>not</u> change the activation amount that turn.

front.gametext: When drawn for destiny, destiny +1 for each Dark Jedi or Jedi on table. Deploy on [Episode I] Sidious (even as a 'react'). May add 1 to Force drain where present. May target a character or creature for free. Draw two destiny. Target hit, and its forfeit = 0, if total destiny > defense value.
front.lore: Blank.
front.title: •Sidious' Lightsaber

pulledBy: I Will Finish What You Started
rulings: Example: If there are 2 Dark Jedi and 0 Jedi, this card is destiny +2.
Example: If there are 2 Dark Jedi and 1 Jedi, this card is destiny +3.
If a destiny draw cannot be modified (e.g. I Don't Like Sand) then this card does not modify its own destiny value, and is destiny 0.

front.gametext: Deploy on table. If Revenge Of The Sith on table, your Sidious may be targeted by Force Lightning and Lord Sidious may use his game text as if alone. Once per game, if Sidious with a Dark Jedi, may retrieve a character into hand. [Immune to Alter.]
front.lore: Blank.
front.title: •Tragedy Of Plagueis

rulings: When using the Force Lightning text, treat all instances of the word 'Emperor' on Force Lightning as 'your Sidious' instead.
When retrieving a character into hand, search entire Lost Pile; do not shuffle.

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Emperor and Maul are lost. At the start of your turn, if Sidious on Coruscant (or Insidious Prisoner on table), may place two cards from hand on Reserve Deck, reshuffle, and draw two cards from Reserve Deck. (Immune to Alter.)
front.lore: Eliciting fear from the opponent gives the dark side a powerful advantage.
front.title: •Unlimited Power!

rulings:
These cards are lost:
  • Emperor Palpatine
  • Emperor Palpatine, Forseer
  • Palpatine, Emperor Returned
  • The Emperor

These cards are not lost:
  • Darth Sidious
  • Lord Sidious
  • Senator Palpatine
If the Light card Senator Palpatine is on Coruscant, the condition (Sidious on Coruscant) has been met.

front.gametext: Opponent may not target your Republic characters with weapons unless each of your [Presence] droids present with them are 'hit.' [Set 8] Where Are Those Droidekas?! ignores Wat Tambor. Once per game, may draw two cards from Reserve Deck.
front.lore: Skakoan leader. Trade Federation. Techno Union.
front.title: •Wat Tambor

rulings: Wat Tambor's first sentence is global, protecting Dark's Republic characters wherever there are Presence droids.
If Wat Tambor is at a site and his game text is canceled, the last sentence on Where Are Those Droidekas?! (V) will not work.

front.gametext: Take an admiral or general into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. OR If your admiral is in battle at a system (or your general is in battle at a site), prevent opponent from drawing more than one battle destiny (and if a moff in battle, your total battle destiny is +1). OR Raise your converted location to the top.
front.title: •Imperial Command & •In Range

rulings: The second function cannot be played with only a moff. Having an admiral or general is required.
An opponent's card that 'draws two battle destiny if unable to otherwise' will circumvent the limit on the second function.

front.gametext: Use 3 Force to take a Neimoidian or an Effect of any kind into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. OR Deploy Blockade Flagship: Bridge from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Blank.
front.title: •Seal Off The Bridge

rulings: The first function may be played at any time. You do not specify in advance whether you are searching for a Neimoidian or an Effect.
The second function (deploying the Bridge) may only be played during your deploy phase, and only if the Bridge is not already on table.

cancels: Force retrieval from General Leia Organa, Rey With Lightsaber, Rey All Of The Jedi, and Rose Tico.

front.errataNotes: Original Text: For remainder of turn, opponent's Force retrieval using Resistance characters' game text is canceled. OR For remainder of turn, opponent may not cancel your battle destiny draws. OR Search opponent's Lost Pile; place one device you find there out of play. OR Cancel It Could Be Worse. OR Cancel Projection Of A Skywalker at an opponent's planet site.
front.gametext: For remainder of turn, opponent may not cancel your battle destiny draws or character weapon destiny draws. OR If you have two battlegrounds on table (and opponent does not), for remainder of turn, your total power in battles is +1 for each opponent's non-battleground location on table. OR Cancel It Could Be Worse or Nabrun Leids. OR If opponent does not occupy a battleground site (or if Menace Fades on table), cancel Projection Of A Skywalker.
front.title: •A Dark Time For The Rebellion & •Tarkin's Orders
front.printableSlipUrl: https://res.starwarsccg.org/vkit/cards/standard/A Dark Time For The Rebellion And Tarkins Orders/image.png

rulings: First function: The number of destiny draws may still be limited, and/or the draws may be prevented from being added.
Second function: Count the number of opponent's non-battlegrounds at the time the Interrupt was played. That is the power bonus for remainder of turn.
Third function: Plays after the opponent pays the cost (using Force for ICBW or Nabrun).
Fourth function: Targets and cancels a specific POAS on table (not both, if there are two copies on table).

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot. While Stele piloting: immune to attrition < 5, game text of Fighters Coming In may not be canceled, and the power of your TIE Defenders here may not be reduced.
front.lore: Blank
front.title: •Alpha 1

pulledBy: Short Range Fighters & Watch Your Back!
rulings: Prevents game text of Fighters Coming In from being 'suspended' by General Leia Organa or Grand Admiral Thrawn (V).
'Power of your TIE Defenders here may not be reduced' protects against all negative modifiers (e.g. Combined Fleet Action or Dash Rendar) and against resets to a lower number (e.g. Power Pivot).

front.gametext: If Visage Of The Emperor on table, deploy on table. At Mustafar, Devastator is deploy -3 and immune to attrition < 6. Once per turn, may deploy Devastator, Mustafar, or a private platform from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. [Immune to Alter.]
front.lore: After dueling his son and seizing control of a city in the clouds, Vader resumed his quest to destroy the Alliance.
front.title: •Crush The Rebellion (V)

rulings: Either virtual or non-virtual Visage Of The Emperor anywhere on table will allow this card to deploy.

cancels: A battle (where a Fett escorting a captive)

front.gametext: For remainder of turn, your Fetts add 1 to their weapon destiny draws and targets they `hit' are forfeit = 0. OR Once per game, cancel a battle just initiated where a Fett is escorting a captive; opponent's cards there move for free this turn. [Immune to Sense.]
front.lore: Blank
front.title: •He's No Good To Me Dead

rulings: The entire Interrupt is immune to Sense.
First function: 'your Fetts' means Dark's cards with a Jango Fett or Boba Fett persona, including Boba Fett In Slave I. It does not affect Light's Boba Fett card.

Second function: All opponent's cards at the location of the battle <u>at the time this Interrupt is played</u> move for free this turn. The battle is canceled first, so opponent's excluded cards become active again and are also targeted to move for free.

cancels: Suspends Menace Fades when conditions are met.

front.gametext: Dark:  While your [Episode VII] objective on table and your First Order leader here, Menace Fades is suspended.  Light:  If Starkiller Base on table, your Force generation is -1 here.
front.title: •Hosnian Prime

rulings: While Menace Fades is suspended, it cannot be targeted to be canceled (e.g. by Alter).

front.gametext: If Revenge Of The Sith on table, choose: If a Dark Jedi is in battle with an opponent's character of ability > 3, add one battle destiny. OR During your move phase, use 2 Force to relocate your apprentice from an [Episode I] site to another site.
front.lore: 'Several fighters have broken off from the main group. Come with me.' Darth Vader targets his TIE fighter's fire-linked blaster cannons at the Rebel pilots in the trench.
front.title: I Have You Now (V)

rulings: Both functions require Revenge Of The Sith on table to play.
First function: Play during weapons segment. The battle destiny is then added even if the conditions for it are no longer met later.
Second function: The destination site does not need to be an Episode I site.
Second function: The character may not move to or from a pilot/passenger slot of a starship or vehicle.
Second function: The word 'apprentice' <u>only</u> refers to the apprentice chosen by Revenge Of The Sith (it is not referring to characters with 'apprentice' in title or lore).

front.gametext: Dark:  If you control Podrace Arena, Force drain +1 here.  Light:  If opponent controls Podrace Arena, Force drain -1 here.
front.title: •Malastare (V)

rulings: It is possible for a player to control Tatooine: Podrace Arena regardless of whether there is a podrace occurring there.

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Once per game, may deploy Sebulba from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Once per turn, may deploy Malastare or Podrace Arena from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. While present with Sebulba, Jar Jar's game text is canceled. [Immune to Alter.]
front.lore: 'Your buddy here was about to be turned into orange goo. He picked a fight with a Dug. An especially dangerous Dug called Sebulba.'
front.title: •Ni Chuba Na?? (V)

rulings: In a single turn, may deploy Sebulba as well as one of either Malastare or Podrace Arena. Note that these are separate top-level actions.
In order for Sebulba to be present with Jar Jar, neither of them can be inside a starship or an enclosed vehicle.

back.gametext: A Great Tactician Creates Plans: Deploy Lothal system, Advanced Projects Laboratory, Imperial Complex, and Thrawn's Art Collection. For remainder of game, you may not deploy Chiraneau or [Episode I] (or [Episode VII]) cards with ability or [Presence]. Once per turn, may deploy a battleground system (or a site to Lothal) from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. While this side up, Imperial Star Destroyers deploy -1 (-3 if Chimaera). Flip this card during any deploy phase if Thrawn at a battleground and two artwork cards on table. The Result Is Often Resentment: While this side up, if a battle was just initiated involving an Imperial leader or piloted TIE defender, may 'study' one artwork card. If it is a weapon, cancel the battle. Otherwise, if possible, if its printed destiny number is: (0-2) opponent's immunity to attrition is canceled; (3-4) opponent excludes their character from battle; (5+) add 3 to your total power. Place artwork card in owner's Lost Pile. Flip this card if Thrawn not on table or (except during battle) if no artwork cards on table.
back.title: A Great Tactician Creates Plans / The Result Is Often Resentment

front.errataNotes: Original could not deploy any admirals except Thrawn, and pulling sites/systems was only while on the 0-side.
front.gametext: A Great Tactician Creates Plans: Deploy Lothal system, Advanced Projects Laboratory, Imperial Complex, and Thrawn's Art Collection. For remainder of game, you may not deploy Chiraneau or [Episode I] (or [Episode VII]) cards with ability or [Presence]. Once per turn, may deploy a battleground system (or a site to Lothal) from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. While this side up, Imperial Star Destroyers deploy -1 (-3 if Chimaera). Flip this card during any deploy phase if Thrawn at a battleground and two artwork cards on table. The Result Is Often Resentment: While this side up, if a battle was just initiated involving an Imperial leader or piloted TIE defender, may 'study' one artwork card. If it is a weapon, cancel the battle. Otherwise, if possible, if its printed destiny number is: (0-2) opponent's immunity to attrition is canceled; (3-4) opponent excludes their character from battle; (5+) add 3 to your total power. Place artwork card in owner's Lost Pile. Flip this card if Thrawn not on table or (except during battle) if no artwork cards on table.
front.title: A Great Tactician Creates Plans / The Result Is Often Resentment

rulings: (Both sides) This Objective must flip as an automatic action as soon as the flip conditions are met.
(0-side) 'Flip this card during any deploy phase' means it will flip during either player's deploy phase.
(0-side) 'Imperial Star Destroyers' refers to Imperial affiliation (not First Order, Rebel, Independent, etc).  It does not refer to Imperial-class. Thus Dominator and Executor are deploy -1.

(7-side) After studying an artwork card, place it in Lost Pile even if it was not possible to perform the specified action (e.g., even if there was no character to exclude from battle or no immunity to attrition to cancel).
(7-side) For a multi-destiny artwork card such as R2-D2, the destiny value is chosen by the card owner (typically Light) <u>after</u> Dark chooses it to be studied.

front.gametext: May add 6 pilots, 6 passengers, and 4 TIEs. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. While Thrawn piloting, immune to attrition < 5 and game text of We're In Attack Position Now may not be canceled.
front.lore: Early model Imperial-class Star Destroyer. Acting command ship in the absence of Executor.
front.title: •Chimaera (V)

rulings: With Thrawn aboard, the game text of We're In Attack Position Now cannot be canceled/suspended by General Leia Organa.
Kuat Drive Yards (V) will still cancel the entire We're In Attack Position Now card, sending it to Lost Pile.

If General Leia Organa is currently suspending WIAPN, and then Dark uses Alert My Star Destroyer (V) to deploy Chimaera (V) with Thrawn aboard simultaneously, the discount from WIAPN is not applied (Dark pays the deploy cost first, before WIAPN gets un-suspended).

front.gametext: [Pilot] 2. Your total battle destiny at sites is +1 for each of your participating [Presence] droids that has a [Permanent Weapon] weapon but did not fire it in that battle. Weapon destinies at same system are -1.
front.lore: Neimoidian Trade Federation captain who gained his current position through political backstabbing and family connections. Not favored by Darth Sidious.
front.title: •Daultay Dofine (V)

rulings: If a [Presence] droid attempts to fire its permanent weapon and the firing is canceled, then the weapon did not fire, so Dofine gives +1 to total battle destiny.

front.gametext: Power and forfeit +2 at a Coruscant location. At the beginning of opponent's control phase, if present with opponent's character, `sell death sticks' (opponent must use or lose 1 Force; if a Jedi present, also place Elan in Used Pile).
front.lore: Balosar information broker.
front.title: •Elan Sleazebaggano

front.gametext: [Pilot] 2: any capital starship. While with Thrawn, your starships here are power and hyperspeed +1. During your control phase, may use 1 Force to take a card with 'artwork' or 'studied' in game text into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Blank
front.title: •Ensign Eli Vanto

front.gametext: If you just initiated battle here, battle damage against you here this turn is canceled. Once per turn, may target opponent's non-'hit' character here. If Fennec on table when target lost this turn, opponent loses 1 Force.
front.lore: Female assassin, bounty hunter, and mercenary.
front.title: •Fennec Shand

rulings: Fennec schedules the prevention of battle damage as an automatic response to initiating battle, which will then occur even if Fennec is subsequently removed from table or excluded from battle.
If Fennec is to be automatically excluded (e.g. due to being targeted by Rebel Barrier earlier that turn), her exclusion and the prevention of battle damage are competing automatic actions.
Fennec's 'once per turn' function schedules potential Force loss which may occur later even if Fennec's game text is subsequently canceled.

front.gametext: If an artwork card was just stacked (or a Rebel was just captured here), may take a card without ability into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. While in a battle you lost, unless 'hit' (or no other Imperials present), Pryce may not be forfeited. Immune to attrition < 4.
front.lore: Female leader and miner.
front.title: •Governor Pryce

rulings: If Pryce is with (for example) Emperor Palpatine and Dark is facing 5 attrition (so Pryce is not immune), Dark must satisfy the attrition, but cannot forfeit Pryce; therefore Dark must forfeit Emperor Palpatine in this scenario.

front.gametext: LOST: Deploy [Episode I] Coruscant from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. STARTING: If A Stunning Move on table, deploy three Effects that deploy on your side of table, deploy for free, and are always immune to Alter. Place Interrupt in hand.
front.lore: Blank
front.title: •Grievous' Gambit

front.gametext: USED: During battle, add 1 to your total battle destiny for each artwork card on table. LOST: Once per game, if your [Set 19] objective just `studied' an Interrupt, you may take one Interrupt into hand from Lost Pile.
front.lore: Blank
front.title: •History, Philosophy, And Art

rulings: The phrase 'artwork card on table' refers to cards stacked on Thrawn's Art Collection.

front.errataNotes: E1 was a 2/0 system with this text: Dark: While you occupy with an admiral, gains one [Dark Side] icon. Light: While you control, opponent occupies with an admiral, or Lothal converted, gains one [Light Side] icon. Original was a 2/1 system with this text: Dark: While you control, at related battleground sites you control with an Imperial leader, your Force drains are +1. Light: If Ghost and Phantom piloted here, Force drain +1 here. If no Rebel starships piloted here, Force drain -1 here.
front.gametext: Dark: While you occupy, gains one [Dark Side] icon. Light: While you occupy, gains one [Light Side] icon. Unless Ghost or Phantom piloted here, Force drain -1 here.
front.title: •Lothal

front.errataNotes: Original Dark Text could not pull Pryce. Original Light Text: Opponent may not reduce or cancel your Force drains here.
front.gametext: Dark: Once per game, may deploy TIE Defender Project, Pryce, or Thrawn here from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Light: Opponent may not reduce or cancel your Force drains here.
front.title: •Lothal: Advanced Projects Laboratory

front.gametext: Dark: Rukh, Imperials, AT-DPs, AT-STs, and speeder bikes are power and defense value +1 here. Light: While you occupy, your Imperial Complex game text is canceled.
front.title: •Lothal: Capital City

rulings: Dark's text even increases the power and defense value of relevant LS cards (such as Chewie's AT-ST or a Light side Speeder Bike).

front.gametext: Dark: If you control with a leader, once per battle at a related site, you may deploy a card as a `react'. Light: Your non-Rebel characters deploy +1 here.
front.title: •Lothal: Imperial Complex

rulings: Only characters, vehicles, starships, weapons, and devices may be deployed as a react.

front.gametext: Dark: If your miner present, your Force generation is +2 here. Light: If you control, your Force generation is +1 here.
front.title: •Lothal: Imperial Strip Mines

rulings: The Underground icon does not prevent cards from shuttling between this site and the Lothal system.

front.gametext: While present at a battleground site and you control more systems than opponent, Force drain +1 here. Power and defense value +2 while Thrawn at a system with a parsec number > 5. Immune to attrition < 3.
front.lore: Female leader.
front.title: •Magistrate Morgan Elsbeth

front.gametext: Deploy on table. When deployed, may take the top card of Lost Pile into hand. During your move phase, may cancel Landing Claw (then place it out of play from Lost Pile). Elis Helrot and Nabrun Leids are unique (•) and are Lost Interrupts. [Immune to Alter.]
front.lore: Jabba's influence is not easily ignored. Neither are his voracious and vile appetites. Even Jedi soon learn this lesson.
front.title: •No Escape (V)

front.gametext: Deploy on your interior site. If opponent just deployed a character or vehicle here, may lose 1 Force to move your character to here using landspeed (at normal use of the Force). Opponent may not 'react' to here. May place out of play to draw top card of Reserve Deck.
front.lore: Remote surveillance viewers with droid controllers supplement security. Can activate alarms and automated weapons when needed, bringing help to endangered locations.
front.title: Observation Holocam (V)

rulings: The movement action requires the loss of 1 Force as well as the normal movement cost (e.g. for most characters, Dark will lose 1 Force and then use 1 Force.  For EPP Mara with her conditions met, Dark will lose 1 Force and then move her for free).

front.gametext: USED: During battle, target a character present with [Set 13] Dooku. Target is power -3. LOST: If lightsaber combat was just initiated, add one destiny to your total. OR If [Set 13] Dooku on table, deploy Dooku's Lightsaber from Lost Pile.
front.lore: Those who can use the Force are able to manipulate the objects around them to their advantage.
front.title: •Surely You Can Do Better

rulings: The first Lost function of this Interrupt adds a lightsaber combat destiny. Therefore a player with Deep Hatred on table may instead use a combat card.

front.gametext: Destiny +1 for each Black Sun agent or Jedi on table (limit +5) when drawn for destiny. Deploys only to Coruscant. Never deploys or moves (even if carried) to a site opponent occupies. May cancel Projection Of A Skywalker here. Immune to attrition.
front.lore: Leader. Secretive manipulator of the galaxy. Played Darth Vader and Prince Xizor off against one another in his relentless pursuit of 'young Skywalker.'
front.title: •The Emperor (V)

rulings: To determine destiny bonus, count up all cards that are either Black Sun agents or Jedi (e.g. if there are 3 Black Sun agents and 1 Jedi, then The Emperor is destiny +4).
Do not count inactive cards such as a captive Jedi.

front.gametext: USED: Add 1 to hyperspeed of a dreadnaught or Star Destroyer for each artwork card on table for remainder of turn. LOST: Once per game, if your [Set 19] objective just `studied' a vehicle or starship, relocate your Star Destroyer from anywhere on table to that battle.
front.lore: The Empire's efficient, fear-driven logistical systems can quickly divert weapons and equipment from one conflict to another, focusing on regions of highest strategic priority.
front.title: •Thrawn Pincer

rulings: (USED) The phrase 'artwork card on table' refers to cards stacked on Thrawn's Art Collection.
(USED) When Dark has (for example) 3 artwork cards, this Interrupt gives +3 hyperspeed to 1 starship, not +1 hyperspeed to 3 starships.
(USED) Can be played ('cycled') with 0 artwork cards to add 0 to hyperspeed (but there must be a dreadnaught or Star Destroyer to target).

(USED) The hyperspeed bonus is a one time adjustment counted up and applied at the time when the Interrupt is played.  The hyperspeed bonus does not fluctuate as additional artwork cards are stacked or removed later on in the turn.
(LOST) Can relocate to a location outside of normal movement range
(LOST) Can even relocate to and/or from an asteroid sector

front.gametext: Use 4 Force to deploy on table. If you just initiated a Force drain (or won a battle) at same battleground as Thrawn, opponent loses 1 Force (cannot be reduced) and stacks it here face up. (These stacked cards are artwork cards.) [Immune to Alter.]
front.lore: Blank
front.title: •Thrawn's Art Collection

front.gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, and 4 TIEs. While Khurgee aboard, power, armor, and hyperspeed +2. While Death Star II on table, Thunderflare moves for free. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2.
front.lore: Overpowered Star Destroyer. Energy is transferred from hyperdrive to weapons. Patrol duties in the Core Worlds make it a common first assignment for junior officers.
front.title: •Thunderflare (V)

front.gametext: Permanent weapon is Hunting Rifle (may target a character or creature; draw destiny; target hit and forfeit -2 if destiny +1 > defense value. If firing from Dune Sea, Jundland Wastes, or a canyon, targets at an adjacent site or adds 1 to weapon destiny).
front.lore: Blank
front.title: Tusken Raider With Hunting Rifle

rulings: The last sentence of this card causes him to automatically add 1 to total weapon destiny unless firing at an adjacent site, in which case he does not add 1.

front.gametext: USED: Target a character in battle. Target and cards that share any characteristic with target are power and forfeit -1. LOST: Once per game, if your [Set 19] objective just `studied' a character, add one battle destiny (two if a character of same species is participating in battle).
front.lore: The Empire considers alien species to be inferior.
front.title: •Understand Art, Understand A Species

rulings: (USED) A list of all characteristics is provided in Appendix D of the Advanced Rulebook.
(USED) For example, if targeting Captain Han Solo, all captains, smugglers, Corellians, and scoundrels in the battle are power and forfeit -1.
(USED) Change lasts until the end of the battle.
(USED) The initial target can even belong to Dark player, but all the additional affected characters are still opponent's only.
(USED) May be used even if no other cards share any characteristic with target.
(USED) Only character cards have characteristics, so only character cards can be made power and forfeit -1.
(LOST) The 'character of same species' may even be an exact duplicate of the studied card.

front.gametext: Your battle destiny draws here are +¬ for each device, droid, starship, vehicle, or weapon card here. During battle with an opponent's droid, adds one destiny to total power. Once per game, may retrieve a device or character weapon.
front.lore: Crolute scavenger and thief.
front.title: •Unkar Plutt

rulings: R2-D2 & C-3PO is 1 droid. Intimidator & Persecutor is 1 starship. X-wing Assault Squadron is 1 starship.

front.gametext: [Pilot] 3. If alone and a battle was just initiated here, may take Lightsaber Parry, Physical Choke, or Vader's Anger into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Opponent's non-Jedi characters here are power and forfeit -1. Immune to attrition < 5 (< 7 if with a Jedi).
front.lore: Sought to extinguish all Jedi. Former student of Obi-Wan Kenobi. Seduced by the dark side of the Force.
front.title: •Vader (V)

front.gametext: Deploy on [Episode I] Vader. May add 1 to Force drain where present. May target a character or creature for free. Draw two destiny. Subtract 1 if targeting Obi-Wan. Add 1 if targeting a Padawan. Target hit, and its forfeit = 0, if total destiny > defense value.
front.lore: Custom-built by Darth Vader. After the Clone Wars, he wielded this weapon while hunting down the last of the Jedi. Cuts through almost anything except another lightsaber blade.
front.title: •Vader's Lightsaber (V)

rulings: If targeting Obi-Wan Kenobi, Padawan Learner, both the -1 and the +1 are applied (effectively canceling out).

front.gametext: [0] Corscant [1] Carida, Corellia, Eriadu, Kirdo III, Kuat [2] Alderaan, Bothuwui, Kiffex, Rendili, Tibrin, Wakeelmui [3] Malastare, Nal Hutta, Raithal, Ralltiir [4] Aquaris, Chandrila, Corulag, Yavin 4* [5] Anoat, Dantooine, Hoth*, Naboo [6] Bespin, Fondor, Kashyyyk, Mon Calamari [7] Clak'dor VII, Ord Mantell, Roche, Sullust, Tatooine [8] Endor, Kessel [9] Dagobah, Gall * Known Rebel Base
front.title: Hyperoute Navigation Chart (V)

combo: Grand Admiral Thrawn at a system or site + Imperial Command

front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. if a Rebel just moved from here, your Imperials present may follow that character (using landspeed). While at a battleground site, functions as a general and game text of Admiral's Orders is canceled.
front.lore: The last remaining Grand Admiral. Found legendary Katana fleet of missing dreadnaughts. Military genius. Master of unorthodox tactics. Passionate collector of art. Leader.
front.title: •Grand Admiral Thrawn (V) (AI)

front.gametext: Jabba's game text is canceled. While with two aliens, adds one destiny to attrition. While at Audience Chamber, your Force drains at other Tatooine battlegrounds are +1 and, if opponent just deployed a character here, may activate 1 Force.
front.lore: Twi'lek gangster. Leader. Plotted to kill Jabba.
front.title: •Bib Fortuna, Heir To The Palace

rulings: The 'two aliens' can be both Dark, both Light, or one of each. Bib does not count as one of the aliens.
The phrase 'may activate 1 Force' means Dark may activate, not the opponent.

front.gametext: Plays on table. At end of a turn, if opponent has 15 or more cards in hand, may use 2 Force to shuffle all but 9 (random selection) into Used Pile. If Grimtaash or Thrown Back just targeted your hand, may reveal 2 cards from hand; they cannot be removed or checked for duplicates.
front.lore: Anakin had to heed Qui-Gon's advice to avoid the rapidly approaching storm.
front.title: •Drop! (V)

rulings: A player may view cards that are being removed from their own hand.
When 2 cards are revealed to prevent them from being placed in Used Pile, the hand will still be reduced to the size required by Grimtaash or Thrown Back.

If a player has 2 of the same card and reveals 1 to prevent it from being checked for duplicates, the other copy is not lost. If a player has 3 of the same card and reveals 2 of them, the other copy is not lost. If a player has 3 of the same card and reveals only 1 of them, the other 2 are duplicates of each other and are lost.

front.gametext: Dark: If you control, your total power is +1 at Ralltiir sites. Light: Your characters shuttle to and from here for free.
front.title: •Ralltiir (V)

front.gametext: Deploys +3 to your location. Obi-Wan is not a general. Once per turn, if opponent's card just moved from here, opponent loses 1 Force. Your characters here move (using landspeed) to sites opponent occupies for free. Immune to attrition < 4.
front.lore: Female Inquisitor.
front.title: •Third Sister

rulings: Third Sister only checks for movement of characters, vehicles, and starships.
Third Sister affects the Obi-Wan persona globally. This prevents Rebel Leadership (V) from taking General Kenobi into hand from Reserve Deck.

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Power and defense value +2 with 4-LOM. Once during battle, if opponent just drew weapon or battle destiny, may draw destiny; reset opponent's destiny number to your drawn destiny number. Immune to attrition < 3.
front.lore: Male Gand. Practitioner of ancient religious findsman vocation. Bounty hunter and scout. Gains surprisingly accurate information through mystical visions during meditation.
front.title: •Zuckuss (V)

combo: 4-LOM With Concussion Rifle + Boba Fett, Bounty Hunter Two battle destinies.

front.gametext: Permanent weapon is •4-LOM's Concussion Rifle (may target a character for free; target is power -1 until end of turn).  Once per turn, may place a card from hand on bottom of Used Pile to draw top card from Reserve Deck.
front.lore: Accomplished thief and information broker. Modified by Jabba to be an effective bounty hunter. The Hutt often teams 4-LOM with other hired killers.
front.title: •4-LOM With Concussion Rifle (V) (AI)

rulings: This weapon is not a blaster.

front.gametext: Draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise. Attrition against opponent is +1 here.
front.lore: Blank.
front.title: •••B2 Battle Droid (AI)

front.gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles, and 4 TIEs. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2. During battle, may lose 1 Force to cancel a non-[Immune to Sense] Interrupt.
front.lore: One of the Imperial cruisers that chased the Millennium Falcon from Tatooine. It scanned the Falcon just before Han punched his starship to lightspeed.
front.title: •Conquest (V) (AI)

rulings: May only cancel one Interrupt per battle.
Only check if the currently played Interrupt function is immune to Sense. If not, it may be canceled.

front.gametext: Deploys -1 if Sidious (or Insidious Prisoner) on table. Power +1 for each Jedi here. May be targeted by Force Lightning. Once per game, if opponent just initiated battle here, may take Force Lightning or Force Push into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Immune to attrition < 6 (< 8 if with a Jedi).
front.lore: Serrennoian leader. Trade Federation.
front.title: •Count Dooku (AI)

rulings: When using this text, treat all instances of the word 'Emperor' on Force Lightning as 'Dooku' instead.

combo: Darth Maul, Lone Hunter + Maul Strikes
Darth Maul, Lone Hunter + The Phantom Menace While present with an opponent's Jedi, Maul is defense value +2 and immune to attrition.
Darth Maul, Lone Hunter + I Have You Now Add one battle destiny (two if Rebel is Luke) if a Dark Jedi and a Rebel with ability > 2 are involved in the same battle.
Darth Maul, Lone Hunter + Force Field Cancels an attempt to target a Dark Jedi with a character weapon.

front.gametext: If drawn for destiny, may take into hand to cancel and redraw that destiny. Cancels Blaster Deflection (and Amidala's game text) here. Maul's weapon destiny draws may not be modified or canceled by opponent. Immune to attrition < 5.
front.lore: Trade Federation.
front.title: •Darth Maul, Lone Hunter (AI)

rulings: Cancels game text of any version of the Amidala persona, including Padme.

front.gametext: Deploy on Dooku or a [Separatist] character of ability > 4. Adds 1 to this character's duel and lightsaber combat totals. May add 1 to Force drain where present. May target a character for free. Draw two destiny. Target hit, and its forfeit = 0, if total destiny > defense value.
front.lore: Blank.
front.title: •Dooku's Lightsaber (AI)

pulledBy: I Will Finish What You Started

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Unless alone, may place Trench in Used Pile to make an [Episode I] starship here immune to attrition for remainder of turn. While at opponent's system, their starships deploy +1 here.
front.lore: Harch commander. Leader. Trade Federation.
front.title: •Admiral Trench (AI)

front.gametext: Deploys -2 to Mustafar. May add 1 pilot and 3 passengers. Permanent pilot is •Jendon, who provides ability of 2. If Vader armed with a lightsaber weapon card at a battleground, Force drain +1 here.
front.lore: Customized transport of Lord Vader. Employs advanced sensor jamming gear. Modified with enhanced tactical displays constructed to the Dark Lord's specifications.
front.title: •Colonel Jendon In Vader's Personal Shuttle

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Your Gamorreans, Niktos, and Weequays are guards. Your guards are forfeit +1. Your alien leaders with your guard are defense value +1. During battle, may reduce a character's defense value by 1 for each of your guards present. [Immune to Alter.]
front.lore: Most of Jabba's guards had been sold to the Hutt and were too scared (or too dumb) to leave. Jabba assigned his best guards to watch over his most prized possessions.
front.title: •Well Guarded (V)

front.gametext: For remainder of turn, your speeder bikes are power and forfeit +1. OR Subtract 2 from a just drawn destiny targeting the ability or defense value of a biker scout piloting a speeder bike.
front.lore: The Empire trains its personnel to operate a variety of specialized equipment in demanding environments. This training allows troops to take seemingly risky actions.
front.title: Accelerate (V)

front.gametext: Deploys -1 if Dooku on table. Whenever a player loses a battle here, that player loses 1 Force. While armed, opponent's weapon destiny draws targeting Ventress are -1. Opponent may not cancel battles here. Immune to [Permanent Weapon] weapons and attrition < 4.
front.lore: Female Dathomirian assassin.
front.title: •Asajj Ventress

front.gametext: Deploy on a Sith. If present at opponent's site, may add 1 to Force drain here. May target a character (twice per battle if on Ventress). Draw two destiny. Subtract 2 from total if this weapon already fired this battle. Target hit, and its forfeit = 0, if total destiny > defense value.
front.lore: Blank
front.title: •Asajj Ventress' Lightsabers

front.gametext: Power +1 if Stardust or Stolen Data Tapes on table. While with another trooper, attrition against opponent here is +1. During your move phase, when moving with a 'squad' of up to two other stormtroopers, they all move (using landspeed) for 1 Force.
front.lore: Captain Mod Terrik, a typical officer of the Desert Sands sandtrooper unit. Fearless and highly motivated. Willing to sacrifice as many troops as necessary. Leader.
front.title: •Captain Mod Terrik

front.gametext: Dark: If Vader's Malediction on table and Vader alone here, opponent's Interrupts are Lost Interrupts. Light: If you occupy, opponent's Chasm Walkway game text here is canceled. May not be converted.
front.title: •Cloud City: Chasm Walkway (V)

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. While aboard Devastator, adds 1 to armor and hyperspeed and, once during your deploy phase, your trooper at a related site may make a regular move using landspeed.
front.lore: Vader's aide on the Devastator. Personally supervised search for Death Star plans on Tatooine by Vader's order. Was graduated with honors from Imperial Navy Academy on Carida.
front.title: •Commander Praji (V)

front.gametext: During your turn, target opponent's spy at a site you control; target is lost. (Immune to Droid Shutdown.) [Immune to Sense.] OR Cancel Dodge, I Think I Can Handle Myself, or a Force drain initiated by a lone Falcon. OR Target a starship weapon; it may not fire this turn.
front.lore: The Imperial Navy boasts the best communications network in the galaxy. Sophisticated control technology allows the Empire to dispatch armed forces without delay.
front.title: ComScan Detection (V)

front.gametext: Adds 3 to power of any speeder bike he pilots. While piloting a speeder bike, draws one battle destiny if unable to otherwise. Once per game, may take a speeder bike (or an Effect with 'speeder bike' in game text) into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Frequently engaged in brawls at the local enlisted clubs on homeworld of Corulag. Stormtrooper assigned to biker scout unit. Monitors Yuzzum activity.
front.title: •Corporal Avarik (V)

front.gametext: Deploys -1 to Endor. Your Lando and your [Endor] leaders may not be targeted by weapons here. While at a Cloud City site, modifiers to Force drains here may not be canceled. Once per game, may take Blasted Droid into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
front.lore: Stormtrooper assigned to Commander Igar's honor guard. Accompanied Vader on Drazin's homeworld of Bespin. Shot C-3PO there.
front.title: •Corporal Drazin (V)

front.gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots (3 if a speeder bike). When deployed, may deploy a battleground or speeder bike from Used Pile; reshuffle. When firing a Scout Blaster, adds 1 to his total weapon destiny (2 if targeting an alien).
front.lore: Originally from Ukio. Stormtrooper assigned to search for Rebel activity on Endor. Trying to impress the commander of his biker scout detachment.
front.title: •Corporal Oberk (V)

front.gametext: Cancel Rebel Barrier. OR If your non-Ozzel ISB agent leader in battle, cancel It's A Trap! or opponent's 'react' away from that battle. OR If three non-Ozzel ISB agent leaders are in battle together, add two battle destiny.
front.lore: Imperial leaders are ruthlessly effective when working together. Tarkin, Motti and Tagge presented a deadly combination as they plotted to, 'crush the Rebellion.'
front.title: •Dark Collaboration (V)

front.gametext: Deploy on table. [Reflections III] Falcon loses immunity to attrition. During opponent's draw phase, if you occupy a battleground site and opponent does not, may place in Used Pile (if Systems Will Slip Through Your Fingers or a 'liberated' system on table, opponent loses 3 Force).
front.lore: Blank
front.title: •Deactivated Hyperdrive

front.gametext: May add 3 pilots and 6 passengers. Permanent pilot provides ability of 3. Deploys and moves like a starfighter. Your total battle destiny here is +1 for each gangster aboard. Immune to attrition < 5.
front.lore: Crimson Dawn.
front.title: •First Light

front.gametext: Your non-[Maintenance] troopers have armor = 4. At same and adjacent sites where you have a non-pilot trooper, your total power is +3. Once per game, if with two troopers, may re-circulate.
front.lore: Oversees defense operations of Death Star. Outstanding tactician. No-nonsense leader. Member of House of Tagge, a powerful noble family and corporate conglomerate.
front.title: •General Tagge (V)

front.gametext: Deploy on table. I Must Be Allowed To Speak may only target opponent's locations (even if converted). At Tatooine battlegrounds where you have an alien and a gambler, gangster, or Dug, Force drains may not be canceled or reduced by opponent. [Immune to Alter.]
front.lore: Jabba's criminal empire extends to all reaches of the Outer Rim.
front.title: •Hutt Influence (V)

front.gametext: Deploy on a location. At same battleground, opponent may not cancel or reduce your Force drains here. You initiate battles here for free. If you just initiated battle here, may draw top card of Reserve Deck. Total battle destiny and forfeit values may not be increased here.
front.lore: Full Imperial scans include full-spectrum transceivers, dedicated energy receptors, crystal gravfield traps, and hyperwave signal interceptors.
front.title: Hyperwave Scan (V)

front.gametext: Dark: During your move phase, your [Episode VII] characters may move from here to a battleground site. Light: If Finn or Rey here, opponent's First Order characters may not move from here.
front.title: •Jakku: Niima Marketplace

front.gametext: Deploy on table. May deploy Cantina from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Your Cantina may not be converted. Once per turn, if you just deployed an alien to Cantina, may peek at the top two cards of your Reserve Deck; take one into hand and shuffle your Reserve Deck. Immune to Blue Milk. [Immune to Alter.]
front.lore: Popular beverage served in many cantinas and tapcafes. Has intoxicating effect on many species. Favorite drink of Kabe, Chadra-Fan thief of Mos Eisley.
front.title: •Juri Juice (V)

front.gametext: When deployed, may target an opponent's spy present to be power = 0 until end of turn. Once per turn, if an ISB agent on table, may place a card from hand on Used Pile; the next ISB agent you deploy this turn is deploy -1.
front.lore: Female ISB leader.
front.title: •Lieutenant Dedra Meero

front.gametext: When deployed, may shuffle any player's Reserve Deck, Lost Pile, or Used Pile. ISB agent leaders at same and related sites (or at all locations while Partagaz present at a Coruscant site) are power and defense value +1.
front.lore: ISB leader.
front.title: •Major Partagaz

front.gametext: Deploy on table. While Nal Hutta on table and your alien at Audience Chamber, [Reflections III] Leia's game text is canceled and, once during opponent's turn, may activate 1 Force. Once per turn, may deploy Hutt Influence, Bib, or a barge from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. [Immune to Alter.]
front.lore: Jabba runs his organization out of a palace built around a B'omarr monastery. His fortress near the border of the western Dune Sea is safe from enemies in Mos Eisley.
front.title: •Power Of The Hutt (V)

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Your scouts piloting speeder bikes are defense value = 5 and immune to Clash Of Sabers. Once per game, your speeder bike piloted by a scout may follow an opponent's character that just moved from same site. [Immune to Alter.]
front.lore: When away from the Imperial Palace on Coruscant, the Emperor is protected by legions of troops. Typically this force includes soldiers trained to fight in the local environment.
front.title: •Royal Escort (V)

front.gametext: Deploy on table. While you occupy Tatooine system, your Force generation is +1 at Tatooine sites you occupy with a trooper and, during your deploy phase, may exchange a non-[Maintenance] Imperial trooper in hand with one in Reserve Deck; reshuffle. [Immune to Alter.]
front.lore: Vader sent Imperial stormtroopers to the surface of Tatooine in search of the stolen Death Star plans. 'There'll be no one to stop us this time.'
front.title: •Send a Detachment Down (V)

front.gametext: When deployed, power +2 for remainder of turn. During battle with two of your troopers (or two ISB agents), may target a Rebel present with Tarl; target is immune to attrition and target's game text is canceled.
front.lore: Took part in the capture of the Rebel Blockade Runner Tantive IV. Stormtrooper trained on Corulag. Corellia native.
front.title: •Sergeant Tarl (V)

front.gametext: During battle, add one battle destiny.
front.lore: Using the power of the dark side, Vader caused Luke to lose his confidence and question his sense of direction.
front.title: •Shattered Hope (V)

front.gametext: Dark: Once per turn, may deploy Djas Puhr, Tonnika Sisters, or [Jabba's Palace] Wuher here from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Light: Unless Obi-Wan here (or at Mos Eisley), you may not move to here during your control phase.
front.title: •Tatooine: Cantina (V)

front.gametext: Dark: If Jabba at Audience Chamber, [Set 4] Jabba's Sail Barge deploys -2 here. Light: Once per game, may deploy Boba Fett here from Reserve Deck (reshuffle) or Lost Pile.
front.title: •Tatooine: Great Pit of Carkoon (V)

front.gametext: Dark: Once per turn, if your Imperial here, may deploy a [Hoth] device from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. Light: Once per turn, a player who controls this site may raise their converted related location to the top.
front.title: •Tatooine: Imperial Landing Site

front.gametext: Dark: If your trooper here and no aliens on Tatooine, Force drain +1 at Jawa Camp. Light: Jawas deploy here for 1 Force from their owner only. Obi-Wan moves to here for free.
front.title: •Tatooine: Jawa Camp (V)

front.gametext: Dark: Imperial stormtroopers here are forfeit +1 (and power +1 if a sandtrooper). Light: Imperial stormtroopers here may not be targeted by Clash Of Sabers or blasters.
front.title: •Tatooine: Mos Eisley (V)

front.gametext: Deploy on table. During your control phase, if you occupy Tatooine system, opponent loses 1 Force for each Tatooine battleground site you occupy with a unique (•) trooper. While you have three troopers on Tatooine, immune to Alter and Endor Celebration.
front.lore: Sandtroopers commanded by Governor Aryon do not enjoy their assignment. They find a means of venting their frustrations by harassing the local inhabitants.
front.title: •Tatooine Occupation (V)

front.gametext: Once per game, may reveal from hand to take a dewback into hand from outside your deck and deploy both simultaneously. Deploys -2 aboard a dewback. Your characters aboard dewbacks here may not be targeted by axes or lightsabers.
front.lore: Sandtrooper.
front.title: •TD-4445

rulings: Once the Dewback is brought into play, it is treated as any normal card. It goes to Lost Pile when forfeited, can be retrieved, etc.

front.gametext: Deploy on table. Rebel Barrier is a Lost Interrupt. If no card stacked here, may stack one Interrupt just played here. To play any new Interrupt of the same name, player must first stack it here. Once per game, may shuffle any deck or pile. [Immune to Alter.]
front.lore: Dianogas use their seven tentacles for both locomotion and catching food. The few survivors of such attacks claim that a dianoga tentacle has the strength of a hydro-clamp.
front.title: Tentacle (V)

front.gametext: If Vader is your apprentice, deploy on table. Vader's game text may not be canceled. While Vader alone, armed with a [Death Star II] lightsaber, and present at a site, your Force drains there are +1. If you just drew Vader for destiny, may take him into hand. [Immune to Alter.]
front.lore: '... And together, we can rule the galaxy as father and son!'
front.title: •Vader's Malediction

front.gametext: If Vader is your apprentice, choose: take The Works into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. OR Cancel Uncontrollable Fury. (Immune to Run Luke, Run!) OR At start of your battle phase, move Vader (using landspeed) to a site you do not occupy.
front.lore: Vader sought to hunt down and destroy all Jedi. After completing the circle with Obi-Wan, he turned his attention to the young Skywalker.
front.title: •Vader's Obsession (V)

front.gametext: May add 1 pilot. Permanent pilots are •Zuckuss, who provides ability of 4, and •4-LOM. Players may not add power destinies or draw more than one battle destiny here. Immune to attrition < 5.
front.lore: Commissioned by a group of Gand venture capitalists headed by Zuckuss. Manufactured by Byblos Drive Yards. Uses repulsorlift technology developed for combat cloud cars.
front.title: •Zuckuss And 4-LOM In Mist Hunter
